items.name: 12-Gauge Buckshot Shell
items.description: 12-Gauge Buckshot Shell, the basic ammunition used by Shotguns . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts, this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered.

items.name: 12-Gauge CHAC Shell
items.description: 12-Gauge CHAC Shell is an advanced purchaseable buckshot ammunition that does up to 450 damage. It pairs well with the CHAC "Boomstick" Shotgun that can also be purchased from the Workshop .

items.name: 12-Gauge CHAC Shell Box
items.description: The 12-Gauge CHAC Shell Box provides 25 rounds of the 12-Gauge CHAC Shell that works with any Shotgun and pairs well with the CHAC "Boomstick" Shotgun that can also be purchased from the Workshop .

items.name: 12-Gauge Casing
items.description: The 12-Gauge Casing is a vital component used in the crafting of 12-Gauge Buckshot Shells and 12-Gauge Slugs .

items.name: 12-Gauge Cold Steel Shell
items.description: 12-Gauge Cold Steel Shell is a Cold Steel variant of ammunition for Shotguns . It inflicts extra Frost damage and a chance to slow the target and weaken their attacks.

items.name: 12-Gauge Explosive Shell
items.description: 12-Gauge Explosive Shells are used by Shotguns . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered. Damages area around target. Caution when using this ammunition is advised. 12-Gauge Explosive Shells have 6 pellets per shell.

items.name: 12-Gauge Miasmic Shell
items.description: 12-Gauge Miasmic Shell, a Miasmic variant of ammunition used by Shotguns .

items.name: 12-Gauge Obsidian Shell
items.description: 12-Gauge Obsidian Shells are a variant of 12-Gauge Buckshot Shells that deal fire damage on hit and have a chance to apply a unique debuff to targets while also setting them ablaze. Although it may have a low percent chance of setting targets on fire, 12-Gauge Obsidian Shells can decimate Fauna that have a weakness to fire, especially when the 'Burning' modifier occurs. .

items.name: 12-Gauge Slug
items.description: 12-Gauge Slugs are used by the Shotguns . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered.

items.name: 12.7mm CHAC Ammo Box
items.description: The 12.7mm CHAC Ammo Box provides 25 12.7mm CHAC Rounds of Sniper Ammunition that works with the Anti-materiel Rifle .

items.name: 12.7mm CHAC Explosive Ammo Box
items.description: The 12.7mm CHAC Explosive Ammo Box provides 25 12.7mm CHAC Explosive Rounds of Sniper Ammunition that works with the Anti-materiel Rifle .

items.name: 12.7mm CHAC Explosive Round
items.description: 12.7mm CHAC Explosive Round is a type of explosive Sniper Ammunition for the Anti-materiel Rifle that does 500 projectile damage and 400 explosive damage.

items.name: 12.7mm CHAC Incendiary Ammo Box
items.description: The 12.7mm CHAC Incendiary Ammo Box provides 25 12.7mm CHAC Incendiary Rounds of Sniper Ammunition that works with the Anti-materiel Rifle .

items.name: 12.7mm CHAC Incendiary Round
items.description: 12.7mm CHAC Incendiary Round is a type of explosive Sniper Ammunition for the Anti-materiel Rifle that does 500 projectile damage and +25% fire damage.

items.name: 12.7mm CHAC Round
items.description: 12.7mm CHAC Round is a type of Sniper Ammunition for the Anti-materiel Rifle that does 600 damage.

items.name: 5.56mm Armor Piercing Round
items.description: 5.56mm Armor Piercing Round is used by the Assault Rifle .

items.name: 5.56mm Cold Steel Round
items.description: 5.56mm Cold Steel Round is a Cold Steel variant of ammunition for the Assault Rifle . It inflicts extra Frost damage and a chance to slow the target and weaken their attacks.

items.name: 5.56mm Explosive Round
items.description: The 5.56mm Explosive Round is used by the Assault Rifle . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered. Damages area around target. Caution when using this ammunition is advised.

items.name: 5.56mm Incendiary Round
items.description: The 5.56mm Incendiary Rounds are used in the fully-automatic Tier 4  Assault Rifle . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered.

items.name: 5.56mm Miasmic Round
items.description: 5.56mm Miasmic Round, a Miasmic variant of ammunition used by the Assault Rifle .

items.name: 5.56mm Obsidian Round
items.description: 5.56mm Obsidian Rounds are an alternative to 5.56mm Incendiary Rounds that deal fire damage on hit and has a chance to apply a unique debuff to targets while also setting them ablaze. Although it may have a low percent chance of setting targets on fire, 5.56mm Obsidian Rounds excel when used against Fauna that have a weakness to fire, dealing more damage than 5.56mm Rounds . .

items.name: 5.56mm Round
items.description: The 5.56mm Rounds are used in the fully-automatic Tier 4  Assault Rifle . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered.

items.name: 7.62mm Armor Piercing Round
items.description: 7.62mm Armor Piercing Rounds are used by the Bolt Action Rifle and the Hunting Rifle . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered. Unlike standard ammunition, the 7.62mm Armor Piercing Round can pierce hardened points and will deal 250 damage, similar to hitting a non-hardened point.

items.name: 7.62mm CHAC Ammo Box
items.description: The 7.62mm CHAC Ammo Box provides 25 7.62mm CHAC Rounds of Rifle Ammunition that works with Rifles .

items.name: 7.62mm CHAC Round
items.description: 7.62mm CHAC Round is a purchaseable type of Rifle Ammunition for use in any Rifle .

items.name: 7.62mm Cold Steel Round
items.description: 7.62mm Cold Steel Round is a Cold Steel variant of ammunition for Rifles . It inflicts extra Frost damage and a chance to slow the target and weaken their attacks.

items.name: 7.62mm Explosive Round
items.description: 7.62mm Explosive Rounds are used by the Bolt Action Rifle and the Hunting Rifle . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered. Damages area around target. Caution when using this ammunition is advised.

items.name: 7.62mm Incendiary Round
items.description: 7.62mm Incendiary Rounds are used by the Bolt Action Rifle / Hunting Rifle . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered. Hitting a target will set it ablaze, dealing damage for approximately 20 seconds. Deals 8-11 damage a second to normal targets, and 16-22 damage a second to targets that are weak to fire..

items.name: 7.62mm Miasmic Round
items.description: 7.62mm Miasmic Round, a Miasmic variant of ammunition used by Rifles .

items.name: 7.62mm Obsidian Round
items.description: 7.62mm Obsidian Rounds are an alternative to 7.62mm Incendiary Rounds that deals fire damage on hit and has a chance to apply a unique debuff to targets while also setting them ablaze. Although it may have a low percent chance of setting targets on fire, 7.62mm Obsidian Rounds excel when used against Fauna that have a weakness to fire, dealing more damage than 7.62mm Rounds . .

items.name: 9mm Armor Piercing Round
items.description: 9mm Armor Piercing Rounds are used by the Pistol . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered. Unlike standard ammunition, the 9mm Armor Piercing Round can pierce hardened points and will deal 100 damage, similar to hitting a non-hardened point.

items.name: 9mm CHAC Ammo
items.description: 9mm CHAC Ammo is an advanced pistol ammunition that does 200 damage.

items.name: 9mm CHAC Ammo Box
items.description: The 9mm CHAC Ammo Box provides 25 rounds of 9mm CHAC Ammo that works with any Pistol and pairs well with the CHAC "Sentinel" Pistol that can also be purchased from the Workshop .

items.name: 9mm Cold Steel Round
items.description: 9mm Cold Steel Round is a Cold Steel variant of ammunition for Pistols . It inflicts extra Frost damage and a chance to slow the target and weaken their attacks.

items.name: 9mm Explosive Round
items.description: 9mm Explosive Rounds are used by the Pistol . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered. Damages area around target. Caution when using this ammunition is advised.

items.name: 9mm Incendiary Round
items.description: 9mm Incendiary Rounds are used by the Pistol . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered. Hitting a target will set it ablaze, dealing damage for approximately 20 seconds. Deals 8-11 damage a second to normal targets, and 16-22 damage a second to targets that are weak to fire. .

items.name: 9mm Miasmic Round
items.description: 9mm Miasmic Round, a Miasmic variant of ammunition used by Pistols .

items.name: 9mm Obsidian Round
items.description: 9mm Obsidian Rounds are an alternative to 9mm Incendiary Rounds that deals fire damage on hit and has a chance to apply a unique debuff to targets while also setting them ablaze. Although it may have a low percent chance of setting targets on fire, 9mm Obsidian Rounds excel when used against Fauna that have a weakness to fire, dealing more damage than 9mm Rounds . .

items.name: 9mm Round
items.description: The basic ammunition used by the Pistols . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered. With the talent Pistol Proficiency , Prospectors can craft this ammo at a -25% reduced resource cost. Also, with the talent Freebies , Prospectors have a 5% chance to craft double ammo. The ability to craft double ammo works in tandem, on a successful proc chance, with the reduced resource cost recipe netting a total of six extra rounds of ammunition.

items.name: Acidic Glands
items.description: Acidic Glands can be taken to an Organic Residue Cleanser to be turned into 5x Animal Fat . Hazardous when carried in small amounts, deadly when carried in large quantities/with several other Miasmic items. Despite the risk, Acidic Glands is an excellent source of Animal Fat .

items.name: AdLift Module
items.description: This module increases the user's weight capacity by 15% when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Ad Lift Modules may be equipped if the prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit and will further increase the amount the user can carry.

items.name: Advanced Alteration Bench
items.description: The Advanced Alteration Bench is a late game technology that allows prospectors to create Attachment Packs ( Tier 3  ) and Advanced Attachment Packs ( Tier 4  ) to upgrade armor pieces, ranged weapons, and tools. An active power connection providing at least 1,500 electricity to craft Attachment Packs is required. A power connection is not required to add and remove Attachment packs from items.

items.name: Advanced Aquarium
items.description: The Advanced Aquarium allows Prospectors to store and display their favorite catches. Fish stored in the Advanced Aquarium will not spoil so long as it is connected to a power network providing at least 1,000 units of Power and a water network providing at least 500 units of Water . The Advanced Aquarium will not function if these requirements are not met. The Advanced Aquarium can store 4 fish.

items.name: Advanced Battery Rack
items.description: The Advanced Battery Rack is a power-storing device that must be placed indoors. It can store up to 6,000k Ws of power and can charge/output power at a max rate of 10,000 Watts per second.

items.name: Advanced Creature Deterrent
items.description: While useful for protecting Prospectors from predators, the Advanced Creature Deterrent also prevents the spawning of Fauna so be aware that deer, pronghorns, rabbits, chamois, or other animals will not spawn within the indicated radius.

items.name: Advanced Deep Mining Ore Scanner
items.description: Locates Deep Ore Deposits within the area that can be mined with a Biofuel Deep-Mining Drill or an Electric Deep-Mining Drill . Unlike the Deep Mining Ore Scanner , the Advanced Deep Mining Ore Scanner can be toggled to detect specific deep ore deposits.

items.name: Advanced Fishing Trap
items.description: One approach to catching fish is by using a Fishing Trap. Though a Lure is not required, attaching one can increase the quality, length, and weight of the caught fish. Additionally, certain lures can increase the odds of catching a rarer type of fish. To attach a lure to the Advanced Fishing Trap, inspect the trap by pressing 'F' and drag the lure into the dedicated lure slot.

items.name: Advanced Iron Lure
items.description: The Advanced Iron Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. The capture zone size increase widens the size of the capture area during the fishing minigame, increasing the success chance of catching a fish. Like all Lures , the Advanced Iron Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Advanced Masonry Bench
items.description: The Advanced Masonry Bench enables the construction of Scoria Brick Building Pieces and Clay Brick Building Pieces and is able to craft items made the Masonry Bench at a faster rate, but only once the prospector researches the blueprint sets for those building pieces.

items.name: Advanced Pistol
items.description: The Advanced Pistol is the most advanced Tier 4  handgun with the largest ammo capacity, durability and rate of fire. It fires Pistol Ammunition such as Armor Piercing , Explosive , Incendiary , Obsidian or regular 9mm Rounds .

items.name: Advanced Storm Visor Attachment
items.description: The Advanced Storm Visor Attachment is an end-game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Advanced Armor Attachment Packs in the Tier 4  Tech Tree.

items.name: Advanced Supplemental Filtration Attachment
items.description: The Advanced Supplemental Filtration Attachment is an armor alteration that provides resistance to poison and reduced water consumption.

items.name: Advanced Supplemental Respiration Attachment
items.description: The Advanced Supplemental Respiration Attachment is an end-game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Advanced Armor Attachment Packs in the Tier 4  Tech Tree.

items.name: Advanced Textiles Bench
items.description: Allows for the crafting of more advanced Armor sets, Cured Leather and Platinum Weave . The Advanced Textiles Bench is also able to craft items made at the Textiles Bench , removing the need for multiple benches.

items.name: Advanced Tool Attachment Pack
items.description: The Advanced Tool Attachment Pack is a Tier 4  item that allows Prospectors to alter their tools with additional bonuses. Similar to Tool Attachment Pack , both can be applied at an Alteration Bench or Advanced Alteration Bench .

items.name: Aerodynamic Attachment
items.description: Aerodynamic Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Armor Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Aeroponic Crop Plot
items.description: The Aeroponic Crop Plot is a farming plot for growing Seeds that can later be harvested for Plant Resources once fully grown. Unless the Prospector has the Fresh Is Best talent when deploying a seed into the crop plot, the grown Plant Resource will eventually wither if not harvested.

items.name: Alpha Wolf Trophy
items.description: Alpha Wolf Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Alpha Wolf Vestige
items.description: Alpha Wolf Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create an Alpha Wolf Trophy , which can help help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Alteration Bench
items.description: The Alteration Bench is a mid-to-late game technology that allows Prospectors to create Attachment Packs to upgrade armor pieces, ranged weapons, and tools.

items.name: Aluminium Arrow
items.description: The Aluminium Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.description: Resistant to weather, but lighter than Stone Buildings, Aluminium Buildings are an asset when traveling to new areas far from your dropship or base, bringing with you the equivalent of a Stone Base in your backpack. Can be repaired with a Repair Hammer .

items.name: Ammo Casing
items.description: The Ammo Casing is a vital component used in the crafting of 9mm Rounds and 7.62mm Rounds .

items.name: Animal Bait
items.description: Animal Bait is used to lure random predators when left in an open area. The blueprint is unlocked account-wide after completing the prospect Wet Work: Extermination . Stacks up to 5.

items.name: Animal Bed
items.description: The Animal Bed serves as a place for juvenile animals to sleep while taming and is required to tame juvenile animals. Tamed Mounts and Pets can also use the Animal Bed when tired.

items.name: Animal Fat
items.description: Animal fat is produced from the rendering down of raw meat and is used in Cooking to make late-game Foods such as Pastry , Fried Chunky Vegetables and, Freshwater Fillet Curry . It is used to create and power the Lantern .

items.name: Animal Healthbar Module
items.description: This module allows the wearer to see creature alert level and health when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot. The Animal Healthbar Module is researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect.

items.name: Animal Highlighting Module
items.description: Animal Highlighting Module is researched and created on the Space Station in the Workshop . Equip in an Envirosuit Module Slot after dropping down for a prospect.

items.name: Antelope Trophy
items.description: Antelope Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Antelope Vestige
items.description: Antelope Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create an Antelope Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Anti-Parasitic Paste
items.description: Anti-Parasitic Paste is one of the multiple, easily overlooked recipes available in the Tier 1  tech tree. Reduces the duration of the Parasites debuff upon consumption.

items.name: Anti-Parasitic Pill
items.description: Anti-Parasitic Pills are used to cure, and prevent for a short time, further ailments such as Festering Wounds and Dysentery .

items.name: Anti-Parasitic Tonic
items.description: Used alone to cure parasitic infections such as Festering Wound and Dysentery or as a mid-stage ingredient to the prophylactic Anti-Parasitic Pill

items.name: Anti-Parasitic Vaccine I
items.description: Anti-Parasitic Vaccine I is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unqiue Status Effect , which makes surviving the enviroment without worry possible.

items.name: Anti-Parasitic Vaccine II
items.description: Anti-Parasitic Vaccine II is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unqiue Status Effect , which makes surviving the enviroment without worry possible.

items.name: Anti-Parasitic Vaccine III
items.description: Anti-Parasitic Vaccine III is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unique Status Effect , which makes surviving the environment without worry possible.

items.name: Anti-Poison Paste
items.description: Anti-Poison Paste is one of the multiple, easily overlooked recipes available in the tier 1 tech tree. Reduces the duration of Poison from critters like the Venomous Fish or the Caveworm .

items.name: Anti-Poison Pill
items.description: Anti-Poison Pills are used to cure, and prevent for a short time, further ailments from contact with poisonous substances.

items.name: Anti-Poison Tonic
items.description: Used alone to cure Poison from critters like the Venomous Fish , or as a mid-stage ingredient to the prophylactic Anti-poison Pill .

items.name: Anti-Poison Vaccine I
items.description: Anti-Poison Vaccine I is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unique Status Effect , which makes surviving the environment without worry possible.

items.name: Anti-Poison Vaccine II
items.description: Anti-Poison Vaccine II is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unique Status Effect , which makes surviving the environment without worry possible.

items.name: Anti-Poison Vaccine III
items.description: Anti-Poison Vaccine III is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unique Status Effect , which makes surviving the environment without worry possible.

items.name: Anti-materiel Rifle
items.description: The Anti-materiel Rifle is a bolt-action, anti-materiel rifle with a long effective range and an included scope for viewing the target. It fires Sniper Ammunition purchased from the Workshop .

items.name: Antibiotic Paste
items.description: Antibiotic Paste reduces the duration of bacterial infections like food poisoning and the Cave Sickness debuff from caves by 50% upon consumption.

items.name: Antibiotic Pill
items.description: Antibiotic Pills are used to cure, and prevent for a short time, further ailments such as Cave Sickness , Infected Wounds , and Food Poisoning .

items.name: Antibiotic Tonic
items.description: Used alone to cure infections such as Cave Sickness , Infected Wound , and Food poisoning , or as a mid-stage ingredient to the prophylactic Antibiotic Pill .

items.name: Anvil Bench
items.description: The Anvil Bench is unlocked near the start of the Tier 2  Tech Tree . It enables the Prospector to craft higher quality tools such as the Iron Pickaxe and Steel Pickaxe . It is also where these tools can be repaired. While it can be placed with no shelter, it would be unusable. Will take damage if left without shelter (or under a severely damaged roof) in storms.

items.name: Aquarium
items.description: The Aquarium allows Prospectors to store and display their favorite catches. Fish stored in the Aquarium will not spoil so long as there is biofuel available and the Aquarium is connected to a water network providing at least 250 units of water. The Aquarium will not function if these requirements are not met. With a full Biofuel Can , the Aquarium will last about three and a half hours. Can only hold 1 fish.

items.name: Archer's Backpack
items.description: The Archer's Backpack is a must need for the avid archer, quickly dispatch a flurry of arrows at your target with this innovative quiver system.

items.name: Arctic Animal Feed
items.description: Arctic Animal Feed is an Animal Feed for Pets or Mounts with a unique Status Effect . Can be fed to mounts to satisfy Hunger . Arctic Animal Feed decays in 10,800 seconds, but that decay can be slowed down by storing Arctic Animal Feed inside an Ice Box or Refrigerator .

items.name: Arctic Arm Armor
items.description: Arctic Armor is a major upgrade to Fur Armor , offering unrivaled cold resistance.

items.name: Arctic Explorer Saddle
items.description: The Arctic Explorer Saddle is a saddle for Mounts that has an artic theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC and is a cosmetic change to the Basic Riding Saddle that provides no additional attributes.

items.name: Arctic Feet Armor
items.description: Arctic Armor is a major upgrade to Fur Armor , offering unrivaled cold resistance.

Prospectors can set their respawn location to a bed, however if this bed is deconstructed or destroyed, the prospector's spawn location will reset back to the drop-pod. The Art Deco Bed has the best sleep quality of any bed.

items.description: Ashen Drake Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create an Ashen Drake Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Assault Rifle
items.description: The Assault Rifle is an automatic firearm with reduced critical damage, +15 round ammo capacity and a high rate of fire. It uses Assault Rifle Ammunition such as Armor Piercing , Explosive , Incendiary , Obsidian or regular 5.56mm Rounds .

items.name: Attack Speed Attachment
items.description: Attack Speed Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Tool Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Automated Defense System: Pistol
items.description: Automated Defense System: Pistol is a deployable base defense turret that fires Pistol Ammunition at hostile Fauna .

items.name: Avocado
items.description: Avocado is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Avocado Farming Packet
items.description: The Avocado Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station or the Orbital Exchange Interface and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Avocado seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: BEAST
items.description: While holding the BEAST, Prospectors can left-click while looking at an animal to "scan" that animal (must be close to the target to initiate a scan). Unlike what the description says, the scanned animal will take additional damage until another scan is performed. Scanning animals using the BEAST also grants 3 bestiary points for the animal scanned.

items.name: Bacon Butty
items.description: Bacon Butty is a consumable food that boosts health, stamina, health regeneration, experience gained and critical damage.

items.name: Bacterial Vaccine I
items.description: Bacterial Vaccine I is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unique Status Effect , which makes surviving the environment without worry possible.

items.name: Bacterial Vaccine II
items.description: Bacterial Vaccine II is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unique Status Effect , which makes surviving the environment without worry possible.

items.name: Bacterial Vaccine III
items.description: Bacterial Vaccine III is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unique Status Effect , which makes surviving the environment without worry possible.

items.name: Banana
items.description: A Banana is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. It can be eaten to boost maximum stamina for 60 seconds and to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Banana Farming Packet
items.description: The Banana Farming Packet is a packet of seeds for planting and growing Bananas . It is unlocked in the Workshop after completing the mission Ape Escape in the Great Hunts Campaigns .

items.name: Barbecue Carrot
items.description: Barbecue Carrot is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Bark Lure
items.description: The Bark Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. The capture zone increase is the size of the capture area during the fishing minigame, increasing the success chance of catching a fish. Like all Lures , the Bark Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Basic Bandage
items.description: Basic Bandage is used to heal Wound and Exotic Wound Status Effects .

items.name: Basic Battery Rack
items.description: The Basic Battery Rack is a power-storing device that must be placed indoors. It can store up to 1,000k Ws of power and can charge/output power at a max rate of 1,500 Watts per second.

items.name: Basic Ceiling Light
items.description: The Basic Ceiling Light provides lighting for a Prospector's base. Requires 150 units of power to function.

items.name: Basic Dried Meat
items.description: Basic Dried Meat is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Basic Fertilizer
items.description: Basic Fertilizer is used on crop plots to enhance the growth of plants. When applied, Crop Yield and Crop Growth Speed is increased by 15% for 1200 seconds. To fertilize a crop plot, equip a fertilizer of your choosing from your hotbar and left click the plot you wish to fertilize.

items.name: Basic Fishing Bench
items.description: The Basic Fishing Bench is where Prospectors can craft the Wooden Fishing Rod and the Refined Wood Fishing Rod , as well as various Lures on the left hand side of the bench. The right side of the bench is used to fillet any fish caught using a Fishing Rod or Fishing Trap. Does not require shelter to be used.

items.name: Basic Fishing Rod
items.description: One approach to catching fish is by using a Fishing Rod. Though a lure is not required, attaching one can increase the quality, length, and weight of the caught fish. Additionally, certain lures can increase the odds of catching fish of a certain rarity or increase the size of the capture area. For a list of available lures, view this page .

items.name: Basic Fishing Trap
items.description: One approach to catching fish is by using a Fishing Trap. Though a Lure is not required, attaching one can increase the quality, length, and weight of the caught fish. Additionally, certain lures can increase the odds of catching a rarer type of fish. To attach a lure to the Basic Fishing Trap, inspect the trap by pressing 'F' and drag the lure into the dedicated lure slot.

items.name: Basic Rainwater Purifier
items.description: Basic Rainwater Purifiers can be crafted using Character Crafting with the following resources:

items.name: Basic Riding Saddle
items.description: The Basic Riding Saddle is an item that allows prospectors to ride tamed Mounts . The Basic Riding Saddle can be use on all Mounts (regardless of who tamed them) and comes with two inventory slots and one heavy cargo inventory slot for Equipment . Items stored in the saddle is dropped into a lootable overflow bag when the mount dies.

items.name: Basic Scope Attachment
items.description: Basic Scope Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech. Does not add actual scope to weapon.

items.name: Basic Wall Light
items.description: The Basic Wall Light provides lighting for a Prospector's base. Requires 150 units of power to function.

items.name: Basic Water Purifier
items.description: Basic Water Purifiers can be crafted using Character Crafting with the following resources:

items.name: Battery Cavelight
items.description: The Battery Cavelight is a portable Light Source that can be deployed on a floor or wall to provide illumination in the surrounding area. It is good for marking a path through caves.

items.name: Battery Powered Lantern
items.description: The Battery Powered Lantern is a portable Handheld Light Source that provides illumination in the surrounding area. Can be equipped in the "L" light slot on the hotbar.

items.name: Battery Spotlight
items.description: The Battery Spotlight is a portable Light Source that can be deployed on a floor or wall to provide illumination in a concentrated area. It is useful as a temporary light source while mining in caves.

items.name: Bean Farming Packet
items.description: The Bean Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Bean seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Bear Rug
items.description: Bear Rugs are decorative deployables that can be placed on any ground surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from being for decorative purposes, it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Bearhide Saddle
items.description: The Bearhide Saddle is a saddle for Mounts that has a bear theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC and is a cosmetic change to the Basic Riding Saddle that provides no additional attributes.

items.name: Bedroll
items.description: The Bedroll allows prospectors to sleep provided it is sufficiently sheltered, a campfire/heater/dehumidifier/etc is nearby, and it is night time in-game. In a multiplayer game, all prospectors must sleep at the same time to pass the night. Sleeping will provide the Well Rested Status Effect . Prospectors can set their respawn location to a bedroll, however if this bedroll is picked up or destroyed, the prospector's spawn location will reset back to their drop pod.

items.name: Beehive
items.description: The Beehive is the foundation for Beekeeping all other units attach to the hive. The base model uses Worker Bees or Queen Bees as fuel to produce Honeycomb . Honeycomb is produced at 1 unit per min.

items.name: Beehive Breeding Center
items.description: A Beekeeping element that attaches to a Beehive and provides the facilities for a Queen Bee to produce Worker Bees

items.name: Beehive Extractor
items.description: A Beekeeping element that attaches to a small Beehive to automatically extract Honey and Beeswax from Honeycomb . Requires power and is attached through the small Beehive GUI.

items.name: Beer
items.description: Beer is a mid-game beverage made from Yeast and Wheat that greatly increases stamina and stamina regeneration.

items.name: Berry & Seed Bar
items.description: Full of energy for long hikes, long lasting effects and easily crafted.

items.name: Berry Farming Packet
items.description: The Berry Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Berry seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Berry Jam
items.description: Berry Jam is a long-lasting Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Berry Jam, Strawberry Jam and Pickled Carrot , does not spoil and is therefore a valuable food for long-term storage.

items.name: Berry Smoked Saltwater Fillet
items.description: Berry Smoked Saltwater Fillet is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Big Breakfast
items.description: Big Breakfast is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Binoculars
items.description: See your prey from further away.

items.name: Biofuel
items.description: Biofuel is a mid-game, Tier 3  fuel that can be crafted or purchased and used to fuel a variety of Deployable equipment and sometimes quest items seen in Missions .

items.name: Biofuel Bio-Cleaner
items.description: The Biofuel Bio-Cleaner is a deployable Tier 3  cleaning device that can process organic materials collected from world bosses into Legendary Biomass and clean infected materials found on Prometheus , similar to the Tier 4  Organic Residue Cleanser .

items.name: Biofuel Can
items.description: Biofuel Can is used to store Biofuel . It is filled at either the Biofuel Composter or Electric Composter .

items.name: Biofuel Chimney Cap
items.description: A Biofuel Chimney Cap is the final cap piece to place on a Biofuel Chimney Extension or directly on a Biofuel Fireplace . Two variants, a half height and full height, are available by holding the 'R' key when deploying.

items.name: Biofuel Chimney Extension
items.description: A Biofuel Chimney Extension is a wide round section of metal chimney or stove pipe to place on a Biofuel Fireplace or another existing Biofuel Chimney Extension to extend the chimney vertically. It is usually capped with a Biofuel Chimney Cap .

items.name: Biofuel Composter
items.description: The Biofuel Composter enables the Prospector to produce Biofuel . Can be connected to a water network providing at least 100 units of water to increase processing speed, but is not required to produce Biofuel.

items.name: Biofuel Deep-Mining Drill
items.description: The Biofuel Deep-Mining Drill will mine deep mining ore deposits when supplied with biofuel from a Biofuel Can / MXC Fuel Canister . The Biofuel Deep-Mining Drill has 5 slots and will last 2 hours and 5 minutes on a full Biofuel Can .

items.name: Biofuel Extractor
items.description: This device is used to extract Exotics from Exotic Deposits. Does not require electricity, but uses biofuel instead. The Biofuel Extractor runs 33% slower than the Electric Extractor , but can be crafted earlier in the Tech Tree .

items.name: Biofuel Fireplace
items.description: The Biofuel Fireplace is deployable Tier 3  version of the Fireplace that burns Biofuel to provide a source of heat, a source of light , Coziness and a means to cook Food indoors.

items.name: Biofuel Generator
items.description: The Biofuel Generator generates Electricity when supplied with biofuel from a Biofuel Can . Use an Electricity Tool to connect it to Benches to provide power.

items.name: Biofuel Lamp
items.description: Provides exceptional lightning compared to the Torch or Lantern . Can be equipped in the "L" light slot on the hotbar.

items.name: Biofuel Oxite Dissolver
items.description: More efficient than the Oxite Dissolver , this is used in tandem with Oxygen Containers placed into the oxidizer. The front slots of the deployable only accept Oxygen Containers and will automatically fill said containers from Oxite placed into the machine when supplied with Biofuel from a Biofuel Can . A full Biofuel Can will last three minutes and twenty seconds, producing 0.2 Liters of Oxygen every two seconds.

items.name: Biofuel Radar
items.description: The Biofuel Radar is used to scan for Exotic / Volatile Raw Exotic deposits. Once activated, aggravated Fauna (varies per region) will attempt to destroy the radar by any means necessary. Radars of all types will show ALL exotic veins on the map in each scan, regardless of whether they have been depleted. Scans performed in an Outpost will not complete as there are no exotic veins in them. This can be used to spawn aggressive wildlife for resources or experience.

items.name: Biofuel Stove
items.description: The Biofuel Stove is a mid- to late-game technology that expands the recipes available compared to the Potbelly Stove . It requires Biofuel to run and must be snapped to a side of the Kitchen Bench .

items.name: Biofuel Water Pump
items.description: The Biofuel Water Pump outputs 1,000 Water when supplied with biofuel; use the Water Pipe Tool to connect it to Crafting Benches / Water Storage to provide water. The Biofuel Water Pump can output water for two hours and thirty minutes with a full Biofuel Can .

items.name: Biomore Backpack
items.description: The Biomore Backpack provides six inventory slots, along with 3 active auras where the prospector and nearby allies having increased physical resistance, quicker healing from bacterial, parasitic and poison modifiers, and additional health regeneration. It also has offers buffs for the wearer, reducing the stamina impact from using tools, and providing more health to downed prospectors when revived. An excellent choice for prospectors specializing in rescues.

items.name: Biotech Maul
items.description: The Biotech Maul is a heavy melee-focused Legendary Weapon that can be purchased at the Bio-lab .

items.name: Black Jaguar Trophy
items.description: Black Jaguar Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Black Jaguar Vestige
items.description: Black Jaguar Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Black Jaguar Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Black Tusker Animal Bed
items.description: The Black Tusker Animal Bed is a bed for Mounts and Pets that has a tusker theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC . Provides no additional attributes and is a cosmetic change to the Animal Bed .

items.name: Black Wolf Arrow
items.description: The Black Wolf Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 10.

items.name: Black Wolf Knife
items.description: The Black Wolf Knife is a knife with a 25% chance to inflict hemorrhage on targets and can be used as a tool to skin fauna. For the thrown variant of the Black Wolf Knife, view Black Wolf Throwing Knife .

items.name: Black Wolf Lure
items.description: The Black Wolf Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. The capture zone size increase widens the size of the capture area during the fishing minigame, increasing the success chance of catching a fish. Like all Lures , the Black Wolf Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Black Wolf Throwing Knife
items.description: The Black Wolf Throwing Knife is a variant of the Black Wolf Knife that can be thrown. Unlike the Black Wolf Knife , the Black Wolf Throwing Knife cannot be used to skin fauna. Crafted in batches of five and stacks up to fifty.

items.name: Black Wolf Tooth
items.description: Black Wolf Teeth are a resource obtained by skinning an Alpha Wolf . Only after completing Lupine: Extermination can these be used to craft new weaponry at the Anvil Bench .

items.name: Blood Thinning Paste
items.description: Blood Thinning Paste is one of the multiple, easily overlooked recipes available in the Tier 1  tech tree. Reduces the duration of Concussions and Contusions when you're unlucky enough to kiss a falling tree.

items.name: Blood Thinning Pill
items.description: Blood Thinning Pills are used to cure, and prevent for a short time, further Contusions and Concussions .

items.name: Blood Thinning Tonic
items.description: Used alone to treat trauma such as Concussion and Contusion , when you're unlucky enough to kiss a falling tree, or as a mid-stage ingredient to craft the Blood Thinning Pill .

items.name: Blood Thinning Vaccine I
items.description: Blood Thinning Vaccine I is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unique Status Effect , which makes surviving the environment without worry possible.

items.name: Blood Thinning Vaccine II
items.description: Blood Thinning Vaccine II is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unique Status Effect , which makes surviving the environment without worry possible.

items.description: Blood Thinning Vaccine III is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unique Status Effect , which makes surviving the environment without worry possible.

items.name: Blueback Vestige

items.name: Bolt Action Rifle
items.description: The Bolt Action Rifle is the first long-range Firearm that prospectors can create. It can utilize the 7.62mm Round , the Incendiary Rifle Round , etc. Along with the Shotgun , it provides Prospectors with a significant increase in survivability when encountering the Fauna of Icarus. The Bolt Action Rifle can fire 75 rounds before breaking, and the talent Gunsmith can increase this to up to a maximum of 90 rounds, so bring a Machining Bench for long trips.

items.name: Bone
items.description: Bone is a Animal Resource obtained from Fauna . It is also sometimes found when harvesting fish.

items.name: Bone Arm Armor
items.description: Bone Armor provides relatively good protection from Icarus' fauna as a Tier 1  armor with a minor boost to temperature resistance. Also provides a considerable damage increase when a full set is worn.

items.name: Bone Arrow
items.description: The Bone Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass.

items.name: Bone Chest Armor
items.description: Bone Armor provides relatively good protection from Icarus' fauna as a Tier 1  armor with a minor boost to temperature resistance. Also provides a considerable damage increase when a full set is worn.

items.name: Bone Feet Armor
items.description: Bone Armor provides relatively good protection from Icarus' fauna as a Tier 1  armor with a minor boost to temperature resistance. Also provides a considerable damage increase when a full set is worn.

items.name: Bone Head Armor
items.description: Bone Armor provides relatively good protection from Icarus' fauna as a Tier 1  armor with a minor boost to temperature resistance. Also provides a considerable damage increase when a full set is worn.

items.name: Bone Javelin
items.description: The Bone Javelin is a variant of the Bone Spear that can only be thrown and is an upgrade to the Wood Javelin . Despite it requiring more materials to craft, the increase in damage can mean the difference between winning and losing a fight against Icarus' fauna.

items.name: Bone Knife
items.description: The Bone Knife is an upgrade in damage and durability from the Stone Knife , the Bone Knife can be used as either a melee weapon or tool.

items.name: Bone Leg Armor
items.description: Bone Armor provides relatively good protection from Icarus' fauna as a Tier 1  armor with a minor boost to temperature resistance. Also provides a considerable damage increase when a full set is worn.

items.name: Bone Lure
items.description: The Bone Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. The capture zone increase is the size of the capture area during the fishing minigame, increasing the success chance of catching a fish. Like all Lures , the Bone Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Bone Shield
items.description: The Bone Shield is crafted at the Character Crafting menu with the following resources:

items.name: Bone Sickle
items.description: Used by 'attacking' plants such as shrubs, Reed Flower , Wheat , etc. Sickles significantly increase the yield of plants when harvesting.

items.name: Bone Spear
items.description: Spears increase the range to which Prospectors can attack fauna, providing a unique advantage when up high. The Bone Spear has twice as much health than the Wood Spear , which can be the difference between winning and losing against Icarus' fauna. Unlike the Bone Javelin , the Bone Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Bone Throwing Knife
items.description: The Bone Throwing Knife is a variant of the Bone Knife that can be thrown. Unlike the Bone Knife , the Bone Throwing Knife cannot be used to skin fauna. Crafted in batches of five and stacks up to fifty.

items.name: Bovine Pack Harness
items.description: The Bovine Pack Harness is a cargo saddle for Buffalo and Tusker that has 22 inventory slots and +300 Kg weight capacity.

items.name: Bramble Bush
items.description: Bramble Bush is produced by harvesting the cultivated variety of Bramble . Bramble can be grown with Seeds either harvested from wild, extracted with the Seed Extractor or using a Bramble Farming Packet from the Workshop .
harvested_from: extracted with the Seed Extractor or using a Bramble Farming Packet from the Workshop

items.name: Bramble Farming Packet
items.description: The Bramble Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Bramble seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Brazier
items.description: Brazier Misc Repaired with Hammers

items.name: Bread
items.description: Bread is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Bread Dough
items.description: Bread Dough is the precursor to the mid/late-game Food Bread . Bread Dough will eventually decay, but can be preserved in an Ice Box , Refrigerator , or Deep Freeze .

items.name: Broiled Kumara
items.description: Broiled Kumara is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Broken Pottery
items.description: The Broken Pottery is an item unlocked by completing the Fracture mission. There are four varieties of pottery selectable by 'R'.

items.description: The Bronze Alpha Sandworm Statue is a decorative bronze item.

Though it may not increase attack damage, it pairs well with the Calibrated Grip Attachment s and Attack Speed Attachment s, further increasing knife attack speed.

items.name: Brutalist 10-Seater Table
items.description: The Brutalist 10-Seater Table seats ten and is mode from concrete, copper nails and glass.

items.name: Brutalist 2-Seater Couch
items.description: The Brutalist 2-Seater Couch is a couch made with concrete and leather in the Brutalist design aesthetic. It serves as a seat for Prospectors and provides a small bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Brutalist 3-Seater Couch
items.description: The Brutalist 3-Seater Couch is a couch made with concrete and leather in the Brutalist design aesthetic. It serves as a seat for Prospectors and provides a small bonus to Coziness . The Brutalist 3-Seater Couch is part of the Industrial Furniture Pack DLC.

items.name: Brutalist 6-Seater Table
items.description: The Brutalist 6-Seater Table seats six, is mode from concrete, copper nails and glass.

items.name: Brutalist Bed
items.description: The Brutalist Bed is mode from concrete and platinum weave, and has an increased sleep quality.

items.name: Brutalist Bookshelf
items.description: The Brutalist Bookshelf is mode from concrete and iron.

items.name: Brutalist Candlestick
items.description: The Brutalist Candlestick is mode from concrete and either animal fat or beeswax. There are two varieties by selecting R. Fuel is either beeswax or animal fat.

items.name: Brutalist Coffee Table
items.description: The Brutalist Coffee Table is mode from concrete, iron and glass.

items.name: Brutalist Dining Chair
items.description: The Brutalist Dining Chair seats one and is mode from concrete and leather.

items.name: Brutalist Display Cabinet
items.description: The Brutalist Display Cabinet is made from concrete and iron, and serves as decorative shelving and a display cabinet. It has 25 inventory slots for Storage and provides a small bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Brutalist Dresser
items.description: The Brutalist Dresser is a concrete bedroom furniture piece made in the Brutalist design aesthetic. It has 10 inventory slots for Storage and provides a small bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Brutalist Lamp
items.description: The Brutalist Lamp is a table lamp with a concrete base and round shade in the Brutalist design aesthetic. It requires 150 units of Electricity to operate and provides a Light Source and bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Brutalist Lounge Chair
items.description: The Brutalist Lounge Chair is a minimalist chair made with concrete and leather in the Brutalist design aesthetic. It serves as a seat for Prospectors and provides a small bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Brutalist Nightstand
items.description: The Brutalist Nightstand is a concrete bedside furniture piece made in the Brutalist design aesthetic. It has 10 inventory slots for Storage and provides a small bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Brutalist Octagonal Table
items.description: The Brutalist Octagonal Table seats six and is mode from concrete and copper nails.

items.name: Brutalist Sitting Bench
items.description: The Brutalist Sitting Bench is made soley from concrete and seats two prospectors.

items.name: Brutalist Square Lamp
items.description: The Brutalist Square Lamp is a table lamp with a concrete base and a square shade (despite the appearance of the in-game item icon) in the Brutalist design aesthetic. It requires 150 units of Electricity to operate and provides a Light Source and bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Brutalist Stool
items.description: The Brutalist Stool seats one and is made from concrete.

items.name: Brutalist Wall Shelf
items.description: The Brutalist Wall Shelf is a decorative shelf for holding small items such as Lamps or small Trophies . It provides a small bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Brutalist Wardrobe
items.description: The Brutalist Wardrobe is a concrete bedside furniture piece made in the Brutalist design aesthetic. It has 25 inventory slots for Storage and provides a small bonus to Coziness . The deployable has two varieties selectable by the 'R' key.

items.name: Buffalo Rug
items.description: Buffalo Rugs are decorative deployables that can be placed on any ground surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from being for decorative purposes, it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .
items.crafted_at: Advanced Textiles Bench Electric Textiles Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Advanced Textiles Bench Electric Textiles Bench

items.name: Buffalo Trophy
items.description: Buffalo Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Buffalo Vestige
items.description: Buffalo Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Buffalo Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary . They are also used at the Advanced Textiles Bench / Electric Textiles Bench to make Buffalo Rugs . Decorative purposes aside, both provide a boost to coziness, which increases the duration and effect of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Building Upgrade Tool
items.description: This item is no longer craftable. Upgrade functionality has been merged with all repair hammers: prospectors can hold R to select a building material and Right-Click Building Pieces to apply the upgrade if they have the new building pieces in their inventory.

items.name: Bullseye Target
items.description: Bullseye Targets are deployable items used for target practice and to test weapon damage.

items.name: Burlap Animal Bed
items.description: The Burlap Animal Bed is a bed for Mounts and Pets that has a basic theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC . Provides no additional attributes and is a cosmetic change to the Animal Bed .

items.name: Butter
items.description: Butter is a late-game intermediate resource crafted from Cream and used in various recipes.

items.name: C0NT4CT Radio
items.description: The C0NT4CT Radio is a portable device that when in range, provides the same access to missions as a CONT4CT Device in Open World prospects.

items.name: CHAC "Boomstick" Shotgun
items.description: The CHAC "Boomstick" Shotgun is an advanced purchaseable Shotgun with increase projectile and critical damage. It fires any Shotgun Ammunition and is comparable to other Tier 4  Firearms .

items.name: CHAC "Sentinel" Pistol
items.description: The CHAC "Sentinel" Pistol is an advanced handgun with increased projectile and critical damage that is comparable, or better than other Tier 4  Firearms .

items.name: CHAC "Sovereign" Rifle
items.description: The CHAC "Sovereign" Rifle is a purchaseable rifle with a fast reload speed and moderate damage capability.

items.name: CONT4CT Device
items.description: The CONT4CT Device grants Prospectors access to SMPL3 missions and Operations . Though the CONT4CT Device can be crafted in Missions , they can only be used in Open Worlds and Outposts . Must be deployed outdoors.

items.name: Cacoa Farming Packet
items.description: The Cacoa Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Cocoa seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Calf
items.description: A Calf is an imported domesticated Fauna that is brought down to the planet and raised to maturity primarily to produce Milk .

items.name: Calibrated Grip Attachment
items.description: Calibrated Grip Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Armor Attachment Pack tech. It is worth noting that The Wear Rate reduction applies to weapons as well as tools.

items.name: Campfire
items.description: The first available cooking station, the campfire is an essential early structure that allows prospectors to pass the night and to cook Raw Meat or Fish Chunks , yielding safe to consume versions.

items.name: Canteen
items.description: Filled at any water source, including a Rain Reservoir . The Canteen is water tight, and is a mid-game item requiring a Machining Bench . Canteens can hold 5.0 L of water, 5 times as much as a water skin and can keep the Prospector hydrated for approximately 10x as long due to the leakage of the water skin.

items.name: Caramel Berry Tart
items.description: Caramel Berry Tart is late-game Food that when consumed provides a considerable boost to stamina, speed, resistance to cave sickness and a chance to mine additional stone.

items.name: Caramel Pastry
items.description: Caramel Pastry is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Carbon Arrow
items.description: The Carbon Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Carbon Fiber
items.description: While being a Tier 3  component, Carbon Fiber is only used to make Carbon Arrows , the Carbon Spear / Javelin , and the Carbon Fibre Round Shield in the Tier 3  Tech Tree; however, it is a critical component widely used in Tier 4  crafting.

items.name: Carbon Fibre Round Shield
items.description: The Carbon Fibre Round Shield is crafted at the Forge/Foundry with the following resources:

items.name: Carbon Javelin
items.description: The Carbon Javelin is a variant of the Carbon Spear that can only be thrown and is a cheaper upgrade to the Platinum Javelin that deals more damage and has a lower break chance.

items.name: Carbon Paste
items.description: Carbon Paste is a crafted resource meant to be smelted in a Concrete Furnace or Electric Furnace to make Carbon Fiber and is a critical component in Tier 4  crafting.

items.name: Carbon Spear
items.description: The Carbon Spear is an upgrade to the Platinum Spear that deals more damage and is cheaper to craft. Unlike the Carbon Javelin , the Carbon Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Carcass Harvesting Attachment
items.description: Carcass Harvesting Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Tool Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Carpentry Bench
items.description: While it can be placed with no shelter, it would be unusable. Will take damage if left without shelter (or under severely damaged roof) in storms.

items.name: Carrot
items.description: Carrots are a common form of Plantlife found in the Forest and Riverlands locations on Icarus. When consumed by prospectors, they replenish Hunger .

items.name: Carrot Cake
items.description: Carrot Cake is a deployable Food item that when placed on a surface will provide 8 Carrot Cake Pieces that can be picked up and consumed by Prospectors.

items.name: Carrot Cake Piece
items.description: Carrot Cake Piece is a late-game Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Carrot Farming Packet
items.description: The Carrot Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Carrot seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.description: The Carved Wood 2-Seater Couch is a decorative item.

items.name: Carved Wood 3-Seater Couch
items.description: The Carved Wood 3-Seater Couch is a decorative item.

items.name: Carved Wood Armchair
items.description: The Carved Wood Armchair is a decorative item.

items.name: Carved Wood Bed
items.description: The Carved Wood Bed allows prospectors to sleep provided it is sufficiently sheltered and it is night time in-game. In a multiplayer game, all prospectors must sleep at the same time to pass the night. Prospectors can set their respawn location to a bed, however if this bed is deconstructed or destroyed, the prospector's spawn location will reset back to the drop-pod.

items.name: Carved Wood Bookshelf
items.description: The Carved Wood Bookshelf is a decorative item.

items.name: Carved Wood Cabinet
items.description: The Carved Wood Cabinet is a decorative piece with 10 item slots.

items.name: Carved Wood Candlestick
items.description: The Carved Wood Candlestick can be crafted using either beeswax or animal fat and will take either as fuel. There are three varieties that can be selected using the 'R' key while deploying.

items.name: Carved Wood Chair
items.description: The Carved Wood Chair is a decorative chair of two varieties, select R when deploying.

items.name: Carved Wood Coffee Table
items.description: The Carved Wood Coffee Table is a decorative item with two varieties, select R when deploying.

items.name: Carved Wood Desk Lamp
items.description: The Carved Wood Desk Lamp is a decorative item that requires 150 kwh of electricity

items.name: Carved Wood Dresser
items.description: The Carved Wood Dresser is a decorative item with 10 inventory slots.

items.name: Carved Wood Large Table
items.description: The Carved Wood Large Table is a long wood table with room for 10 seats. The item has two build variants that can be selected with the 'R' key when deploying.

items.name: Carved Wood Narrow Wardrobe
items.description: Carved Wood Narrow Wardrobe is a decorative narrow wardrobe with 10 inventory slots. It has two build variants available by selecting 'R' when deploying.

items.name: Carved Wood Nightstand
items.description: The Carved Wood Nightstand is a decorative nightstand with 10 inventory slots. It has five build variants available by using the 'R' key when deploying.

items.name: Carved Wood Round Table
items.description: The Carved Wood Round Table is a decorative round wood table.

items.name: Carved Wood Sitting Bench
items.description: The Carved Wood Sitting Bench is a decorative wooden bench that provides seating and a small bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Carved Wood Stool

items.description: The Carved Wood Table is a decorative table with seating for six and a bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Carved Wood Wall Shelf
items.description: The Carved Wood Wall Shelf is a decorative item that has two varieties, select R when deploying.

items.name: Carved Wood Wardrobe
items.description: The Carved Wood Wardrobe is a decorative wardrobe with 10 inventory slots. It has two build variants available by selecting 'R' when deploying.

items.name: Cave Scanner
items.description: Locates caves with audible beeping. While the cave scanner is equipped and in hand the scanner's lights will blink and it will beep so long as a cave is somewhat nearby. The frequency of blinking/beeping increases as the Prospector approaches a cave. Furthermore, the scanner will beep more rapidly if the Prospector is looking in the direction of a cave.

items.name: Cave Survival Inhaler
items.description: The Cave Survival Inhaler is a Medicine that boosts resistance to Cave Sickness , increases health and stamina regeneration in caves and adds a 15% chance to harvest additional Stone when mining.

items.name: Caveworm Arrow
items.description: The Caveworm Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Similar to the Poison Arrow , these are helpful in a 'fire and flee' situation. Firing multiple arrows will continue to stack the Poisoned debuff, dealing damage over time.

items.name: Caveworm Bow
items.description: Using arrows and talents interchangeably with other bows, the Caveworm Bow is harder hitting than the Longbow and is equal in strength to the Recurve Bow .

items.name: Caveworm Javelin
items.description: The Caveworm Javelin is a variant of the Caveworm Spear that can only be thrown. Although Javelins have a moderate charge time and projectile travel time, they are one of the highest damage-dealing weapons in Icarus and are devastating when mastered. Crafted in batches of five and stacks up to twenty.

items.name: Caveworm Knife
items.description: The Caveworm Knife is made with resources obtained from Caveworms . Though the Caveworm Knife can be used as a melee weapon or tool to skin fauna, the Caveworm Knife has very little durability, which can prove problematic while on the go as it can only be repaired at an Anvil Bench .

items.name: Caveworm Spear
items.description: Spears increase the range to which Prospectors can attack fauna, providing a unique advantage when up high. Unlike the Caveworm Javelin , the Caveworm Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Caveworm Throwing Knife
items.description: The Caveworm Throwing Knife is a variant of the Caveworm Knife that can be thrown. Unlike the Caveworm Knife , the Caveworm Throwing Knife cannot be used to skin fauna. Crafted in batches of five and stacks up to fifty.

items.name: Caveworm Trophy
items.description: Caveworm Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Caveworm Vestige
items.description: Caveworm Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Caveworm Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Cement Mixer
items.description: The Cement Mixer allows the Prospector to craft Concrete Mix , and Concrete Building Pieces .

items.name: Chala Trophy
items.description: Chala Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Chala Vestige
items.description: Chala Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Chala Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Chamois Trophy
items.description: Chamois Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Chamois Vestige
items.description: Chamois Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Chamois Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Charcoal
items.description: Charcoal is a basic resource used for a variety of items, ranging from Gunpowder to end-game medicines like Antibiotic Pill . It is obtained either as a byproduct of burning wood in a Crafting/Cooking Bench or Furnace that requires wood as a fuel, also it can be obtained from felling a fully burnt tree.

items.name: Charging Station
items.description: The Charging Station charges basic battery powered devices like the Flashlight and requires 500 Watts to function.

items.name: Chargrilled Chicken
items.description: Chargrilled Chicken is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Charred Corn
items.description: Charred Corn is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Cheese
items.description: Cheese is a consumable food that boosts stamina and health regeneration.

items.name: Cheese Pizza Slice
items.description: Cheese Pizza Slice is a late-game Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. It provides a boost to health, stamina, stamina regeneration and experience gained and granted to allies.

items.name: Cheese Roll
items.description: Cheese Roll is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Chemistry Bench
items.description: Grants the Prospector the ability to swiftly create Medicine , Fertilizer , Volatile Substance and Distilled Miasmic Coating .

items.name: Chewy Coconut Cookie
items.description: Chewy Coconut Cookie is a late-game Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Chicken
items.description: A Chicken is a Transplanted farm animal that provides a source of Eggs and Raw Chicken for Food recipes.

items.name: Chimney Cap
items.description: A Chimney Cap is the final cap piece to place on a Chimney Extension or directly on a Fireplace . A smaller variant, the Chimney Cap Half can also be used for the same purpose.

items.name: Chimney Cap Half
items.description: A Chimney Cap Half is a decorative final cap piece to place on a Chimney Extension or directly on a Fireplace . It is the smaller variant of the Chimney Cap , but with less vertical height.

items.name: Chimney Extension
items.description: A Chimney Extension is a decorative section of stone chimney to place on a Fireplace or another existing Chimney Extension to extend the chimney vertically. It is usually capped with a Chimney Cap or Chimney Cap Half .

items.name: Choc-Chip Cookie
items.description: Choc-Chip Cookie is late-game Food that when consumed provides a considerable boost to stamina, charge speed, reload speed and a chance to mine additional stone.

items.name: Chocolate Cake
items.description: Chocolate Cake is a deployable Food item that when placed on a surface will provide 8 Chocolate Cake Pieces that can be picked up and consumed by Prospectors.

items.name: Chocolate Cake Piece
items.description: Chocolate Cake Piece is a late-game Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Classic Rustic Sign
items.description: A Classic Rustic Sign made of wood.

items.name: Clay
items.description: A moldable, fine-grained material that can be baked into bricks. Clay is found in the Swamp Biome in Icarus. In order to collect it, one needs to first break it apart using a Sledgehammer . Clay can be refined into Clay Bricks at any furnace.

items.name: Clay Brick
items.description: Clay Bricks are a refined resource primarily used to craft Clay Brick Building Pieces at an Advanced Masonry Bench / Electric Masonry Bench .
items.crafted_at: Stone Furnace Concrete Furnace Electric Furnace

items.description: Cloth Armor, while not being very protective in a fight, provides relatively good protection from the heat in deserts. It also makes traveling slightly quicker.
