items.name: Coal Ore
items.description: Coal Ore is a Mineral found on Icarus in the open and caves. It's most basic use is as a fuel in a Campfire or Stone Furnace , though this is somewhat inefficient as it is more valuable as component for crafting.

items.name: Cocoa Seed
items.description: Cocoa Seed are a common form of Plantlife found in the Forest and Riverlands locations on Icarus.

items.name: Cocoa Smoked Soft Meat
items.description: Cocoa Smoked Soft Meat is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Coconut Cake
items.description: Coconut Cake is a deployable Food item that when placed on a surface will provide 8 Coconut Cake Pieces that can be picked up and consumed by Prospectors.

items.name: Coconut Cake Piece
items.description: Coconut Cake Piece is a late-game Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Coconut Farming Packet
items.description: The Coconut Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station or the Orbital Exchange Interface and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five seeds that can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop Plots .

items.name: Coffee Bean
items.description: Coffee Bean are a common form of Plantlife found in the Forest and Riverlands locations on Icarus.

items.name: Coffee Farming Packet
items.description: The Coffee Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Coffee seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Coffee Smoked Fatty T-bone
items.description: Coffee Smoked Fatty T-bone is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Cold Steel Arrow
items.description: The Cold Steel Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow , introduced in Chapter - New Frontier . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Cold Steel Axe
items.description: The Cold Steel Axe is a mid/late-game Axe that is introduced with Chapter - New Frontier . The Cold Steel Axe can be crafted while on the surface of Icarus.

items.name: Cold Steel Bolt
items.description: The Cold Steel Bolt is ammunition used with a Crossbow . In addition to projectile damage, it has a chance to inflict a Freeze modifier that slows and damages enemies.

items.name: Cold Steel Ingot
items.description: Cold Steel Ingots are a refined resource crafted from Steel Ingots and Super Cooled Ice . Prospectors must use a Concrete Furnace or an Electric Furnace to refine the resources listed below into a Cold Steel Ingot.

items.name: Cold Steel Javelin
items.description: The Cold Steel Javelin is a variant of the Cold Steel Spear that can only be thrown. Deals frost damage on hit and has a 15% chance to apply a unique debuff to targets while dealing periodic frost damage. Excels when used against Fauna that have a weakness to frost. . When the Freeze modifier does proc, periodic frost damage is dealt to the target over the span of 10 seconds. Fauna with:

items.name: Cold Steel Knife
items.description: The Cold Steel Knife is a mid/late-game Knife that is introduced with the addition of Cold Steel Ingots on the Prometheus map.

items.name: Cold Steel Pickaxe
items.description: The Cold Steel Pickaxe is a mid/late-game Pickaxe that was introduced with New Frontiers .

items.name: Cold Steel Sickle
items.description: Cold Steel Sickle is a Tier 3  Sickle made with Cold Steel Ingots introduced on Prometheus . Due to the materials required, crafting the item requires the New Frontiers DLC.

items.name: Cold Steel Sledgehammer
items.description: Cold Steel Sledgehammer is a Tier 3  Sledgehammer made with Cold Steel Ingots . Due to the materials required, crafting the item requires the New Frontiers DLC.

items.name: Cold Steel Spear
items.description: Element damage does not scale with Spear talents. Unlike the Cold Steel Javelin , the Cold Steel Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Cold Steel Throwing Knife
items.description: The Cold Steel Throwing Knife is a variant of the Cold Steel Knife that can only be thrown and is unlocked upon researching the Cold Steel Knife . Cannot be used to skin Fauna - crafted in batches of five and stacks up to fifty.

items.name: Cold Survival Inhaler
items.description: The Cold Survival Inhaler is a Medicine that boosts resistance to cold, damage from frost and the Hypothermia Status Effect .

items.name: Columbian Mammoth Trophy
items.description: Columbian Mammoth Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Columbian Mammoth Vestige
items.description: Columbian Mammoth Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Columbian Mammoth Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Combat Knife
items.description: While not particularly good for skinning a carcass, this knife excels in close quarters combat. Cannot be thrown.

items.name: Composite Arms Armor
items.description: Composite Arms Armor is the highest tier of crafted armor in Icarus and thus provides superior protection from wildlife, while providing considerable insulation from the elements.

items.name: Composite Arrow
items.description: The Composite Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Composite Chest Armor
items.description: Composite Chest Armor is the highest tier of crafted armor in Icarus and thus provides superior protection from wildlife, while providing considerable insulation from the elements.

items.name: Composite Dropship Recall Beacon
items.description: The Composite Dropship Recall Beacon will fire a flare that calls the Prospectors dropship to that location when thrown, which can either be used for immediate extraction or left there for use later on. Multiple Recall Beacons can be used per session, however, these are one-use items, so use them carefully. Items stored in the dropships inventory will not be lost when the dropship is called, allowing Prospectors to transport equipment/resources over large distances.

items.name: Composite Feet Armor
items.description: Composite Feet Armor is the highest tier of crafted armor in Icarus and thus provides superior protection from wildlife, while providing considerable insulation from the elements.

items.name: Composite Head Armor
items.description: Composite Head Armor is the highest tier of crafted armor in Icarus and thus provides superior protection from wildlife, while providing considerable insulation from the elements.

items.name: Composite Javelin
items.description: The Composite Javelin is a variant of the Composite Spear that can only be thrown and is the highest damage dealing Javelin currently available. Despite the heavy tech investment to reach Composites , Composite Javelins are far cheaper to craft than the Titanium Javelin and are worth the investment for the increased damage and low projectile break chance.

items.name: Composite Legs Armor
items.description: Composite Legs Armor is the highest tier of crafted armor in Icarus and thus provides superior protection from wildlife, while providing considerable insulation from the elements.

items.name: Composite Paste
items.description: Composite Paste is an end-game crafted resource which can be smelted into Composites inside of the Electric Furnace .

items.name: Composite Spear
items.description: The Composite Spear is an upgrade to the Titanium Spear that deals more damage and is cheaper to craft once Composites can be crafted. Despite Composites being a hefty tech investment, the Composite Spear has the highest damage output and durability outside of Prometheus exclusive Spears. Unlike the Composite Javelin , the Composite Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Composite Tactical Shield
items.description: The Composite Tactical Shield is crafted at the Foundry with the following resources:

items.name: Composites
items.description: Composites are an end-game crafted material used to make Tier 4  Armors and various Weapons / Deployables . Prospectors require a Material Processor , an Electric Furnace , and Power .

items.name: Compound Bow
items.description: The tail-end of the 20th Century brought about many advancements in technology and archery didn't get left behind. A Compound Bow works like a simple block and tackle, multiplying input energy over distance with it's Cam and Idler Wheel pulleys, instead of traditional bow limbs; which allows the Compound Bow to hit harder than the Recurve Bow .

items.name: Condensed Enzymes
items.description: Condensed Enzymes are a unique resource in Icarus, introduced as part of the horde events. These geysers are scattered across various biomes. To trigger the event, players need to deploy a Vapor Condenser (crafted at the Fabricator ) on top of an Enzyme Geysers . Successfully completing the event typically rewards players with Exotics ; however, once the reward cap of three Exotics is reached, further completions will yield Condensed Enzymes instead.

items.name: Cooling Bandage
items.description: The Cooling Bandage is used to heal Heatstroke, Heat Exhaustion and Exotic Overheat Status Effects . If the Prospector's core temperature is still extremely high, the cooling bandage will not remove these debuffs.

items.name: Copper Attachment
items.description: Copper Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Tool Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Copper Bolt
items.description: The Copper Bolt is ammunition used with a Crossbow . Like arrows and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Copper Cluster Lamp
items.description: The Copper Cluster Lamp is a simple low output lamp that does not require fuel to operate but does require water to craft.

items.description: Copper Nail are used widely in crafting of items such as interior Interior Wood Building Pieces , and other items made of Refined Wood at the Carpentry Bench and Machining Bench .

items.name: Copper Ore
items.description: Copper Ore is an early-game Mineral Resource . It is widely used in the construction of Interior Wood Building Pieces , and prospectors can make extensive use of copper once they reach level 20 and unlock Tier 3  , as it is a crucial component in Electronics . In the late game, copper is used in various deployables like the Refrigerator and the Material Processor .

items.name: Copper Wire
items.description: Copper Wire is used in a variety of high-end buildings and components and is crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Corn
items.description: Corn are a common form of Plantlife found in the Forest and Riverlands locations on Icarus. When consumed by prospectors, they replenish Hunger .

items.name: Corn Farming Packet
items.description: The Corn Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Corn seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Cow
items.description: A Cow is the mature version of a Calf that can be purchased and brought down to the planet primarily to produce Milk .

items.name: Crafting
items.description: Crafting is the skill that enables many of the other ways prospectors pursue their goals on Icarus. While they can gather Food with their bare hands, and can attempt to Hunt with their fists, everything they attempt on the moon's surface is facilitated by crafting.

items.name: Crafting Bench
items.description: The Crafting Bench allows the prospector to craft Tier 2  items. While it can be placed with no shelter, it would be unusable. Will take damage if left without shelter (or under severely damaged roof) in storms.

items.name: Cream
items.description: Cream is a late-game intermediate resource crafted from Milk and used in various recipes.

items.name: Creamed Corn
items.description: Creamed Corn is a Food that satisfies Hunger . It provides the unique Status Effect , Creamed Corn , which increases maximum Health and Stamina and reduces the Stamina consumed by actions.

items.name: Crispy Bacon
items.description: Crispy Bacon is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Crispy Potato
items.description: Crispy Potato is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Crocodile Skin Saddle
items.description: The Crocodile Skin Saddle is a saddle for mounts that has an crocodile theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC and is a cosmetic change to the Basic Riding Saddle that provides no additional attributes.

items.name: Crocodile Trophy
items.description: Crocodile Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. items.name: Crossbow
items.description: The earliest known Crossbows were invented on Earth in the first millennium BC, not later than the 7th century BC in ancient China, not later than the 1st century AD in Greece; on Icarus, Prospectors will test this ancient technology in many challenges to see if it still holds up.

items.name: Crude Ammo
items.description: Crude Ammo is a crude, low-tech ammunition that works with all categories of Pistols .

items.name: Crumbed Saltwater Fillet

items.description: Crunchy Soy Bean is a consumable food that boosts maximum health and health regeneration.

items.name: Crushed Bone

items.name: Cryogenically Frozen Calf
items.description: The Cryogenically Frozen Calf is a deployable container containing a Calf that can be researched and obtained in the Workshop and called down to the planet using the Orbital Exchange Interface .

items.name: Cryogenically Frozen Chicken
items.description: The Cryogenically Frozen Chicken is a deployable container containing a Chicken that can be researched and obtained in the Workshop and called down to the planet using the Orbital Exchange Interface .

items.name: Crystallized Miasma
items.description: Crystallized Miasma is a resource required to make Distilled Miasmic Coating , a precursor resource used in making Miasmic Tools, Weapons, and Ammunition. Crystallized Miasma is collected from Fauna located in Swamps across Icarus - a map of Prometheus regions can be found here ).

items.name: Culinex Backpack
items.description: The Culinex Backpack provides six inventory slots, reduces consumption of food and water, adds +25% to the effectiveness of cooked food modifiers and increases the duration of cooked food modifiers by +25% for items cooked with the backpack equipped.

items.name: Deep Mining Ore Scanner
items.description: Locates Deep Ore Deposits within the area that can be mined with a Biofuel Deep-Mining Drill or an Electric Deep-Mining Drill . Does not indicate the type of deep ore deposit detected, unlike the Advanced Deep Mining Ore Scanner .

items.name: Dehumidifier
items.description: The Dehumidifier allows for cave exploration without the risk of catching Cave Sickness within its effective range. Unlike the Electric Dehumidifier , the Dehumidifier does not prevent Caveworms from spawning.

items.name: Deluxe Leather Saddle
items.description: The Deluxe Leather Saddle is a saddle for Mounts made with cured leather. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC and is a cosmetic change to the Basic Riding Saddle that provides no additional attributes.

items.name: Desert Animal Feed
items.description: Desert Animal Feed is an Animal Feed for Pets or Mounts with a unique Status Effect . Can be fed to mounts to satisfy Hunger . Desert Animal Feed decays in 10,800 seconds, but that decay can be slowed down by storing Desert Animal Feed inside an Ice Box or Refrigerator .

items.name: Desert Tracker Saddle
items.description: The Desert Tracker Saddle is a saddle for mounts that has desert theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC and is a cosmetic change to the Basic Riding Saddle that provides no additional attributes.

items.name: Detoxifier Module
items.description: This module increases poison resistance by 50% when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot, reducing the amount of damage received when poisoned. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Detoxifier Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit. The resistance increase from each Detoxifier Module will stack and will grant near immunity to poison if four are equipped.

items.name: Directional Worklamp
items.description: The Directional Worklamp provides lighting for a Prospector's base. Requires 150 units of power to function.

items.name: Dirt
items.description: Dirt is a Resource found on the surface of Icarus in Forest , Grassland , and Swamp biomes. Dirt is collected with a Shovel and can be used to make a variety of items.

items.name: Dirt Corner
items.description: Dirt Corners are a Tier 1  buildable that are used in tandem with Dirt Ramps , allowing for the creation of rounded ramps. Due to the nature of its building material, Dirt Corners must be attached to the terrain when placed; failure to do so will result in the collapse of the building piece.

items.name: Dirt Foundation
items.description: Dirt Foundations are a Tier 1  buildable that serves as an alternative to Thatch Beams / Wood Beams that provides a more natural look to structures. Due to the nature of its building material, Dirt Foundations must be attached to the terrain when placed; failure to do so will result in the collapse of the building piece.

items.name: Dirt Mounds
items.description: A Shovel can be used on grass/dirt/mud to create a dirt mound by right-clicking. Dirt mounds can also be made in bulk by using a Seeding Cart .

items.name: Dirt Ramp
items.description: Dirt Ramps are a Tier 1  buildable that serves as an alternative to Thatch Ramps / Wood Ramps that provides a more natural look to structures. Due to the nature of its building material, Dirt Ramps must be attached to the terrain when placed; failure to do so will result in the collapse of the building piece.

items.name: Distilled Miasmic Coating
items.description: Distilled Miasmic Coating is a refined resource primarily used to craft a variety of Miasmic Tools, Weapons, and Ammunition that can give Prospectors an edge while on the surface of Icarus.

items.name: Dogtags Lure
items.description: The Dogtags Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. Like all Lures , the Dogtags Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: DoseUp Module
items.description: This module reduces oxygen, food, and water consumption by 15% when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Dose Up Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit and will further reduce the consumption of oxygen, food, and water.

items.name: Drac Trophy
items.description: Drac Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Drac Vestige
items.description: Drac Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Drac Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Dreadwing Trophy
items.description: Dreadwing Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Dreadwing Vestige
items.description: Dreadwing Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Dreadwing Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Dried Avocado
items.description: Dried Avocado is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Dried Fatty T-Bone
items.description: Dried Fatty T-Bone is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Dried Freshwater Fillet
items.description: Dried Freshwater Fillet is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Dried Gamey Meat
items.description: Dried Gamey Meat is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.description: Dried Giant Steak is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.description: Dried Rhubarb is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Dried Saltwater Fillet
items.description: Dried Saltwater Fillet is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Dried Soft Meat
items.description: Dried Soft Meat is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Dried Stringy Meat
items.description: Dried Stringy Meat is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Dried Tomato
items.description: Dried Tomato is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Dried White Meat
items.description: Dried White Meat is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Drying Rack
items.description: The Drying Rack is an early-game cooking bench that provides a way for Prospectors to preserve foods, while also giving the Prospector a variety of unique status effects from various dried foods. The Drying Rack can also be used to create Cured Leather .

items.name: Economic Attachment
items.description: Economic Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Egg
items.description: An egg from a Chicken .

items.name: Electric Carpentry Bench
items.description: The Electric Carpentry Bench allows for manufacturing of refined wood deployables at a faster rate than the Carpentry Bench . Prospectors can use the Electric Carpentry Bench to craft furniture, like an improved Wooden Bed , and storage items like an Interior Wood Cupboard . The Electric Carpentry Bench can also create Interior Wood building pieces.

items.name: Electric Chimney Cap
items.description: A Electric Chimney Cap is the final cap piece to place on an Electric Chimney Extension or directly on an Electric Fireplace .

items.name: Electric Chimney Extension
items.description: A Electric Chimney Extension is a wide flat section of metal chimney or stove pipe to place on a Electric Fireplace or another existing Electric Chimney Extension to extend the chimney vertically. It is usually capped with a Electric Chimney Cap .

items.name: Electric Composter
items.description: The Electric Composter enables the Prospector to produce Biofuel at an accelerated rate compared to the Biofuel Composter . An active power connection providing at least 1500 units is required to operate the Electric Composter. Similar to the Biofuel Composter , an active Water source increases processing speed and is not required.

items.name: Electric Deep-Mining Drill
items.description: The Electric Deep-Mining Drill will mine Deep Mining Ore Deposits when supplied with 2,000 units of Power . The Electric Deep-Mining Drill has more inventory slots, twenty in all, 15 more slots than its biofuel counterpart. This allows 1000 or 2000 ore to be accumulated before needing to be emptied, depending on the ore type.

items.name: Electric Dehumidifier
items.description: The Electric Dehumidifier allows for cave exploration without the risk of catching Cave Sickness while also preventing cave worms from spawning within its effective range. Will not prevent creatures from spawning when activating Thumpers , Radars, or other mission items that have been placed or activated.

items.name: Electric Extractor
items.description: The Electric Extractor is used to extract Exotics from Exotic Deposits. A connection providing at least 1,500 units of power is required.

items.name: Electric Fireplace
items.description: The Electric Fireplace is Tier 4  version of the Fireplace that is powered by Electricity to provide a source of heat, a source of light , Coziness and a means to cook Food indoors. At least 250 units of electricity are required to power the fireplace.

items.name: Electric Furnace
items.description: The Electric Furnace is the end-game furnace capable of smelting Composite Paste into Composites , a material required for most Tier 4  blueprints, and can refine all other minerals faster than the lower tier furnaces.

items.name: Electric Masonry Bench
items.description: The Electric Masonry Bench enables the construction of Stone Building Pieces and Concrete Building Pieces at a faster rate than the Masonry Bench and Cement Mixer , but only once the Prospector researches the blueprints for building pieces. The Electric Masonry Bench can also craft all building pieces made at the Masonry Bench / Advanced Masonry Bench .

items.name: Electric Radar
items.description: The Electric Radar is used to scan for Exotic / Volatile Raw Exotic deposits. Once activated, aggravated Fauna (varies per region) will attempt to destroy the radar by any means necessary. Radars of all types will show ALL exotic veins on the map in each scan, regardless of whether they have been depleted. Scans performed in an Outpost will not complete as there are no exotic veins in them. This can be used to spawn aggressive wildlife for resources or experience.

items.name: Electric Stove
items.description: The Electric Stove is a late-game technology that provides a more robust cooking experience and expands the recipes available compared to the Biofuel Stove . It requires 1,000 units of Power to function and must be snapped to a side of a Marble Kitchen Bench or Kitchen Bench .

items.name: Electric Textiles Bench
items.description: A power connection providing at least 2,500 of power is required to utilize this bench. Allows for the crafting of more advanced Armor sets and items that can be made at the Textiles Bench and Advanced Textiles Bench .

items.name: Electric Water Pump
items.description: The Electric Water Pump provides Water when supplied with electricity, use the Water Pipe Tool to connect it to Crafting Benches / Water Storage to provide water. Requires 1,000 units of Electricity to function and outputs 1,000 units of Water .

items.name: Electric Water Purifier
items.description: Electric Water Purifiers can be crafted from the Fabricator with the following resources once the appropriate blueprint point has been spent:

items.name: Electricity Tool
items.description: The Electricity Tool connects Power Sources to Deployables / Power Storage to provide Electricity .

items.name: Electrolytic Oxygen Synthesizer
items.description: The Electrolytic Oxygen Synthesizer produces oxygen from water, removing the need for Oxite . Requires 1,550 Watts and 500 Liters per second to function. The Electrolytic Oxygen Synthesizer can hold up to 10 Oxygen Containers and will auto fill tanks in seconds.

items.name: Electronic Food Trough
items.description: All Food Troughs have an allow list for nearby animals that can be accessed by pressing 'X'. To change which animals can eat from a specific food trough, select the animals permitted to eat from the food trough and select "Allowlist-Only Interaction". By default, all nearby animals can eat from food troughs.

items.name: Electronics
items.description: Electronics are used in a variety of high-end buildings and components.

items.name: Elegant Curtain Door
items.description: The Elegant Curtain Door is a luxury decorative covering for a doorway.
items.crafted_at: Advanced Textiles Bench Electric Textiles Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Advanced Textiles Bench Electric Textiles Bench

items.name: Elegant Curtain Window
items.description: The Elegant Curtain Window is a luxury decorative window covering.
items.crafted_at: Advanced Textiles Bench Electric Textiles Bench

items.name: Elephant Trophy
items.description: Elephant Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Elephant Vestige
items.description: Elephant Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create an Elephant Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Encrypted Satellite Upgrade
items.description: The Encrypted Satellite Upgrade grants Prospectors access to Operations locked behind encrypted signals. Note: an Infrasonic Relay Upgrade must also be slotted into a CONT4CT Device to access encrypted signals.

items.name: Endurance Animal Feed
items.description: Endurance Animal Feed is an Animal Feed for Pets or Mounts with a unique Status Effect . Can be fed to mounts to satisfy Hunger . Endurance Animal Feed decays in 10,800 seconds, but that decay can be slowed down by storing Endurance Animal Feed inside an Ice Box or Refrigerator .

items.name: Endurogel
items.description: Endurogel is a Consumable that restores a portion of stamina when consumed. It is a one time use consumable.

items.name: Energy Bar
items.description: Energy Bar is a long-lasting Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. It provides buffs good for being on the go.

items.name: Enzyme Geysers
items.description: Enzyme Geysers are natural formations found across several biomes in Icarus. These geysers are important resource nodes that offer valuable materials depending on the equipment used.

items.name: Epoxy
items.description: Epoxy is used extensively in crafting a variety of items deep into the end-game. Prospectors will find themselves stocking up on epoxy very often.

items.name: Equix Trophy
items.description: Equix Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Equix Vestige
items.description: Equix Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create an Equix Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Exotic Harvester
items.description: The Exotic Harvester is used to extract Volatile Raw Exotics from Volatile Raw Exotic deposits. Requires 1,500 k Wh to operate.

items.name: Exotics
items.description: Exotics are one the most valuable Mineral harvested on Icarus and are a potential reward for completing certain Missions / Operations . They were the reason terraforming failed on Icarus, and now their unique properties are sought after by the various Factions seeking to exploit Icarus.
harvested_from: any mission except Potshot: Training; the yield per vein
where they are located vary per mission

items.name: F.I.S.H.
items.description: When held, the F.I.S.H. will scan the area and indicate which fish can be caught in the area with the base percent chance of catching each. As the Prospector catches each type, the icons for each will appear on the display.

items.name: Fabricator
items.description: The Fabricator is the late-game crafting bench, it enables the crafting of Weapons and Tools like the Combat Knife and a Titanium Pickaxe . It also enables the creation of power sources, such as the Biofuel Generator , and the Refrigerator .

items.name: Farmers Satchel
items.description: Farmers Satchel is a leather satchel that is a Tier 2  upgrade for the Seed Pouch , has 24 inventory slots and holds both Fertilizer and Seeds .
items.crafted_at: Crafted AtTextiles BenchAdvanced Textiles BenchElectric Textiles Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Crafted AtTextiles BenchAdvanced Textiles BenchElectric Textiles Bench

items.name: Fiber
items.description: In-game description: A bundle of soft fiber, highly useful.

items.name: Fiber Farming Packet
items.description: The Fiber Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Fiber seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Fiber Lure
items.description: The Fiber Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. The capture zone increase is the size of the capture area during the fishing minigame, increasing the success chance of catching a fish. Like all Lures , the Fiber Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Filtered Water Trough
items.description: The Filtered Water Trough is an expensive variant of the Large Water Trough that is used to keep Mounts and Pets hydrated. Currently does not apply a modifier to animals that drink from it, making it an expensive upgrade to it's lower tier counterparts. Must be connected to Electricity and Water providing at least 1,000 Watts and 30 liters per second to function.

items.name: Fire Arrow
items.description: Want to turn that forest filled with bears into an inferno? The fire arrow is your friend. Need a light at the top of that cave? Fire arrow. While not as bright as the Flare Arrow , it will continue burning upon impact. Similar to the Poison Arrow , the Fire Arrow is a DOT upgrade to the Stone Arrow , which is helpful when in a 'fire and flee' situation. These arrows cannot be recovered once fired.

items.name: Fire Extinguisher
items.description: The Fire Extinguisher is a Tier 3  tool used to hastily put out fires. As Prospectors use the Fire Extinguisher, its durability decreases and cannot be repaired at the Machining Bench when broken.

items.name: Fire Whacker
items.description: The Fire Whacker is used to put out brush fires on the ground, other players who are on fire, or structures that are ablaze from lightning strikes. The Fire Whacker can also be used to put yourself out - aim down at your feet and start whacking; cannot be in/on source of fire while attempting to use the fire whacker on yourself.

items.name: Firepit
items.description: The Firepit is an upgrade to the Campfire , providing significantly more heat, increased inventory size, and is marginally faster at processing. Due to the increased weight of the Firepit, it should only be deployed in structures that provide adequate support.

items.name: Fireplace
items.description: The Fireplace is deployable stone and wood building piece that provides a source of heat, a source of light, Coziness and a safer alternative to cooking Food than the Campfire . It provides an indoor source of heat that allows the prospector to avoid inadvertently setting themselves ablaze.

items.name: First Cohort Envirosuit
items.description: As part of the ICARUS: Supporters Edition (unavailable for purchase), prospectors received an exclusive UDA envirosuit with a built-in water slot  giving an edge to prospectors who dare pursue fortune on the moon's surface. Theres no better way to show your commitment than to wear it with pride. The First Cohort Envirosuit is researched and crafted in the Workshop on the Space Station .
items.crafted_at: the Workshop on the Space Station

base_recipe.crafted_at: the Workshop on the Space Station

items.name: Fish Chunk Stew
items.description: Fish Chunk Stew is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Fish Chunks
items.description: Fish Chunks are added to the Prospector's inventory after looting the carcass of a fish. Fish caught using a Fishing Trap or Fishing Rod can be converted into Fish Chunks as well. Fish Chunks can be cooked in a Campfire , or used in other dishes such as Freshwater Fillet Curry or Crumbed Saltwater Fillet . Right-click a Freshwater/Saltwater fish to convert it into Fish Chunks .

items.name: Fish Pie
items.description: Fish Pie is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Fish Trophy Mount
items.description: The Fish Trophy Mount can be used to display impressive catches with details of the quality, weight, and length of the fish shown. When holding down R, Prospectors can choose between 3 different variants. Fish stored in the Fish Trophy Mount will not spoil. All Fish obtained using a Fishing Rod or Fishing Trap can be placed in the Fish Trophy Mount.

items.name: Fisher's Module
items.description: This module increases the user's ability to catch Unique Fish and, somehow, increases the quality of caught fish. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Fisher's Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit, which will further increasing the user's ability to fish and become the Master Angler they wish to be.

items.name: Flamethrower
items.description: The Flamethrower is a biofuel-powered weapon that sprays a jet of flame that sets fire to any creatures or flammable materials such as trees, shrubs or Wood Building Pieces .

items.name: Flare Arrow
items.description: Flare Arrows are used to light up dark areas/cave roofs and can be shot high into the air to illuminate the darkness or to signal fellow Prospectors from a distance. These arrows cannot be recovered once fired.

items.name: Flashlight
items.description: The Flashlight is a late-game Light Source , capable of illuminating an entire cave. Can be equipped in the "L" light slot on the hotbar.

items.name: Flatbread
items.description: Flatbread is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Flatbread Dough
items.description: Flatbread Dough is the precursor to the mid/late-game Food Flatbread . Flatbread Dough will eventually decay, but can be preserved in an Ice Box , Refrigerator , or Deep Freeze .

items.name: Flexible Frame Attachment
items.description: Flexible Frame Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Flint Arrow
items.description: The Flint Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Floor Torch
items.description: Basic lighting for a prospector's base or elsewhere.

items.name: Flour
items.description: Flour is prepared from ground Wheat and is the primary precursor for Flatbread Dough , Bread Dough and Pastry .

items.name: Flow Meter
items.description: Power/water networks can be connected to a Flow Meter, where it will display how much power/water is being produced, consumed, and stored. Only one network can be shown at a time - press 'F' to toggle between power and water networks. Deployables can be toggled on/off remotely via the Flow Meter.

items.name: Food Consumption Paste
items.description: In-game description: An organic confection that arrests hunger for a limited time. In-game flavor text: Just because it's organic, doesn't mean it's good for you.

items.name: Food Trough
items.description: The Food Trough is a basic trough used to feed Mounts / Pets and is recommended if prospectors wish to idly tame a juvenile. Food Troughs benefit from the Extra Space I / Extra Space II talent.

items.name: Forge
items.description: The Forge is the Tier 3  variant of the Anvil Bench that will allow the Prospector to craft higher quality tools such as the Platinum Pickaxe , Cold Steel Knife , etc and items crafted at the Anvil Bench ( Iron Axe , Copper Nails , etc). It is also where these tools can be repaired. Unlike other benches, the Forge can be deployed and used outdoors as it does not require shelter. Can be used indoors or outdoors.

items.name: Foundry
items.description: The Foundry is the Tier 4  variant of the Anvil Bench that will allow the Prospector to craft the highest quality tools/weapons available on planet, such as the Titanium Pickaxe , Compound Bow , etc. The Foundry is also capable of crafting Tier 2  / Tier 3  tools and weapons, removing the need for a Anvil Bench and Forge .

items.name: Frag Grenade
items.description: An explosive weapon thrown by hand. Hold left click to charge a throw. The grenade timer starts when the grenade leaves your hand and will take a few seconds to detonate. Stacks up to 5.

items.name: Freshwater Fish Fillet
items.description: Freshwater Fish Fillet is is the result of filleting a Freshwater Fish at a Basic Fishing Bench . While eating Freshwater Fish Fillet will replenish a small amount of Hunger , there is a possibility of negative Status Effects when doing so. It is better to Cook before eating.

items.name: Fried Chicken
items.description: Fried Chicken is a long-lasting Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs.

items.name: Fried Chunky Vegetables
items.description: Fried Chunky Vegetables is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Fried Fish Chunks
items.description: Fried Fish Chunks is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Fried Tomato
items.description: Fried Tomato is a consumable food that boosts stamina and health regeneration. As Tomatoes are only found on Prometheus , this recipe requires the New Frontiers DLC to obtain the ingredients.

items.name: Frontier Revolver
items.description: The Frontier Revolver is a Legendary Weapon that can be purchased at the Bio-lab .

items.name: Frozen Ore
items.description: Frozen Ore is a resource produced as a by-product of mining a mineral node with a Pickaxe that has a chance to produce frozen ore, such as the Cold Steel Pickaxe or Inaris "Viridian" Pickaxe .

items.name: Fruit Muffin
items.description: Fruit Muffin is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Fruit Pie
items.description: Fruit Pie is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Fruit Salad
items.description: Fruit Salad is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Fruit Smoothie
items.description: Fruit Smoothie is a refreshing Drink that when consumed provides a boost to experience gained and resistance to cave sickness.

items.name: Fruit Snack Pack
items.description: Fruit Snack Pack is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Full Sandworm Brazier
items.description: The Full Sandworm Brazier is a large deployable and decorative source of Heat and Light made from the remains of a Sandworm .

items.name: Full Sandworm Trophy
items.description: The Full Sandworm Trophy is a large decorative deployable that can be placed on the ground to display the remains of a once mighty Sandworm .

items.name: Fur
items.description: Fur is widely used when crafting Armors , and in certain Deployables like the Bedroll . It is a crucial ingredient in Fur Armor , which is essential equipment for prospectors venturing into the Arctic Biome for the first time.

items.name: Fur Arms Armor
items.description: Fur armor is a sidegrade to Leather Armor , offering slightly less physical resistance in exchange for a major boost to cold resistance, making it a necessity when venturing into cold regions. It, however, greatly reduces resistance to heat, making it problematic when delving into hotter biomes.

items.name: Gold Ore
items.description: Gold Ore is a Mineral Resource . Prospectors can make extensive use of Gold Ore once they reach level 20 and unlock Tier 3  , as it is a crucial component in Electronics .

items.name: Gold Ore Lure
items.description: The Gold Ore Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. The capture zone size increase widens the size of the capture area during the fishing minigame, increasing the success chance of catching a fish. Like all Lures , the Gold Ore Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Gold Wire
items.description: Gold Wire is used in a variety of high-end buildings and components and is crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Gorse Farming Packet
items.description: The Gorse Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Gorse seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Gorse Flower
items.description: Gorse Flower are a common form of Plantlife found in the Forest and Riverlands locations on Icarus.

items.name: Gorse Flower Lure
items.description: The Gorse Flower Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. Like all Lures , the Gorse Flower Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Gorse Smoked Gamey Meat
items.description: Gorse Smoked Gamey Meat is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Gorse Tea
items.description: Mid-game warm beverage made by combining a filled Liquid Container such as a Thermos and Gorse Flower .

items.name: Grilled Freshwater Fillet
items.description: Grilled Freshwater Fillet is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Growth Fertilizer
items.description: Growth Fertilizer is used on crop plots to enhance the growth speed of grown crops. When applied, Crop Growth Speed is increased by 50% and Crop Yield is decreased by 25% for 1200 seconds. To fertilize a crop plot, equip a fertilizer of your choosing from your hotbar and left click the plot you wish to fertilize.

items.name: Guano
items.description: Guano is a resource found within the nests of Arctic Vespers , these bat-like creatures inhabit the arctic regions of the game. Players can harvest Guano from their nests once destroyed, providing a valuable material for crafting.

items.name: Gunpowder
items.description: Gunpowder is a precursor resource used in making Ammunition , weapons like the Frag Grenade , and Volatile Substance .

items.name: Handcannon Attachment
items.description: Handcannon Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Healing Boost Module
items.description: When equipped in a module slot of an Envirosuit , this module decreases the duration of negative afflictions received by other Prospectors near the user, however it does not affect the wearer. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop .

items.name: Health Buff Paste
items.description: In-game description: An organic preparation that temporarily increases health. In-game flavor text: Like so many things on Icarus, the exact ingredients would probably render this concoction illegal on Earth.

items.name: Health Recovery Elixir
items.description: Health Recovery Elixir is a craftable Medicine that immediately boosts your health by 500 points when consumed.

items.name: Health Regeneration Paste
items.description: In-game description: A herbal confection that speeds healing. In-game flavor text: The lily's high concentration of bioactive ingredients is thought to inhibit the reuptake of certain cytochromes, briefly flooding your body with oxidating enzymes.

items.name: Health Restoration Paste
items.description: In-game description: An organic fusion that restores health. In-game flavor text: The combination of Icarus's unique conditions and genetic adjustments to plant life has seen the addition of 'useful' methyl chains to many previously innocuous plant-based preparations.

items.name: Hearty Salad
items.description: Hearty Salad is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Heat Bandage
items.description: Heat Bandage is used to heal Frostbite, Frosty and Exotic Chill Status Effects . If the Prospector's core temperature is still freezing, the heat bandage will not remove these debuffs.

items.name: Heat Survival Inhaler
items.description: The Heat Survival Inhaler is a Medicine that boosts resistance to heat, damage from fire and the Hyperthermia Status Effect .

items.name: Heated Animal Bed
items.description: The Heated Animal Bed is a bed for Mounts and Pets that has a luxurious theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC . Provides no additional attributes and is a cosmetic change to the Animal Bed .

items.name: Heavy Air Conditioner
items.description: The Heavy Air Conditioner provides Climate Control inside of a building, making it a great addition to any outpost located in a Desert . A connection providing at least 250 electricity is required to use the Heavy Air Conditioner.

items.name: Heavy Flamethrower
items.description: The Heavy Flamethrower is a heavy duty Biofuel -powered flamethrower Legendary Weapon . It can be purchased at the Bio-lab .

items.name: Heavy Heater
items.description: The Heavy Heater provides Climate Control inside of a building, making it a great addition to any outpost located in a Arctic . A connection providing at least 250 units of Power is required to use the Heavy Heater.

items.name: Hydroponic Crop Plot
items.description: The Hydroponic Crop Plot is a farming plot for growing Seeds that can later be harvested for Plant Resources once fully grown. Unless the Prospector has the Fresh Is Best talent when deploying a seed into the crop plot, the grown Plant Resource will eventually wither if not harvested.

items.name: Hyena Bait
items.description: Hyena Bait is a single-use Crafted Resource used to attract and capture Wild Hyenas when used with a Snare Trap . Hyena Bait does not decay and can only be used in Desert and Volcanic Biomes. Stacks up to ten.

items.name: Hyena Rug
items.description: Hyena Rugs are decorative deployables that can be placed on any ground surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from being for decorative purposes, it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Hyena Trophy
items.description: Hyena Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Hyena Vestige
items.description: Hyena Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Hyena Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary . They are also used at any textiles bench to make Hyena Rugs . Decorative purposes aside, both provide a boost to coziness, which increases the duration and effect of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: IC-001 Extractor
items.description: This device is used to extract Exotics from Exotic Deposits. It requires the IC-001 Prototype Power Source to operate and can extract approximately 330 exotics per power source. The speed of the IC-001 Extractor is the same as the Electric Extractor . Due to a bug, the IC-001 Extractor will operate at the same speed as the Biofuel Extractor .

items.name: IC-001 Prototype Power Source
items.description: The IC-001 Prototype Power Source is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station . It is used to power the IC-001 Extractor . It can be used to extract 330 exotics before depleting and has a stack size of one.

items.name: IC-001 Radar
items.description: The IC-001 Radar is used to scan for Exotic / Volatile Raw Exotic deposits. Once activated, aggravated Fauna (varies per region) will attempt to destroy the radar by any means necessary. Radars of all types will show ALL exotic veins on the map in each scan, regardless of whether they have been depleted. Scans performed in an Outpost will not complete as there are no exotic veins in them. This can be used to spawn aggressive wildlife for resources or experience.

items.name: Ice
items.description: Like stone, prospectors can harvest individual pieces by hand while in the Arctic . However, it is much more efficient to gather Ice from snowpack with a Shovel . Deep Freezers can also be used to generate Ice.

items.name: Ice Borer
items.description: The Ice Borer will drill super-cooled ice deposits when supplied with biofuel from a Biofuel Can / MXC Fuel Canister . Super-cooled ice deposits can only be found on frozen lakes and rivers in the Arctic regions of Prometheus (Biomes: Glacial Cascade or Alpine Steppe - a map of Prometheus biomes can be found here .). The Ice Borer has 5 slots and will last 2 hours and 5 minutes on a full Biofuel Can .

items.name: Ice Box
items.description: The Ice Box will slow the decay of food placed inside, increasing the time until food spoils by 6x when filled with Ice . Items in Ice Box reduce their spoil rate by 500% and the container has 12 inventory slots.

items.name: Ignari Trophy
items.description: Ignari Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. items.name: Ignari Vestige

items.name: Inaris "Agua" Spear
items.description: Element damage does not scale with Spear talents. The Inaris "Agua" Spear cannot be thrown, and there are currently no Workshop Javelins .

items.name: Inaris "Aruda" Arrow
items.description: The Inaris "Aruda" Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass.

items.name: Inaris "Aruda" Arrow Bundle
items.description: Consuming the Inaris "Aruda" Arrow Bundle will add 25x Inaris "Aruda" Arrow s to the Prospectors inventory, must be consumed after dropping into a prospect. Consumed arrow bundles cannot be taken back to the space station. Arrow bundles that have not been consumed can be taken back to the space station for use in another prospect.

items.name: Inaris "Biana" Arrow
items.description: The Inaris "Biana" Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. The elemental damage dealt by these arrows are not effected by Bow talents.

items.name: Inaris "Biana" Arrow Bundle
items.description: Consuming the Inaris "Biana" Arrow Bundle will add 25x Inaris "Biana" Arrow s to the Prospectors inventory, must be consumed after dropping into a Prospect. Consumed arrow bundles cannot be taken back to the space station. Arrow bundles that have not been consumed can be taken back to the space station for use in another prospect.

The Inaris "Cerulean" Knife cannot be thrown, and there currently are no workshop Throwing Knives .

items.description: The Inaris "Heavy" Crossbow is the opposite of the Inaris "Rapid" Crossbow , trading reload speed for a significant boost to overall damage. The Inaris "Heavy" Crossbow can use Crossbow Bolts crafted on planet as well as Bolts crafted in the Workshop .

items.name: Inaris "Lua" Envirosuit
items.description: The Inaris "Lua" Envirosuit is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station .

items.name: Inaris "Lune" Crossbow
items.description: The Inaris "Lune" Crossbow can use Crossbow Bolts crafted on planet as well as Workshop Bolts . Firing faster and dealing more damage than its predecessors, the Inaris "Lune" Crossbow, as a whole, is a must for avid Crossbow users.

items.name: Inaris "Netch" Arrow
items.description: The Inaris "Netch" Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. The elemental damage dealt by these arrows are not effected by Bow talents.

items.name: Inaris "Netch" Arrow Bundle
items.description: Consuming the Inaris "Netch" Arrow Bundle will add 25x Inaris "Biana" Arrow s to the Prospectors inventory, must be consumed after dropping into a Prospect. Consumed arrow bundles cannot be taken back to the space station. Arrow bundles that have not been consumed can be taken back to the space station for use in another prospect.

items.name: Inaris "Neves" Pickaxe
items.description: The Inaris "Neves" Pickaxe is the Workshop equivalent of a Titanium Pickaxe , allowing Prospectors to mine higher tier metals ( Aluminium Ore , Platinum Ore , etc) at earlier stages of a Prospect while greatly increasing yield. Unlike other pickaxes, the Inaris "Neves" Pickaxe is the only pickaxe that reduces the over-encumbrance penalty by 50% when equipped, which makes mobility while over-encumbered bearable when paired with the talent Carry On and Mass Dampener Module s.

items.name: Infrasonic Relay Upgrade
items.description: The Infrasonic Relay Upgrade grants Prospectors access to Operations locked behind encoded signals. Operations are a variation of traditional Missions that are started in Open Worlds . Upon completing an Operation, Prospectors will be granted Ren ( ) and Exotics / Volatile Exotics for their efforts (rewards vary per Operation and is affected by Open World difficulty). To access Encrypted Signals , Prospectors will need to craft an Encrypted Satellite Upgrade .

items.name: Iron Axe
items.description: The Iron Axe is the 2nd axe you will unlock during your time on Icarus. It is located at the bottom of the Tier 2  tech tree, right after the Anvil Bench .

items.name: Iron Bolt
items.description: The Iron Bolt is ammunition used with a Crossbow . Like arrows and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Iron Crop Plot
items.description: The Iron Crop Plot is a farming plot for growing Seeds that can later be harvested for Plant Resources once fully grown. Unless the Prospector has the Fresh Is Best talent when deploying a seed into the crop plot, the grown Plant Resource will eventually wither if not harvested.

items.name: Iron Cupboard
items.description: The Iron Cupboard comes with 50 inventory slots and can be used to safely store valuable resources. Unlike the Wood Cupboard , it does not require shelter and can be placed outside without risk of taking damage during storms.

items.name: Iron Hammer
items.description: Example: If a Prospector were to upgrade a Wood Wall to a Stone Wall , a Stone Wall must be in the inventory of the Prospector when upgrading.

items.name: Iron Ingot
items.description: Iron Ingot is the refined resource crafted from Iron Ore and is one of the most used materials in the Tier 2  Tech Tree and beyond.

items.name: Iron Javelin
items.description: The Iron Javelin is a variant of the Iron Spear that can only be thrown and is an upgrade over the Tier 1  Javelins.

items.name: Iron Knife
items.description: The Iron Knife is an upgrade in damage and durability from the Bone Knife , the Iron Knife can be used as either a melee weapon or tool. It is also the first knife capable of skinning larger fauna such as the Grizzly Bear and Buffalo . An attachment slot is available, allowing for the application of Tool Attachment Packs at an Alteration Bench / Advanced Alteration Bench .

items.name: Iron Lure
items.description: The Iron Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. Like all Lures , the Iron Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Iron Nail
items.description: Iron Nail are used widely in crafting of items such as Stone Building Pieces , and Iron Tools .

items.name: Iron Ore
items.description: Iron Ore is a Mineral , that allows prospectors to create Tier 2  / Tier 3  Tools and Weapons with both the Anvil Bench and Machining Bench . In addition, iron is widely used in Steel Ingot for crafting Items such as the Steel Pickaxe , and Late-game Deployables like the Fabricator / Electric Furnace .

items.name: Iron Ore
items.description: Iron Ore is a Mineral , that allows prospectors to create Tier 2  / Tier 3  Tools and Weapons with both the Anvil Bench and Machining Bench . In addition, iron is widely used in Steel Ingot for crafting Items such as the Steel Pickaxe , and Late-game Deployables like the Fabricator / Electric Furnace .

items.name: Iron Pickaxe
items.description: The Iron Pickaxe is the 2nd pickaxe prospectors can unlock during their time on Icarus. The blueprint is located at the bottom of the tier 2 tech tree and is considerably better than the previous Stone Pickaxe , granting a 125% boost to mining efficiency. Like all iron tools, the iron pickaxe is repairable at an Anvil Bench .

items.name: Iron Shears
items.description: The Iron Shears are use to shear Sheep to obtain Wool . Can cause 30-40 Melee damage

items.name: Iron Sickle
items.description: Used by 'attacking' plants such as shrubs, Reed Flower , Wheat , etc. Sickles significantly increase the yield of plants when harvesting.

items.description: Iron Sledgehammer is a Tier 2  Sledgehammer made with Iron .

items.name: Iron Spear
items.description: The Iron Spear is the first Spear available to prospectors once they reach Tier 2  and serves as an upgrade to its Tier 1  counterparts. Unlike the Iron Javelin , the Iron Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Iron Throwing Knife
items.description: The Iron Throwing Knife is a variant of the Iron Knife that can be thrown. Unlike the Iron Knife , the Iron Throwing Knife cannot be used to skin fauna. Crafted in batches of five and stacks up to fifty.

items.name: Jaguar Buffalo Animal Bed
items.description: The Jaguar Buffalo Animal Bed is a bed for Mounts and Pets that has a Jaguar and Buffalo theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC . Provides no additional attributes and is a cosmetic change to the Animal Bed .

items.name: Jaguar Rug
items.description: Jaguar Rugs are decorative deployables that can be placed on any ground surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from being for decorative purposes, it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Jaguar Trophy
items.description: Jaguar Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Jaguar Vestige
items.description: Jaguar Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Jaguar Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary . They are also used at the Advanced Textiles Bench / Electric Textiles Bench to make Jaguar Rugs . Decorative purposes aside, both provide a boost to coziness, which increases the duration and effect of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Jarred Honey
items.description: Jarred Honey is a long-lasting Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs.

items.name: Javelin Launcher
items.description: The Javelin Launcher is a Legendary Weapon that is a large Crossbow that fires Javelins for ammunition instead of Bolts . It can be purchased at the Bio-lab .

items.name: Kea Trophy
items.description: Kea Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. items.name: Kea Vestige
items.description: Kea Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Kea Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: KickFall Module
items.description: This module increases resistance to fall damage by 40% when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot, reducing the amount of damage received when falling. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Kick Fall Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit. The resistance increase from each Kick Fall Module will stack and will grant near immunity to fall damage if four are equipped. Falling resistance now caps at 99%.

items.name: Kinetic Rifle
items.description: The Kinetic Rifle is a Legendary Weapon Rifle that can be purchased at the Bio-lab .

items.name: Kitchen Bench
items.description: The Kitchen Bench is a mid/late-game crafting bench that expands on cooking foods and it is also the path for creating more advanced medicines.

items.name: Kitchen Storage Block
items.description: A Kitchen Storage Block made of refined wood and copper nails, use it to store your kitchen essentials. Must be snapped to a Kitchen Bench to be placed. It has 40 inventory slots.

items.name: Kiwi Fruit Farming Packet
items.description: The Kiwi Fruit Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Kiwifruit seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop Plots to grow Kiwifruit .

items.name: Kiwifruit
items.description: Kiwifruit are a fresh fruit that can be eaten raw for a small boost in stamina and resistance to cave sickness or used in additional Food recipes.

items.name: Kiwifruit Jam
items.description: Kiwifruit Jam is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Kiwifruit Sorbet
items.description: Kiwifruit Sorbet is late-game Food that when consumed provides a boost to stamina, experience gained and resistance to cave sickness.

items.name: Komodo Trophy

items.name: Lantern
items.description: Similar to torches, the durability of the Lantern will decrease over time. The Lantern can be repaired (refilled) at a Crafting Bench with 1 Animal Fat . The Lantern will last about 45 minutes when lit before needing repairs. The Lantern allows prospectors to see approximately 10 meters, or 5 standard floor pieces, from their position.

items.name: Large Advanced Aquarium
items.description: The Large Advanced Aquarium allows Prospectors to store and display their favorite catches. Fish stored in the Large Advanced Aquarium will not spoil so long as it is connected to a power network providing at least 1,000 units of Power and a water network providing at least 750 units of Water . The Large Advanced Aquarium will not function if these requirements are not met. The Large Advanced Aquarium can store 12 fish.

items.name: Large Beehive Expansion
items.description: A Beekeeping expansion to the small Beehive to increase inventory slots by 6. Requires the Small Beehive Expansion to be installed first. Added through the Beehive GUI

items.name: Large Food Trough
items.description: The Large Food Trough is a slight upgrade to the Food Trough that allows for multiple creatures to eat from it simultaneously. Large Food Troughs benefit from the Extra Space I / Extra Space II talent.

items.name: Large Water Trough
items.description: The Large Water Trough is an upgrade to the Water Trough that allows multiple creatures to drink from it simultaneously and can be connected to Water using a Water Pipe Tool . The Large Water Trough can only store water and cannot provide water to the rest of the network like Water Barrels or Metal Rain Reservoirs .

items.name: Larkwell "Bulwark" Envirosuit
items.description: The Larkwell "Bulwark" Envirosuit offers more resistance to cold/hot environments with the added bonus of exposure resistance, making it a decent upgrade to the Shengong 'Bihu' Envirosuit and the Shengong 'Dongtian' Envirosuit . Requires Red Exotics .

items.name: Larkwell "Haulier" Envirosuit
items.description: Despite the Larkwell "Haulier" Envirosuit not having a water slot, Prospectors adore this Envirosuit for its larger inventory size and mod-ability. Requires Red Exotics .

The Larkwell Martinez Heated Canteen remains filled between Prospects with the added ability to raise the Prospectors core temperature when consumed, making it a useful upgrade to the Shengong 'Hulu' Canteen .

items.description: The Larkwell Martinez Knife is the hardest-hitting Workshop knife available. Unlike Throwing Knives , the Larkwell Martinez Knife cannot be thrown. There currently are no Workshop throwing knives.

items.description: It is worth noting that this Oxygen Container takes 65 Oxite to fill at a Oxite Dissolver and will last just as long as a Shengong 'Liwei' O2 Tank , but comes with the bonus of increased health regeneration and exposure resistance. Will remain filled between Prospects.

items.name: Larkwell Martinez Pickaxe
items.description: The Larkwell Martinez Pickaxe is the Workshop equivalent of a Platinum Pickaxe , allowing Prospectors to mine higher tier metals ( Aluminium Ore , Platinum Ore , etc) at earlier stages of a Prospect while increasing yield. Similar to the Inaris "Neves" Pickaxe , the Larkwell Martinez Pickaxe reduces the over-encumbrance penalty by 10% when equipped.

items.description: The Larkwell Martinez Tazer Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Unlike bolts and javelins, they cannot be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass.

items.description: Consuming the Larkwell Piercing Bolt Bundle will add 25x Larkwell Martinez Piercing Bolt s to the Prospectors inventory, must be consumed after dropping into a prospect. items.description: Consuming the Larkwell Tazer Arrow Bundle will add 25x Larkwell Martinez Tazer Arrow s to the Prospectors inventory, must be consumed after dropping into a prospect. Consumed arrow bundles cannot be taken back to the space station. Arrow bundles that have not been consumed can be taken back to the space station for use in another prospect.

items.name: Lava Broodling Trophy
items.description: Lava Broodling Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Lava Broodling Vestige
items.description: Lava Broodling Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Lava Broodling Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Lava Survival Inhaler
items.description: The Lava Survival Inhaler is a Medicine that boosts resistance to fire, increases health regeneration and exposure resistance while in a volcanic region. It also reduces water consumption.

items.name: Leather
items.description: Leather is a crucial component of many recipes in Icarus. Having a good stockpile of leather is something every prospector strive for.

items.name: Leather Arms Armor
items.description: Leather armor may not offer much protection when fighting against Icarus' Fauna , but it offers more physical protection and thermal insulation than its Tier 1  counterparts, serving as a decent all-around armor for Tier 2  .
