items.name: Legendary Biomass
items.description: Legendary Biomass is an in-game currency used to craft attachments to upgrade Legendary Weapons at the Bio-lab in orbit.

items.name: Light Automatic Carbine
items.description: The Light Automatic Carbine is a semi-automatic rifle the fires pistol Ammunition such as Armor Piercing , Explosive , Incendiary , Obsidian or regular Pistol Rounds .

items.name: Lightning Rod
items.description: The Lightning Rod is used to redirect lightning strikes from hitting buildings.

items.name: Lightweight Frame Attachment
items.description: Lightweight Frame Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Lily
items.description: A small flower which grows in groups in the Forest Biome on Icarus. They can be harvested most efficiently with the use of Sickles .

items.name: Lily Farming Packet
items.description: The Lily Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Lily seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Localized Terraforming Device
items.description: The Localized Terraforming Device is a Deployable device used to restore trees to the Icarus landscape. It is powered by Electricity and charged up for use with Condensed Enzymes or Synthetic Enzymes . Once charged, the device is triggered and creates a localized storm cloud around the device that once cleared, reveals newly restored trees.

items.name: Longbow
items.description: Using arrows and talents interchangeably with other Bows , the Longbow hits harder than the Wood Bow .

items.name: Lowburn Module
items.description: This module increases fire resistance by 50% when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot, reducing the amount of damage received when on fire. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Lowburn Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit. The resistance increase from each Lowburn Module will stack and will grant near immunity to fire if four are equipped.

items.name: Luxury Chicken Coop
items.description: The Luxury Chicken Coop is a luxury red deployable building that houses Chickens and provides a place for them to lay Eggs . When chickens are within proximity to the coop, their eggs will appear in the coop's inventory instead of being laid on the ground.

items.name: MXC Axe
items.description: The MXC Axe is the Workshop equivalent of a Stone Axe , providing a minor boost to felling damage and yield.
items.crafted_at: Workshop Repair Kitat a poweredRepair Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Workshop Repair Kitat a poweredRepair Bench

items.name: MXC Campfire
items.description: The MXC Campfire is similar to a Campfire , only elevated to decrease the odds of Prospectors accidentally setting themselves on fire.

items.name: MXC Camping Cooker
items.description: The MXC Camping Cooker is a portable version of the Potbelly Stove that is purchased from the Workshop on the Space Station and powered by Hydrazine . It does not require shelter to operate.

items.name: MXC Camping Heater
items.description: The MXC Camping Heater is a portable heat source for use in cold regions such as the Arctic that can be purchased from the Workshop on the Space Station.

items.name: MXC Cot
items.description: The MXC Cot is a portable ready-made Bed that can be purchased from the Workshop or brought down to the planet using Orbital Exchange Interface .

items.name: MXC Crate
items.description: The MXC Crate is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospector's loadout before starting a new prospect. Similar to the Medium Iron Crate , the MXC Crate does not require shelter. Has 25 slots.

items.name: MXC Firewhacker
items.description: The MXC Firewhacker is the Workshop equivalent of a Fire Whacker with increased durability and reduced stamina consumption when used.
items.crafted_at: Workshop Repair Kitat a poweredRepair Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Workshop Repair Kitat a poweredRepair Bench

items.name: MXC Flange Arrow
items.description: The MXC Flange Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass.

items.name: MXC Flange Arrow Bundle
items.description: Consuming the bundle will add 5x MXC Flange Arrow to the Prospectors inventory, must be consumed after dropping into a prospect. Consumed arrow bundles cannot be taken back to the space station. Arrow bundles that have not been consumed can be taken back to the space station for use in another prospect.

items.name: MXC Fuel Canister
items.description: The MXC Fuel Canister is purchased from the Workshop on the Space Station and is used for Biofuel storage. It comes prefilled with fuel when purchased and can be refilled at the Biofuel Composter , Electric Composter or by interacting with a Portable Biofuel Tank deployed on the ground. It can be taken back to Orbit and will remain filled, allowing the Prospector to use it across multiple prospects. It does not fill when returned to station. It holds 10 liters of Biofuel.

items.name: MXC Furnace
items.description: The MXC Furnace is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospector's loadout before starting a new prospect. The MXC Furnace functions like a smaller, more lightweight Stone Furnace , and allows for processing of Iron Ore , Copper Ore , and Steel Bloom into ingots.

items.name: MXC Hammer
items.description: Example: If a Prospector were to upgrade a Wood Wall to a Stone Wall , a Stone Wall must be in the inventory of the Prospector when upgrading.

items.name: MXC Hydrazine Canister
items.description: The MXC Hydrazine Canister is purchased from the Workshop on the Space Station and stores 10,000 litres of hydrazine. The fuel is used in several other MXC devices by placing the canister in the device's inventory slot. The fuel canister cannot be refilled.

items.name: MXC Knife
items.description: The MXC Knife is equivalent to Tier 2  Tech like the Iron Knife , giving Prospectors the ability to skin larger animals, such as Buffalo and Grizzly Bears . Unlike Throwing Knives , the MXC Knife cannot be thrown. There currently are no Workshop throwing knives.

items.name: MXC Spear
items.description: The MXC Spear is the first Spear that can be unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospector's loadout before starting a new prospect.

items.name: MXC Venom Arrow
items.description: The MXC Venom Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass.

items.name: MXC Venom Arrow Bundle
items.description: Consuming the bundle will add 5x MXC Venom Arrow to the Prospectors inventory, must be consumed after dropping into a prospect. Consumed arrow bundles cannot be taken back to the space station. Arrow bundles that have not been consumed can be taken back to the space station for use in another prospect.

items.name: Machete
items.description: The Machete is a Tool that can be used to skin Fauna and harvest Carrots, Wheat, shrubbery, etc. similar to Sickles .

items.name: Machining Bench
items.description: Mid-level crafting system made at the Crafting Bench , the Machining Bench provides access to Tier 3  Blueprints. Prospectors can use it to create Deployables and Firearms .

items.name: Makeshift Landmine
items.description: Prospectors on mounts and mounts themselves do not trigger Landmines. Prospectors, however, can trigger and detonate Landmines with a Yellow/Red indicator. All Landmines can be picked up and disarmed, regardless of their current state. Press and hold X to pickup and disarm Landmines. Note: once triggered, Makeshift Landmines will detonate if a Prospector/animal (excluding mounts) is nearby. They can be picked up and disarmed, but Prospectors run the risk of detonating the Landmine.

items.name: Mammoth Tusk
items.description: Mammoth Tusks are a resource obtained from the Woolly Mammoth / Columbian Mammoth . Requires an Iron Knife or better to skin and harvest the downed beast.

items.name: Marble Kitchen Bench
items.description: The Marble Kitchen Bench is a late-game crafting bench that expands on cooking foods and contains the recipes that can be found in the Cooking Station . Crafts 50% faster than the Kitchen Bench . A water connection is not required for the Marble Kitchen Bench to function.

items.name: Marble Kitchen Storage
items.description: The Marble Kitchen Storage is used to store kitchen essentials and must be snapped to a Kitchen Bench to be placed. The Marble Kitchen Storage has 40 slots.

items.name: Masonry Bench
items.description: The Masonry Bench enables the construction of Stone Building Pieces and Scoria Building Pieces , but only once the prospector researches the blueprint sets for those building pieces.

items.name: Mass Dampener Module
items.description: This module increases movement speed by 10% when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Mass Dampeners may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit. The speed increase from each Mass Dampener Module will stack and will further increase movement speed.

items.name: Material Processor
items.description: The Material Processor serves as a much faster and more advanced Tier 4  version of the Mortar and Pestle that uses electricity to craft items.

items.name: Mature Coconut
items.description: If a prospector lets a Ripe Coconut decay, it will ripen into a mature coconut.

items.name: Meat Pie
items.description: Meat Pie is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Medical Satchel
items.description: The Medical Satchel is a 12 slot satchel dedicated to storing medical supplies such as Bandages , Splints and other Medicine . The satchel takes up one inventory or hotbar slot.

items.name: Medicine Bench
items.description: Allows for the crafting of Medicinal Pastes and Tonics such as Antibiotic Pill , Survival Kits and Health Recovery Elixir to cure and prevent ailments and afflictions. It can also be used to craft Volatile Substance and Fertilizer .

items.name: Medium Interior Wood Crate
items.description: A Medium Interior Wood Crate made of refined wood and copper nails. Similar size to the Medium Wood Crate .

items.name: Medium Iron Crate
items.description: A Medium Iron Crate, use it to safely store valuable resources. Unlike the Medium Wood Crate , it does not require shelter and can be placed outside (immune to storm damage).

items.name: Medium Wood Crate
items.description: Larger than the Small Wood Crate , the Medium Wood Crate also possesses an increased inventory space with 20 slots. Like most other Deployables , this must be under Shelter or it will be destroyed when exposed to Weather events. It is possible to loot the contents if this crate is destroyed, but only for a limited time.

items.name: Medium Wood Hedgehog
items.description: The Medium Wood Hedgehog are sturdy defenses used around your base or while at objectives for protection of equipment.

items.name: Melee Damage Attachment
items.description: Melee Damage Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Tool Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Melon Smoked Giant Steak
items.description: Melon Smoked Giant Steak is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Metal Food Trough
items.description: The Metal Food Trough is a decorative upgrade to the Food Trough and allows multiple creatures to eat from it simultaneously, similar to the Large Food Trough . Metal Food Troughs benefit from the Extra Space I / Extra Space II talent.

items.name: Metal Rain Reservoir
items.description: Fill rate is defined by the total excess water available, the flow rate for the water storage unit, and the number of storage units connected to the network. If there are multiple water storage units connected to a single network, the total excess is divided amongst them all - if they are able to be filled. Ex: if a network is producing 2,500 excess water and there are 2 Metal Rain Reservoirs that can be filled, the fill rate for each will be 1,000.

items.name: Metal Water Trough
items.description: The Metal Water Trough is a decorative upgrade to the Water Trough that allows multiple creatures to drink from it simultaneously and can be connected to Water using a Water Pipe Tool , similar to the Large Water Trough . The Metal Water Trough can only store water and cannot provide water to the rest of the network like Water Barrels or Metal Rain Reservoirs .

items.name: Miasmic Arrow
items.description: The Miasmic Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow , requiring Distilled Miasmic Coating introduced on the Prometheus map.

items.name: Miasmic Axe
items.description: Miasmic Axe is a Tier 4  Axe made with Distilled Miasmic Coating derived from Crystallized Miasma found in the Swamps on Prometheus . Due to the materials required, crafting the item requires the New Frontiers DLC.

items.name: Miasmic Javelin
items.description: The Miasmic Javelin is a variant of the Miasmic Spear that can only be thrown. Deals poison damage on hit and has a 15% chance to apply a unique debuff to targets while dealing periodic poison damage. Excels when used against Fauna that have a weakness to poison. . When the Miasma modifier does proc, periodic poison damage is dealt to the target over the span of 10 seconds. Fauna with:

items.name: Miasmic Knife
items.description: Miasmic Knife is a Tier 4  Knife made with Distilled Miasmic Coating derived from Crystallized Miasma found in the Swamps on Prometheus . Due to the materials required, crafting the item requires the New Frontiers DLC.

items.name: Miasmic Pickaxe
items.description: Miasmic Pickaxe is a Tier 4  Pickaxe made with Distilled Miasmic Coating derived from Crystallized Miasma found in the Swamps on Prometheus . Due to the materials required, crafting the item requires the New Frontiers DLC.

items.name: Miasmic Sickle
items.description: Miasmic Sickle is a Tier 4  Sickle made with Distilled Miasmic Coating derived from Crystallized Miasma found in the Swamps on Prometheus . Due to the materials required, crafting the item requires the New Frontiers DLC.

items.name: Miasmic Sledgehammer
items.description: Miasmic Sledgehammer is a Tier 4  Sledgehammer made with Distilled Miasmic Coating derived from Crystallized Miasma found in the Swamps on Prometheus . Due to the materials required, crafting the item requires the New Frontiers DLC.

items.name: Miasmic Spear
items.description: Element damage does not scale with Spear talents. Unlike the Miasmic Javelin , the Miasmic Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Miasmic Throwing Knife
items.description: The Miasmic Throwing Knife is a variant of the Miasmic Knife that can only be thrown and is unlocked upon researching the Miasmic Knife . Cannot be used to skin Fauna - crafted in batches of five and stacks up to fifty.

items.name: MicroMeal
items.description: Micro Meal is a Food with a unique Status Effect : 'Emergency Rations'. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger . It is a one time use emergency ration to stave off starvation.

items.name: Migrating Sands
items.description: INVESTIGATE AN ANOMALY IN THE DESERT

items.name: Milk
items.description: Milk is a late-game resource obtained from mature Cows raised from juvenile Calves purchased from the orbital Workshop . Calves must be raised to adulthood using similar mechanics to taming Mounts including feeding, watering and providing a bed for the animal to sleep on.

items.name: Milk Pail
items.description: Milk Pail is a container for liquid Milk . It holds 5 litres of Milk and unlike the Glass Milk Bottle , the Milk will spoil over time. Once the Milk has spoiled, the Milk Pail will empty and be available for reuse.

items.name: Miner's Module
items.description: This module is the Workshop equivalent of the Supplemental Respiration Attachment , with the added damage bonus to Caveworms . It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Miner's Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit and will further increase benefits received from the modules.

items.name: Mining Armature
items.description: The Mining Armature is an electro-mechanical gauntlet that serves as a Pickaxe for mining or for use in melee combat where it can inflict considerable damage to armored targets. It can be purchased in the Bio-lab and upgraded with various attachments.
items.crafted_at: Workshop Repair Kitat a poweredRepair Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Workshop Repair Kitat a poweredRepair Bench

items.name: Mixed Berries
items.description: Mixed Berries is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Moa Trophy
items.description: Moa Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Moa Vestige
items.description: Moa Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Moa Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Mortar and Pestle
items.description: The Mortar and Pestle is an early-game crafting station that allows prospectors to craft several useful Resources and precursor materials, including but not limited to: Steel Bloom , Epoxy , Tree Sap , Carbon Paste , Organic Resin , and Gunpowder .

items.name: Mountaineering Animal Feed
items.description: Mountaineering Animal Feed is an Animal Feed for Pets or Mounts with a unique Status Effect . Can be fed to mounts to satisfy Hunger . Mountaineering Animal Feed decays in 10,800 seconds, but that decay can be slowed down by storing Mountaineering Animal Feed inside an Ice Box or Refrigerator .

items.name: Mushroom
items.description: Mushrooms can only be harvested in caves in the Arctic biomes, and are harvested by hand. Caves with Mushrooms are almost exclusively caves with pit traps, this can make them easier to find on interactive maps. Also the Mushroom Farming Packet can be purchased in the Workshop . Consuming this item will yield 5 Mushrooms.

items.name: Mushroom Farming Packet
items.description: The Mushroom Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Mushroom seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Mushroom Omelette
items.description: Mushroom Omelette is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Mushroom Soup
items.description: Mushroom Soup is a Food that satisfies Hunger . It provides the unique Status Effect , Mushroom Soup , which increases maximum Health and improves Stamina regeneration.

items.name: NOREX Boss Tracker Upgrade
items.description: The NOREX Boss Tracker Upgrade is an upgrade for the CONT4CT Device deployed in an Open World map that visually upgrades the screens and provides a Bosses tab that provides information on the currently active world bosses.

items.name: Narrow Barrel Attachment
items.description: Narrow Barrel Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Natural Rustic Sign
items.description: A Natural Rustic Sign made of wood.

items.name: Needler Trophy
items.description: Needler Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Needler Vestige
items.description: Needler Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Needler Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Noise Suppression Attachment
items.description: Noise Suppression Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Armor Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Noxious Crust
items.description: Noxious Crust is a by-product of mining using Miasmic Tools that can be taken to an Organic Residue Cleanser or Biofuel Bio-Cleaner to be turned into various Minerals .

items.name: Noxious Logging Inhaler
items.description: The Noxious Logging Inhaler is a Medicine that allows Infected Bark to be harvested when chopping trees and also boosts felling damage and resistance to collision damage from falling trees.

items.name: Noxious Mining Inhaler
items.description: The Noxious Mining Inhaler is a Medicine whose effects allow Noxious Crust to be harvested when mining and add a small boost to mining yield and radius.

items.name: Nutrition Attachment
items.description: The Nutrition Attachment is an armor alteration that adds an extra stomach slot for Food and increases the duration of food Status Effects .

items.name: Obsidian
items.description: Glass formed from the belly of the earth, as chunks of solid lava. Obsidian is found in the Volcanic Biome in Icarus. In order to collect it, one needs to first break it apart using a Sledgehammer .

items.name: Obsidian Arm Armor
items.description: Obsidian Armor is a sidegrade of Composite Armor , providing slightly more physical resistance and a substantial bonus to heat resistance.

items.name: Obsidian Arrow
items.description: The Obsidian Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Obsidian Bolt
items.description: The Obsidian Bolt is ammunition used with a Crossbow . Like arrows and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Obsidian Chest Armor
items.description: Obsidian Armor is a sidegrade of Composite Armor , providing slightly more physical resistance and a substantial bonus to heat resistance.

items.name: Obsidian Feet Armor
items.description: Obsidian Armor is a sidegrade of Composite Armor , providing slightly more physical resistance and a substantial bonus to heat resistance.

items.name: Obsidian Head Armor
items.description: Obsidian Armor is a sidegrade of Composite Armor , providing slightly more physical resistance and a substantial bonus to heat resistance.

items.name: Obsidian Javelin
items.description: The Obsidian Javelin is a variant of the Obsidian Spear that can only be thrown. Deals fire damage on hit and has a 15% chance to apply a unique debuff to targets while also setting them ablaze. Excels when used against Fauna that have a weakness to fire. . When the Burning modifier does proc, periodic fire damage is dealt to the target over the span of 10 seconds. Fauna with:

items.name: Obsidian Leg Armor
items.description: Obsidian Armor is a sidegrade of Composite Armor , providing slightly more physical resistance and a substantial bonus to heat resistance.

items.name: Obsidian Sledgehammer
items.description: Obsidian Sledgehammer is a Tier 2  Sledgehammer made with Shaped Obsidian . Due to the materials required, crafting the item requires the New Frontiers DLC.

items.name: Obsidian Spear
items.description: Element damage does not scale with Spear talents. Unlike the Obsidian Javelin , the Obsidian Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Obsidian Throwing Knife
items.description: The Obsidian Throwing Knife is a variant of the Obsidian Knife that can only be thrown and is unlocked upon researching the Obsidian Knife . Cannot be used to skin Fauna - crafted in batches of five and stacks up to fifty.

items.name: Omni Animal Feed
items.description: Omni Animal Feed is an Animal Feed for Pets or Mounts with a unique Status Effect . Can be fed to mounts to satisfy Hunger . Omni Animal Feed decays in 10,800 seconds, but that decay can be slowed down by storing Omni Animal Feed inside an Ice Box or Refrigerator .

items.name: Omnidirectional Worklamp
items.description: The Omnidirectional Worklamp provides lighting for a Prospector's base. Requires 150 units of power to function.

items.name: One-Shot Pistol
items.description: The One-Shot Pistol is an inexpensive early-game Tier 2  handgun that holds one bullet.

items.name: Orbital Exchange Interface
items.description: The Orbital Exchange Interface is required to send Exotics / Stabilized Exotics back to Orbit and to receive payment for them. Volatile Raw Exotics must be cleaned at a Organic Residue Cleanser before they can be sent up. Must be placed outdoors.

items.name: Organic Residue Cleanser
items.description: The Organic Residue Cleanser is a Tier 4  deployable cleaning device used to clean and process Volatile Raw Exotics , frozen and infected materials and organic materials collected from world bosess.

items.name: Organic Resin
items.description: Organic Resin is used in crafting of items such as Electronics , and Composite Paste , making it a critical component in Tier 4  crafting.

items.name: Ornate Water Trough
items.description: The Ornate Water Trough is a decorative upgrade to the Water Trough that allows multiple creatures to drink from it simultaneously and can be connected to Water using a Water Pipe Tool , similar to the Large Water Trough . The Ornate Water Trough can only store water and cannot provide water to the rest of the network like Water Barrels or Metal Rain Reservoirs .

items.name: Oxidizer
items.description: Early game , unlocking this provides for an incredible boost in efficiency vs the initial need to consume raw Oxite to maintain oxygen supply. Once built and placed, the Oxidizer is used by adding Oxite (10 max) and once the leather balloon is filled, oxygen can be consumed by activating the balloon. The balloon holds up to 1.00L (1000u) of breathable oxygen.

items.name: Oxite
items.description: Oxite is an one of the most precious Minerals found on the surface of Icarus. Prospectors require a steady supply of Oxygen to survive, and Oxite is a solidified mix of water and oxygen.

items.name: Oxite Cluster Lamp
items.description: The Oxite Cluster Lamp is a simple low output lamp that does not require fuel to operate but does require water to craft.
items.crafted_at: Crafted AtMasonry BenchAdvanced Masonry BenchElectric Masonry Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Crafted AtMasonry BenchAdvanced Masonry BenchElectric Masonry Bench

items.name: Oxite Dissolver
items.description: More efficient than the Oxidizer , this is used in tandem with Oxygen Containers placed into the dissolver. The front slots of the deployable only accept Oxygen Containers and will automatically fill said containers from Oxite placed into the machine when supplied with Sulfur . A stack of sulfur will last sixteen minutes and forty seconds, producing 0.1 Liters of Oxygen every two seconds.

items.name: Oxite Geode Lamp
items.description: The Oxite Geode Lamp is a simple low output lamp that does not require fuel to operate but does require water to craft.
items.crafted_at: Crafted AtMasonry BenchAdvanced Masonry BenchElectric Masonry Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Crafted AtMasonry BenchAdvanced Masonry BenchElectric Masonry Bench

items.name: Oxite Monolith Lamp
items.description: The Oxite Monolith Lamp is a simple low output lamp that does not require fuel to operate but does require water to craft.
items.crafted_at: Crafted AtMasonry BenchAdvanced Masonry BenchElectric Masonry Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Crafted AtMasonry BenchAdvanced Masonry BenchElectric Masonry Bench

items.name: Oxygel
items.description: Oxygel is a Consumable that provides Oxygen when consumed. It is a one time use emergency ration of Oxygen.

items.name: Oxygen
items.description: Oxygen is one of the three survival meters that must be maintained by prospectors while attempting a Prospect on Icarus.

items.name: Oxygen Bladder
items.description: Oxygen Bladder is filled at the Oxite Dissolver , and is equipped in an Envirosuit oxygen slot enabling automatic Oxygen replenishment. It holds 1000 oxygen units.

items.name: Oxygen Buff Paste
items.description: In-game description: A natural concoction that increases available oxygen. In-game flavor text: Your parents are a long way from here. What you do with your body is your business.

items.name: Oxygen Consumption Paste
items.description: In-game description: A natural beta blocker. In-game flavor text: This preparation reduces the heart rate, dropping oxygen consumption temporarily.

items.name: Oxygen Restoration Paste
items.description: In-game description: An organic co-factor that rapidly restores oxygen. In-game flavor text: Helper molecule

items.name: Oxygen Tank
items.description: The Oxygen Tank is filled at the Oxite Dissolver and Metal Oxite Dissolver and is equipped in an Envirosuit oxygen slot enabling automatic Oxygen replenishment. It holds 5000 oxygen units, 5 times as much as a Oxygen Bladder ; great for long trips across Icarus.

items.name: Paints
items.description: Paints are used make several different Paintings that can be hung on various Frames .

items.name: Pastry
items.description: Pastry is a component in making food, such as Crumbed Saltwater Fillet and Meat Pie .

items.name: Patcher I Module
items.description: This module increases the number of available inventory slots by 2 when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Patcher I Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit.

items.name: Patcher II Module
items.description: This module increases the number of available inventory slots by 5 when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Patcher II Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit.

items.name: Pavlova
items.description: Pavlova is late-game Food that when consumed provides a considerable boost to health, stamina, speed, resistance to cave sickness and a chance to mine additional stone.

items.name: Pheromone Module
items.description: This module increases the movement speed and maximum stamina of mounts near the user. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Pheromone Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit and will further increase the benefit received from the equipped modules.

items.name: Pickled Avocado
items.description: Pickled Avocado is a Food that satisfies Hunger . It provides the unique Status Effect , Pickled Avocado , which increases maximum Stamina , reduces food consumption, and improves shared experience gain. Pickled Avocado does not decay and is therefore useful for long-term storage.

items.name: Pickled Carrot
items.description: Pickled Carrot is a Food that satisfies Hunger . It provides the unique Status Effect , Pickled Carrot , which improves Projectile Damage and shared experience gain. Pickled Carrot does not decay and is therefore useful for long-term storage.

items.name: Pickled Eggs
items.description: Pickled Eggs is a Food that satisfies Hunger . It provides the unique Status Effect , Pickled Eggs , which increases maximum Stamina , increases the amount of Stone found while mining, and improves shared experience gain. Pickled Eggs does not decay and is therefore useful for long-term storage.

items.name: Pickled Freshwater Fillet
items.description: Pickled Freshwater Fillet is a Food that satisfies Hunger . It provides the unique Status Effect , Pickled Freshwater Fillet , which increases maximum Health , improves Stamina and Health regeneration, and improves shared experience gain. Pickled Freshwater Fillet does not decay and is therefore useful for long-term storage.

items.name: Pickled Tomato
items.description: Pickled Tomato is a Food that satisfies Hunger . It provides the unique Status Effect , Pickled Tomato , which increases maximum Stamina , improves Health regeneration, and improves shared experience gain. Pickled Tomato does not decay and is therefore useful for long-term storage.

items.name: Pistol
items.description: The Pistol is a single-shot 9mm handgun and is a decent upgrade in firepower available to prospectors. It fires 35 rounds of Pistol Ammunition before breaking, so bring a Machining Bench / Repair Bench for long trips.

items.name: Plain Jerky
items.description: Plain Jerky is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Plating Attachment
items.description: Plating Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Armor Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Platinum Attachment
items.description: Platinum Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Tool Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Platinum Axe
items.description: The Platinum Axe is a mid/late-game Axe that can be crafted while on the surface of Icarus.

items.name: Platinum Bolt
items.description: The Platinum Bolt is ammunition used with a Crossbow . Like arrows and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Platinum Crossbow
items.description: The Platinum Crossbow is a mid/late game weapon that can penetrate hardened points with a chance to slow targets but has a slower fire rate than Bows .

items.name: Platinum Hammer
items.description: Example: If a Prospector were to upgrade a Wood Wall to a Stone Wall , a Stone Wall must be in the inventory of the Prospector when upgrading.

items.name: Platinum Ingot
items.description: Platinum Ingot is the refined resource crafted from Platinum Ore .

items.name: Platinum Javelin
items.description: The Platinum Javelin is a variant of the Platinum Spear that can only be thrown; a substantial upgrade to the Tier 2  Javelins.

items.name: Platinum Knife
items.description: The Platinum Knife is an upgrade in damage and durability from the Steel Knife , the Platinum Knife can be used as either a melee weapon or tool. Unlike the Platinum Throwing Knife , the Platinum Knife cannot be thrown.

items.name: Platinum Lightning Rod
items.description: The Platinum Lightning Rod absorbs lightning strikes from Weather Events and optionally captures the energy and directs it to a connected Electricity network.

items.name: Platinum Ore
items.description: Platinum Ore is a mid-game Mineral Resource , and can be utilized by prospectors after they reach level 20 and unlock Tier 3  in the Tech Tree . Platinum is required for a number of upgraded Tools and Weapons , including the Platinum Spear and Platinum Sickle .

items.name: Platinum Pickaxe
items.description: The Platinum Pickaxe is a mid/late-game Pickaxe that can be crafted while on the surface of Icarus.

items.name: Platinum Sheath
items.description: Platinum Sheath is used in a variety of high-end resources and components and is crafted in batches of 4.

items.name: Platinum Shield
items.description: The Platinum Shield is crafted at the Forge or Foundry with the following resources:

items.name: Platinum Shovel
items.description: The Platinum Shovel is an upgrade to the Shovel , offering increased yield when digging and higher tool durability. Like its predecessor, it can be used to create Dirt Mounds (right-click), harvest Ice / Dirt / Sand (left-click), or remove ash/snow buildup on structures in the Arctic / Volcanic biomes on Icarus.

items.name: Platinum Sickle
items.description: Used by 'attacking' plants such as shrubs, Reed Flower , Wheat , etc. Sickles significantly increase the yield of plants when harvesting.

items.name: Platinum Spear
items.description: The Platinum Spear is the first Spear available to prospectors once they reach Tier 3  and serves as an, albeit expensive, upgrade to its Tier 2  counterparts. Unlike the Platinum Javelin , the Platinum Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Platinum Throwing Knife
items.description: The Platinum Throwing Knife is a variant of the Platinum Knife that can be thrown. Unlike the Platinum Knife , the Platinum Throwing Knife cannot be used to skin fauna. Crafted in batches of five and stacks up to fifty.

items.name: Platinum Weave
items.description: Platinum Weave is a Tier 3  crafted resource used for various items including armor, animal items, rugs, fishing lures and furniture.
items.crafted_at: Advanced Textiles Bench Electric Textiles Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Advanced Textiles Bench Electric Textiles Bench

items.name: Player Tracker Module
items.description: When this module is equipped in an Envirosuit module slot it allows a prospector to see other prospectors on the map. It can be researched and created on the Space Station in the Workshop .

items.name: Plumbed Sink
items.description: The Plumbed Sink is bench that can be connected to other Marble Appliances and, when connected to active water connection, provides a short buff when interacted with. The Buff increases crafting speed, movement speed, health regeneration, and reduced water and food consumption. 250 units of Water is required for the Plumbed Sink to function.

items.name: Pockets Attachment
items.description: Pockets Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Armor Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Poison Arrow
items.description: The Poison Arrow is a damage over time upgrade to the Stone Arrow , which is helpful when in a 'fire and flee' situation. DOT effect stacks.

items.name: Poison Paste
items.description: Poison Paste is used for making a variety of items, such as medicines like Anti-Poison Pill or ammo like Poison Arrow .

items.name: Poison Sack
items.description: Poison Sacks are a resource that drops from Caveworms . Only after completing Unearthed: Research can these sacks and Caveworm Scales be used to craft new weaponry at a Crafting Bench .

items.name: Poison Sack Lure
items.description: The Poison Sack Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. Like all Lures , the Poison Sack Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Poisoned Animal Bait
items.description: Poisoned Animal Bait is used to lure random predators when left in an open area, poisoning Fauna who choose to consume it. The blueprint is unlocked account-wide after completing the prospect Wet Work: Extermination . Stacks up to 5.

items.name: Polar Bear Rug
items.description: Polar Bear Rugs are decorative deployables that can be placed on any ground surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from being for decorative purposes, it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .
items.crafted_at: Advanced Textiles Bench Electric Textiles Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Advanced Textiles Bench Electric Textiles Bench

items.name: Polar Bear Trophy
items.description: Polar Bear Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Polar Bear Vestige
items.description: Polar Bear Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Polar Bear Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary . They are also used at the Advanced Textiles Bench / Electric Textiles Bench to make Polar Bear Rugs . Decorative purposes aside, both provide a boost to coziness, which increases the duration and effect of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Portable Beacon
items.description: When deployed, the Portable Beacon will display a map marker that is visible on the map and compass, which is helpful for marking locations of caves/bases/predator spawns/or anything else a Prospector wishes to mark. When interacting with the Portable Beacon, Prospectors can choose from a list of available icons and colors to customize the icon displayed. Must be placed outdoors.

items.name: Portable Biofuel Generator
items.description: The Portable Biofuel Generator generates Electricity when supplied with biofuel from a Biofuel Can .

items.name: Portable Biofuel Tank
items.description: Portable Biofuel Tank is used for Biofuel storage. It is either filled at the Biofuel Composter or Electric Composter .

items.name: Portable Icebox Backpack
items.description: A handy backpack to prevent your food from spoiling on long journeys. Will run for 1 hour on a full charge. Can be recharged at a Charging Station .

items.name: Portable Water Tank
items.description: Portable Water Tank is a deployable that can be connected to a water network once placed to store 150,000 of water and can output 1,000 water per second to keep the network operational. It is the equivalent to a Water Barrel with having half of the storage, but it can be picked up into your character's Backpack/Equipment Slot (G).

items.name: Potato
items.description: A plant which grows in the Swamp and Tundra Biomes on Prometheus. They can be harvested most efficiently with the use of Sickles .

items.name: Potato Bread
items.description: Potato Bread is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Potato Farming Packet
items.description: The Potato Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Potato seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Potato and Carrot Fries
items.description: Potato and Carrot Fries is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Potbelly Stove
items.description: The Potbelly Stove is an early- to mid-game cooking bench that provides a more efficient way to cook raw foods than the Campfire . The Potbelly Stove introduces new, multi-ingredient recipes with unique status effects. It is also an exceptional source of heat.

items.name: Powered Creature Deterrent
items.description: While useful for protecting Prospectors from predators, the Powered Creature Deterrent also prevents the spawning of Fauna so be aware that deer, pronghorns, rabbits, chamois, or other animals will not spawn within the indicated radius.

items.name: Prime Meat Attachment
items.description: Prime Meat Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Tool Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Prometheus
items.description: Prometheus General information Location System: Proxima Centauri Star: Wolf 1061 Gas giant: Minos Moon: Wolf 1061ca / Icarus Difficulty Available by Purchasing New Frontiers Expansion

items.name: Pronghorn Trophy
items.description: Pronghorn Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Pronghorn Vestige
items.description: Pronghorn Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Pronghorn Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Prospector Field Guide
items.description: The Prospector Field Guide is an in-game tool ( default keybind: J) designed to provide players with comprehensive information on bestiaries, fishing records, and craftable items. This guide will be expanded to include detailed entries for every item, offering valuable insights to improve the crafting experience.

items.name: Protection Module
items.description: This module increases the user's resistance to wounds received from aggressive Fauna, specifically the Basic Wound + Deep Wound debuff. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Protection Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit and will grant near immunity to Basic/Deep wounds if four are equipped.

items.name: Prototype Thumper
items.description: The more ore available, the bigger the impact on the surrounding environment, so expect more opposition when taking on lucrative deposits in densely populated areas.

items.name: Prototype Trail Beacon
items.description: The Prototype Trail Beacon is a small portable self-powered beacon that is deployed with the Prototype Trail Beacon Tool to form a breadcrumb trail in the uncharted areas of the Null Sector Region on Prometheus .

items.name: Prototype Trail Beacon Tool
items.description: The Prototype Trail Beacon Tool is a handheld device used to place a breadcrumb trail of Prototype Trail Beacons when exploring the Null Sector Region on the Prometheus map.

items.name: Pumpkin
items.description: Pumpkin are a common form of Plantlife found in the Forest and Riverlands locations on Icarus. When consumed by prospectors, they replenish Hunger .

items.name: Pumpkin Bread
items.description: Pumpkin Bread is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Pumpkin Farming Packet
items.description: The Pumpkin Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Pumpkin seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Pygmy Lop Trophy
items.description: Pygmy Lop Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Pygmy Lop Vestige
items.description: Pygmy Lop Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Pygmy Lop Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Rabbit Trophy
items.description: Rabbit Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Rabbit Vestige
items.description: Rabbit Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Rabbit Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Racing Saddle
items.description: The Racing Saddle is a saddle for Mounts that has a racing theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC and is a cosmetic change to the Basic Riding Saddle that provides no additional attributes.

items.name: Rain Reservoir
items.description: Rain Reservoirs can be crafted from the Crafting Bench with the following resources once the appropriate blueprint point has been spent:

items.name: Ranching Station
items.description: The Ranching Station allows the prospector to craft various Tier 2  equipment to use and maintain mounts and pets. This includes several Food Troughs / Water Troughs , Animal Beds , Saddles / Carts , Animal Feed , and other Ranching Deployables . Must be placed outside.

items.name: Ranged Attachment Pack
items.description: Ranged Attachment Pack is a Tier 3  Tech needed for the Alteration Bench that allows Prospectors to alter their ranged weapons with Attachment Packs .

items.name: Raw Bacon
items.description: Raw meat can be obtained by skinning Wild Boar with a Knife . While eating raw food will replenish Health there is a possibility of negative Status Effects when doing so. It is better to Cook before eating.

items.name: Raw Chicken
items.description: Raw Chicken can be obtained from the carcass of a once cryogenically frozen Chicken that can be purchased from the Workshop .

items.name: Raw Copper Lamp
items.description: The Raw Copper Lamp is a simple low output lamp that does not require fuel to operate but does require water to craft.

items.name: Raw Fatty T-Bone
items.description: Raw Fatty T-Bone can be obtained by Skinning bears with a Knife .

items.name: Raw Gamey Meat
items.description: Raw Gamey Meat can be obtained by Skinning animals with a Knife . Eating Raw Gamey Meat will replenish Health there is a possibility of negative Status Effects when doing so. It is better to Cook first before eating.

items.name: Raw Giant Steak
items.description: Raw Giant Steak can be obtained by Skinning animals with a Knife . Eating Raw Giant Steak will replenish Health there is a possibility of negative Status Effects when doing so. It is better to Cook first before eating.

items.name: Raw Gold Lamp
items.description: The Raw Gold Lamp is a simple low output lamp that does not require fuel to operate but does require water to craft.

items.name: Raw Meat
items.description: Raw meat can be obtained by skinning animals with a Knife . While eating raw meat will replenish Health there is a possibility of negative Status Effects when doing so. It is better to Cook before eating.

items.name: Raw Oxite Lamp
items.description: The Raw Oxite Lamp is a simple low output lamp that does not require fuel to operate but does require water to craft.

items.name: Raw Soft Meat
items.description: Raw Soft Meat can be obtained by Skinning animals with a Knife . Eating Raw Soft Meat will replenish Health there is a possibility of negative Status Effects when doing so. It is better to Cook first before eating.

items.name: Raw Stringy Meat
items.description: Raw Stringy Meat can be obtained by Skinning animals with a Knife . Eating Raw Stringy Meat will replenish Health there is a possibility of negative Status Effects when doing so. It is better to Cook first before eating.

items.name: Raw White Meat
items.description: Eating Raw White Meat will replenish Health there is a possibility of negative Status Effects when doing so. It is better to Cook first before eating.

items.name: Reaping Attachment
items.description: Reaping Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Tool Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Recovery Attachment
items.description: The Recovery Attachment is an armor alteration that reduces the duration of the effects of parasites, poison, bacterial afflications and physical trauma.

items.name: Recurve Bow
items.description: The pinnacle of Instinctive Archery, made of Steel and Aluminium , the Recurve Bow hits harder than the Longbow .

items.name: Redback Trophy
items.description: Redback Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Redback Vestige
items.description: Redback Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Redback Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Reed Farming Packet
items.description: The Reed Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Reed seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Reed Flower
items.description: Reed flowers can be found alongside water in the Forest Biome on Icarus. They can be harvested most efficiently with a Sickle .

items.name: Reed Flower Lure
items.description: The Reed Flower Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. The capture zone size increase widens the size of the capture area during the fishing minigame, increasing the success chance of catching a fish. Like all Lures , the Reed Flower Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Refined Gold
items.description: Refined Gold is the refined resource crafted from Gold Ore .

items.name: Refined Wood
items.description: Refined Wood is used for the construction of Interior Wood Buildings , Refined Wood Deployables, and various Tools.

items.name: Refined Wood Fishing Rod
items.description: One approach to catching fish is by using a Fishing Rod. Though a lure is not required, attaching one can increase the quality, length, and weight of the caught fish. Additionally, certain lures can increase the odds of catching fish of a certain rarity or increase the size of the capture area. For a list of available lures, view this page .

items.name: Refined Wood Lure
items.description: The Refined Wood Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. The capture zone size increase widens the size of the capture area during the fishing minigame, increasing the success chance of catching a fish. Like all Lures , the Refined Wood Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Refrigerator
items.description: The Refrigerator will slow the decay of food placed inside, increasing the time until food spoils by 8x when powered. Requires 500 units of power to function. Has 24 slots.

items.name: Regenerative Combat Inhaler
items.description: The Regenerative Combat Inhaler is a Medicine that boosts health regeneration and resistance to basic and deep wounds.

items.name: Repair Bench
items.description: The Repair Bench has the ability to repair all items youre wearing or have placed on the bench with a single click, regardless of where they were crafted. When combined with a power connection (1,500 electricity ) it can also repair Tier 4  and Orbital Workshop items. To repair Orbital Workshop Items, a Workshop Repair Kit is required.

items.name: Repair Speed Attachment
items.description: Repair Speed Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Tool Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Resources
items.description: Prospectors face a host of challenges when they drop onto Icarus. They must maintain an adequate supply of Oxygen , Water and Food , craft Shelter from the planets storms, and survive encounters with the Fauna . Prospectors will need to rely on a wide range of resources: some they will find in the wild, and others they will make themselves. How prospectors master the use of these resources will determine their overall success during their limited time on Icarus.

items.name: Rhubarb
items.description: Rhubarb is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Rhubarb Farming Packet
items.description: The Rhubarb Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Rhubarb seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Rhubarb Stew
items.description: Rhubarb Stew is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Ripe Coconut
items.description: If a Prospector lets a Young Coconut decay, it will ripen into a ripe coconut. Let a ripe coconut decay, and it will ripen again into a Mature Coconut .

items.name: Roast Chicken
items.description: Roast Chicken is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Roast Squash
items.description: Roast Squash is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Roast Vegetables

items.name: Roat Trophy
items.description: Roat Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Roat Vestige
items.description: Roat Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Roat Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.description: Intermediate crafting item used as a component of many recipes.

items.name: Rustic 2-Seater Couch

items.name: Rustic 3-Seater Couch

items.name: Rustic Armchair
items.description: The Rustic Armchair seats one prospector

items.name: Rustic Bed
items.description: The Rustic Bed allows prospectors to sleep provided it is sufficiently sheltered and it is night time in-game. In a multiplayer game, all prospectors must sleep at the same time to pass the night. Prospectors can set their respawn location to a bed, however if this bed is deconstructed or destroyed, the prospector's spawn location will reset back to the drop-pod.

items.name: Rustic Bookshelf
items.description: The Rustic Bookshelf allows prospectors to store 10 items

items.name: Rustic Cabinet
items.description: The Rustic Cabinet allows prospectors to store 10 items

items.name: Rustic Candles
items.description: Four types of Rustic Candles can be deployed by holding the candle and selecting R for the rotary menu. Two recipes create the candles using either Animal Fat or Beeswax . Holding R when viewing the candle will bring up the fuel container which will either be Animal Fat or Beeswax.

items.name: Rustic Chicken Coop
items.description: The Rustic Chicken Coop is a deployable building that houses Chickens and provides a place for them to lay Eggs . When chickens are within proximity to the coop, their eggs will appear in the coop's inventory instead of being laid on the ground.

items.name: Rustic Coffee Table
items.description: The Rustic Coffee Table allows prospectors to store 10 items

items.name: Rustic Dining Chair
items.description: The Rustic Dining Chair a rustic chair that seats one prospector.

items.name: Rustic Dresser
items.description: The Rustic Dresser allows prospectors to store 10 items

items.name: Rustic Food Trough
items.description: The Rustic Food Trough is a decorative upgrade to the Food Trough and allows multiple creatures to eat from it simultaneously, similar to the Large Food Trough . Rustic Food Troughs benefit from the Extra Space I / Extra Space II talent.

items.name: Rustic Icarus Statue
items.description: The Rustic Icarus Statue is a decorative statue

items.name: Rustic Large Table
items.description: The Rustic Large Table is a simple long wooden table.

items.name: Rustic Narrow Wardrobe
items.description: The Rustic Narrow Wardrobe smaller wardrobe but still has 10 slot capacity and two variations selectable by holding R.

items.name: Rustic Nightstand
items.description: The Rustic Nightstand is available in 5 varieties when holding item selet R for the variations. The Rustic Nightstand allows prospectors to store 5 items.

items.name: Rustic Pot
items.description: The Rustic Pot has two variations that can be selected by holding item and holding R. The item is decorative only and cannot store items

items.name: Rusty Shotgun
items.description: A crude version of the Shotgun that fires slower and holds fewer rounds. It uses any type of Shotgun Ammunition .

items.name: Salt
items.description: Salt is a Mineral and can be found in the wilderness in similar areas to Sulfur , Oxite and Silica .

items.name: Salting Station
items.description: The Salting Station is an early-game cooking bench that provides a way to for Prospectors to preserve foods using Salt . Once a food is salted, it will receive the Preserved modifier, increasing spoil time by 100%. Salting a food item will reset its spoil timer, even if the item is nearly spoiled. This technique can be used to further extend the spoilage.

items.name: Saltwater Fillet Sashimi
items.description: Saltwater Fillet Sashimi is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Saltwater Fish Fillet
items.description: Saltwater Fish Fillet is is the result of filleting a Saltwater Fish at a Basic Fishing Bench . While eating Saltwater Fish Fillet will replenish a small amount of Hunger , there is a possibility of negative Status Effects when doing so. It is better to Cook before eating.

items.name: Sand
items.description: Sand is a Resource found on the surface of Icarus in Desert biomes. Sand is collected with a Shovel and can be used to make Glass in a Concrete Furnace / Electric Furnace .

items.name: Sandworm
items.description: A monstrous beast that lives beneath the sand on Olympus and Styx.

items.name: Sandworm Arms Armor
items.description: Sandworm Arms Armor is made from the scales dropped from a Sandworm . Provides exceptional heat protection with the added bonus of poison resistance when worn with a full set of Sandworm Armor .

items.name: Seared Mushroom
items.description: Seared Mushroom is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Seed Animal Feed
items.description: Seed Animal Feed is a Animal Feed for Pets or Mounts with a unique Status Effect . Can be fed to a mount to satisfy Hunger . Seed Animal Feed decays in 10,800 seconds, but that decay can be slowed down by storing Seed Animal Feed inside an Ice Box or Refrigerator .

items.name: Seed Bread
items.description: Seed Bread is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Seed Cracker
items.description: A snack made with just seed.

items.name: Seed Extractor
items.description: The Seed Extractor is a small deployable bench used to process fruits and plants to extract Seeds for Farming .

items.name: Seed Harvesting Attachment
items.description: Seed Harvesting Attachment is a mid game item for attaching to a Harvesting Cart that allows collection of Seeds while harvesting crops planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop Plots . It has no effect on plants found in the wild.

items.name: Seed Pouch
items.description: A leather pouch for seeds that can fit 12 full stacks of Seeds .

items.name: Seeds
items.description: Seeds are a resource harvested from Flora or produced in a Seed Extractor that can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop Plots to produce more of that specific crop.

items.name: Semi-Automatic Pistol

items.description: The Shengong "Wenhe" Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass.

items.name: Shengong "Wenhe" Arrow Bundle
items.description: Consuming the Shengong "Wenhe" Arrow Bundle will add 25x Shengong "Wenhe" Arrows to the Prospectors inventory, must be consumed after dropping into a prospect. Consumed arrow bundles cannot be taken back to the space station. Arrow bundles that have not been consumed can be taken back to the space station for use in another prospect.

items.name: Shengong "Xingxing" Spear
items.description: The Shengong "Xingxing" Spear is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospector's loadout before starting a new prospect.

items.name: Shengong "Yeying" Bandage
items.description: The Shengong "Yeying" Bandage is an overly priced Basic Bandage purchased from the Workshop that will remove the Bleeding modifier when consumed.

items.name: Shengong 'Liwei' O2 Tank
items.description: It is worth noting that this Oxygen Container takes 65 Oxite to fill at a Oxite Dissolver , and will last significantly longer than an Oxygen Bladder , making it one of the most valuable early game purchases in the Workshop . Will remain filled between Prospects. It holds 6500 oxygen units making it useful for stockpile missions that require oxygen delivery.

items.name: Shengong 'Qie' Knife
items.description: This knife and others, such as the Shengong 'Sichou' Knife , with the additional attribute that gives increased skinning yield actually has a 230% Yield from Skinning. This is because the additional attribute is multiplicative and not additive, making them better than the Titanium Knife or Inaris "Ventura" Knife at skinning. Unlike Throwing Knives , the Shengong 'Qie' Knife cannot be thrown. There currently are no Workshop throwing knives.

items.name: Shengong CY7 Axe
items.description: The Shengong CY7 Axe is a Workshop Axe geared towards combat, intrinsically dealing electric damage with the chance to significantly hinder targets. Ideally used with the Berserker talent, which increases axe melee damage.
items.crafted_at: Workshop Repair Kitat a poweredRepair Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Workshop Repair Kitat a poweredRepair Bench

items.name: Shengong CZ4 Bow
items.description: Using arrows and talents interchangeably with other bows, the Shengong CZ4 Bow is geared more towards elemental damage. When paired with arrows that deal elemental damage ( Obsidian Arrows , Inaris "Netch" Arrows , etc), the Shengong CZ4 Bow can pack a punch, making it a decent, if not expensive, upgrade to the previous Shengong Bows. Dealt elemental damage is not affected by Bow talents.

items.name: Shengong DL7 Knife
items.description: The Shengong DL7 Knife is a Workshop Knife geared towards combat, intrinsically dealing electric damage with a chance to significantly hinder targets. Though the elemental damage does not scale with Knife talents, the debuff applied to targets can prove useful in certain situations. The Shengong DL7 Knife cannot be thrown, and there currently are no workshop Throwing Knives .
items.crafted_at: Workshop Repair Kitat a poweredRepair Bench

items.name: Shengong HS2 Bow
items.description: The Shengong HS2 Bow is a stronger variant of the Shengong Bows using arrows and talents interchangeably with other bows. Despite the Shengong HS2 Bow dealing 35% less damage than the Larkwell Martinez Compound Bow , the Shengong HS2 Bow is unmatched in reload speed and fire rate; perfect for the Prospector who wants to fill the skies with arrows.

items.name: Shengong PF1 Spear
items.description: Element damage does not scale with Spear talents. The Shengong PF1 Spear cannot be thrown, and there are currently no Workshop Javelins .

items.name: Shengong UT5 Pickaxe
items.description: The Shengong UT5 Pickaxe is a Workshop Pickaxe geared towards combat, intrinsically dealing electric damage with the chance to significantly hinder targets. Since the Shengong UT5 Pickaxe has the same mining radius and yield as the Larkwell Martinez Pickaxe , Prospectors are better off using the Inaris "Neves" Pickaxe for mining.
items.crafted_at: Workshop Repair Kitat a poweredRepair Bench

items.name: Shepherd's Pie
items.description: Shepherd's Pie is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Shepherd's Roll
items.description: A Shepherd's Roll is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Shotgun
items.description: The Shotgun is one of the first Firearms available to prospectors. Using 12-Gauge Buckshot Shell for ammunition, the Shotgun is more powerful than the Bolt Action Rifle at close range. However, damage decreases rapidly as range increases, and prospectors should not rely on it for long-range encounters with the Fauna of Icarus. The Shotgun can fire 100 rounds before breaking, and the talent Gunsmith can increase this to up to a maximum of 125 rounds, so bring a Machining Bench for long trips.

items.name: Shovel
items.description: The Shovel is an upgrade to the Wooden Shovel , offering increased yield when digging and higher tool durability. Like its predecessor, it can be used to create Dirt Mounds (right-click), harvest Ice / Dirt / Sand (left-click), or remove ash/snow buildup on structures in the Arctic / Volcanic biomes on Icarus.

items.name: Silencer Attachment
items.description: Silencer Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Silica Ore
items.description: Silica Ore is a Mineral found on the surface of Icarus. Prospectors are likely to first use silica to create the Mortar and Pestle . However, it is also the key in making glass and concrete.

items.name: Simple Creature Deterrent
items.description: While useful for protecting Prospectors from predators, the Simple Creature Deterrent also prevents the spawning of Fauna so be aware that deer, pronghorns, rabbits, chamois, or other animals will not spawn within the indicated radius.

items.name: Sinotai Dropship Recall Beacon
items.description: The Sinotai Dropship Recall Beacon will fire a flare that calls the Prospectors dropship to that location when thrown, which can either be used for immediate extraction or left there for use later on. Multiple Recall Beacons can be used per session, however, these are one-use items, so use them carefully. Items stored in the dropships inventory will not be lost when the dropship is called, allowing Prospectors to transport equipment/resources over large distances.

items.name: Skinning Bench
items.description: The Skinning Bench is used to process, the small to medium carcasses, of the Fauna found on Icarus. While the yields from the skinning bench differ from skinning wildlife with Knives , most notably is the ability to always obtain rarer cuts of meat from fauna such as Raw Stringy Meat .

items.name: Small Beehive Expansion
items.description: The Small Beehive Expansion increases the Small Beehive generic inventory slots by 6 and reduces the energy transmutation cost by 10%.

items.name: Small Blue Pouch
items.description: The Small Blue Pouch is a blue variant of the Small Pouch , a generic six slot container that can be placed in inventory to help organize items. It does not affect the overall weight of items or carrying capacity.

items.name: Small Tree
items.description: A small, immature tree, most often growing in wooded areas of the Forest Biome on Icarus. Can be harvested by hand for Sticks and Fiber , but more efficiently with an Axe .

items.name: Small Wood Crate
items.description: The Small Wood Crate is the first available storage container that can be made by the prospector. While limited in inventory space, anything here will not be lost upon the death of the prospector or count against inventory weight. Like most other Deployables , this must be under Shelter or it will be destroyed when exposed to Weather events. It is possible to loot the contents if this crate is destroyed, but only for a limited time.

items.name: Small Wood Sign
items.description: A Small Wood Sign made of Refined Wood and Copper Nails .

items.name: Smashed Avocado Toast
items.description: Smashed Avocado Toast is a long-lasting Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs.

items.name: Smoke Grenade
items.description: A smoke grenade is a canister-type grenade used as a signaling device, target or landing zone marking device, or as a screening device for unit movements. Upon detonation, the Smoke Grenade will cover the area in smoke and will obstruct the vision of creatures within the smoke. However, it will not stop creatures that are already aggressively pursuing Prospectors, creatures spawned by Thumpers, Radars, or other mission items that have been placed or activated. Stacks up to 5.

items.name: Smoker
items.description: The smoker is powered by Charcoal and gives you another way to cook longer lasting food. The smoker needs to be placed outside and gives a heat modifier.

items.name: Snare Trap
items.description: The Snare Trap is a deployable item used to trap and tame certain animals on Icarus. It must be filled with suitable Animal Bait and placed in an area to attract the desired animal.

items.name: Sniper Scope Attachment
items.description: Sniper Scope Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech. Does not give an actual scope to weapon.

items.name: Snow Leopard Rug
items.description: Snow Leopard Rugs are decorative deployables that can be placed on any ground surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from being for decorative purposes, it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .
items.crafted_at: Advanced Textiles Bench Electric Textiles Bench

items.name: Snow Leopard Skin Animal Bed
items.description: The Snow Leopard Skin Animal Bed is a bed for Mounts and Pets that has a snow leopard theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC . Provides no additional attributes and is a cosmetic change to the Animal Bed .

items.name: Snow Leopard Trophy
items.description: Snow Leopard Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Snow Leopard Vestige
items.description: Snow Leopard Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Snow Leopard Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary . They are also used at the Advanced Textiles Bench / Electric Textiles Bench to make Snow Leopard Rugs . Decorative purposes aside, both provide a boost to coziness, which increases the duration and effect of the Well Rested Buff .
