They are also used at any textiles bench to make Snow Wolf Rugs . Decorative purposes aside, both provide a boost to coziness, which increases the duration and effect of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Solar Panel
items.description: The Solar Panel generates Electricity when positioned in direct sunlight. Use an Electricity Tool to connect it to Benches to provide power. Contrary to its description, the Solar Panel needs to "see" the sun itself, not just be in a sunlit area to work. The panel will only provide power if it has an unobstructed view of the sun in the sky; anything that casts a shadow on it can interfere with power production. Solar Panel can be placed underwater.

items.name: Soy Bean
items.description: Soy Beans are a common form of Plantlife found in the Forest and Riverlands locations on Icarus.

items.name: Soy Bean Stir-Fry
items.description: Soy Bean Stir-Fry is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Splint
items.description: Splint is used to speed up the recovery of broken bones.

items.name: Spoiled Meat
items.description: Spoiled Meat is a byproduct of Raw Meat that has been allowed to go rancid. Can be used to make a variety of items, primarily Poison Paste . Requires the You Gonna Eat That? talent for Spoiled Meat to become consumable.

items.name: Spoiled Plants
items.description: Spoiled Plants are the byproduct of spoiled food like vegetables and fruit, and are used to craft Volatile Substance or Basic Fertilizer for Crop Plots. Cannot be eaten despite having the You Gonna Eat That? talent.

items.name: Sponge
items.description: Sponges are found growing in bodies of water on Icarus and are gathered by hand. Sponges are also be obtained through the use of Water Wheels and Basic Fishing Traps / Advanced Fishing Traps . Sponges can be identified with this reference image:

items.name: Sprinters Animal Feed
items.description: Sprinters Animal Feed is a Animal Feed for Pets or Mounts with a unique Status Effect . Can be fed to mounts to satisfy Hunger . Sprinters Animal Feed decays in 10,800 seconds, but that decay can be slowed down by storing Sprinters Animal Feed inside an Ice Box or Refrigerator .

items.name: Squash
items.description: Squash are a common form of Plantlife found in the Desert locations on Icarus. When consumed by prospectors, they replenish Hunger .

items.name: Squash Farming Packet
items.description: The Squash Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Squash seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Stabilized Exotics
items.description: Stabilized Exotics are a form of currency in the Workshop and the stabilized state that results from processing and cleaning Volatile Raw Exotics found on Prometheus .

items.name: Stamina
items.description: Stamina is a power gauge that fuels many of the actions in Icarus. Using tools, sprinting, jumping, attacking, and crafting all require stamina. Status Effects can increase or decrease max stamina or stamina regeneration. A prospector who runs out of stamina becomes exhausted and cannot perform stamina-consuming actions until they've regained a significant portion of their stamina.

items.name: Stamina Buff Paste
items.description: In-game description: A herbal concoction, temporarily increasing stamina. In-game flavor text: While lacking some of the pharmaceutical refinements, this paste produces similar physiological affects to the 'wakers' once offered to long haul space pilots.

items.name: Stamina Consumption Paste
items.description: In-game description: A biotic compound that slows stamina loss temporarily. In-game flavor text: The time-jarring effects of exotics find their influence in many subtle, poorly understood ways on Icarus.

items.name: Stamina Regeneration Paste
items.description: In-game description: An organic stimulant that accelerates stamina recovery. In-game flavor text: A herbal preparation that acts rapidly on the sympathetic nervous system, increasing noradrenergic activity.

items.name: Stamina Restoration Paste
items.description: In-game description: A natural stimulant that restores lost stamina. In-game flavor text: As countless athletes, party-goers and would-be mystics have noted, the line between natural stimulant and highly addictive narcotic is arbitrary, at best.

items.name: Stealth
items.description: Stealth is concealment from Fauna found on Icarus, and determines how both hostile and passive creatures react to your presence. Hunting is an important task for most Icarus prospectors. It provides a renewable source of Food Items , but also a number of Resources essential to survival.

items.name: Steel Arrow
items.description: The Steel Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Steel Axe
items.description: The Steel Axe is a mid-game Tool available in Icarus. Prospectors can unlock it in Tier 2  of the Tech Tree , after reaching Level 20.

items.name: Steel Bloom
items.description: Steel Bloom is a crafted resource that can be smelted in a Stone Furnace , Concrete Furnace or Electric Furnace to make a Steel Ingot . It can made made from Iron Ore or Iron Ingot and Coal Ore or Charcoal .

items.name: Steel Bolt
items.description: The Steel Bolt is ammunition used with a Crossbow . Like arrows and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Steel Hammer
items.description: Example: If a Prospector were to upgrade a Wood Wall to a Stone Wall , a Stone Wall must be in the inventory of the Prospector when upgrading.

items.name: Steel Heater Shield
items.description: Background information on the Steel Heater Shield can be found here .

items.name: Steel Ingot
items.description: Steel Ingot is the refined resource crafted from Steel Bloom , prospectors may use a Stone Furnace , Concrete Furnace , or Electric Furnace .

items.name: Steel Javelin
items.description: The Steel Javelin is a variant of the Steel Spear that can only be thrown. A cheap upgrade to the Iron Javelin that increases projectile damage with a lower break chance, but is locked until prospectors reach level 20.

items.name: Steel Knife
items.description: The Steel Knife is an upgrade in damage and durability from the Iron Knife , the Steel Knife can be used as either a melee weapon or tool. An attachment slot is available, allowing for the application of Tool Attachment Packs at an Alteration Bench / Advanced Alteration Bench .

items.name: Steel Pickaxe
items.description: The Steel pickaxe is the 3rd pickaxe prospectors can unlock during your time on Icarus and allows for the mining of denser Minerals not obtainable with the Iron Pickaxe or Stone Pickaxe . Like iron tools, the steel pickaxe is made and is repairable at an Anvil Bench .

items.name: Steel Rebar
items.description: Steel Rebar is a critical component of Concrete Structures , and is solely used for this purpose.

items.name: Steel Screw
items.description: Steel Screw is used in crafting high end tools, weapons, and structures like Aluminium Buildings .

items.name: Steel Spear
items.description: The Steel Spear is an upgrade to the Iron Spear that deals more damage/critical damage to targets and has twice the durability. Unlike the Steel Javelin , the Steel Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Steel Throwing Knife
items.description: The Steel Throwing Knife is a variant of the Steel Knife that can be thrown. Unlike the Steel Knife , the Steel Throwing Knife cannot be used to skin fauna. Crafted in batches of five and stacks up to fifty.

items.name: Stew
items.description: Stew is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Stick
items.description: Sticks are harvested by picking them up off of the ground, or when harvesting small trees and saplings. Sticks can also be crafted from wood at the Carpentry Bench , or in the Character Crafting menu if you have the Wood Breakdown talent (and its matching Blueprint in Tier 1 ).

items.name: Stone
items.description: Stone is one of the most abundant Minerals available on Icarus. Prospectors will make extensive use of stone from the moment they exit their drop-pods, as it is widely used in the early game for both Tools and Weapons .

items.name: Stone Arrow
items.description: The Stone Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass.

items.name: Stone Axe
items.description: The Stone Axe is used primarily for chopping down trees and Small Trees , reducing them to usable Wood . In the process of chopping apart fallen trees, a small number of Sticks may be added to your inventory automatically.

items.name: Stone Beam
items.description: Stronger than Wood, and resistant to weather, Stone Buildings are a game changer when it comes to surviving on Icarus.

items.name: Stone Knife
items.description: The first knife that can be unlocked, the Stone Knife is a fast melee weapon and doubles as a tool with any knife being necessary to skin a carcass prior to unlocking the Skinning Bench .

items.description: The Stone Komodo Statue is a decorative stone item.

items.name: Stone Pickaxe
items.description: The Stone Pickaxe is the first Pickaxe available to prospectors and is used to break apart mineable Minerals , reducing them to usable resources. Stone, Sulfur, Oxite, Silica, Coal, Salt, Copper, Iron, Gold, and Exotic nodes can be mined with a Stone Pickaxe. To mine Aluminium, Platinum, and Titanium, prospectors must use a Steel Pickaxe or better.

items.name: Stone Pile
items.description: The Stone Pile, alongside the Wood Pile , are makeshift storage options for large quantities of each raw material. The Stone Pile is immune to ALL Weather damage and can be used as a durable barrier to Fauna , especially against Fauna like the Grizzly Bear . If placed with just a narrow opening between piles, Bears have an incredibly difficult time getting through which allows the Prospector to melee attack just beyond the bear's attack range.

items.name: Stone Water Trough
items.description: The Stone Water Trough is a decorative upgrade to the Water Trough that allows multiple creatures to drink from it simultaneously and can be connected to Water using a Water Pipe Tool , similar to the Large Water Trough . The Stone Water Trough can only store water and cannot provide water to the rest of the network like Water Barrels or Metal Rain Reservoirs .

items.name: Stonejaw Trophy
items.description: Stonejaw Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Stonejaw Vestige
items.description: Stonejaw Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Stonejaw Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Storm Visor Attachment
items.description: Storm Visor Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Armor Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Strawberries & Cream
items.description: Strawberries & Cream is a long-lasting Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs.

items.name: Strawberry
items.description: Strawberry is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Strawberry Farming Packet
items.description: The Strawberry Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Strawberry seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Strawberry Hard Candy
items.description: Strawberry Hard Candy is a consumable food that provides a quick boost of movement speed.

items.name: Strawberry Jam
items.description: Strawberry Jam is a long-lasting Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Strawberry Jam, Berry Jam and Pickled Carrot , do not spoil and is therefore a valuable food for long-term storage.

items.name: Strength Boost Module
items.description: When equipped in a module slot of an Envirosuit , this module increases the carry weight capacity of Prospectors near the user, however it does not affect the wearers max carry weight. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop .

items.name: Strengthened Strings Attachment
items.description: Strengthened Strings Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Striker Terrenus Animal Bed
items.description: The Striker Terrenus Animal Bed is a bed for Mounts and Pets that has an... unsettling theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC . Provides no additional attributes and is a cosmetic change to the Animal Bed .

items.name: Stringy Jerky
items.description: Stringy Jerky is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Submachine Gun
items.description: The Submachine Gun is a compact firearm with low projectile and critical damage, but a high rate of fire. It uses Pistol Ammunition such as Armor Piercing , Explosive , Incendiary , Obsidian or regular 9mm Rounds .

items.name: Sugar Cane
items.description: Sugar Cane does not naturally spawn on Icarus and is obtainable by planting Seeds obtained from a Sugar Cane Farming Packet ordered from the Workshop through the Orbital Exchange Interface .

items.name: Sugar Cane Farming Packet
items.description: The Sugar Cane Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Sugar Cane Seeds , which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop Plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Sugar Cubes
items.description: Sugar Cubes are an intermediate crafting resource produced by processing Sugar Cane in a Mortar and Pestle or a Material Processor

items.name: Suit Conditioning Module
items.description: This module increases the user's resistance to cold/hot environments, reducing the chances of Hypothermia/Hyperthermia. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Suit Conditioning Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit and will further increase the users cold/heat resistance.

items.name: Sulfur
items.description: Sulfur is a Mineral found on the surface of Icarus. Sulfur is used as a fuel source to fill Oxygen Containers and it is used in crafting items like Gunpowder and the Fire Extinguisher .

items.name: Super Cooled Ice
items.description: Super Cooled Ice is a resource required to make Cold Steel Ingots , a precursor resource used in making Cold Steel Tools , Weapons , and Ammo .

items.name: Supplemental Filtration Attachment
items.description: Supplemental Filtration Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Armor Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Supplemental Respiration Attachment
items.description: Supplemental Respiration Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Armor Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Survival Animal Feed
items.description: Survival Animal Feed is an Animal Feed for Pets or Mounts with a unique Status Effect . Can be fed to mounts to satisfy Hunger . Survival Animal Feed decays in 10,800 seconds, but that decay can be slowed down by storing Survival Animal Feed inside an Ice Box or Refrigerator .

items.name: Survival Backpack
items.description: The Survival Backpack is a must need when taking long trips across Icarus, fit everything you need inside for survival! Innovative storage system that mitigates injuries.

items.name: Survival Kit
items.description: Survival Kits are a Tier 3  bandage that heals basic wounds, deep wounds, frostbite and heatstroke Status Effects . It replaces a number of basic items, but requires considerably more materials to craft.

items.name: Survival Module
items.description: This module increases the user's resistance to cold/hot environments, reducing the damage taken from Hypothermia/Hyperthermia. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Survival Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit and will further increase the users resistance to hyperthermia/hypothermia.

items.name: Suture Kit
items.description: A Suture Kit is used to treat a Deep Wound, Hemorrhage or Exotic Deep Wound.

items.name: Sweetcorn Soup
items.description: Sweetcorn Soup is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Synthetic Enzymes
items.description: Synthetic Enzymes are a crafted variant of Condensed Enzymes that can be used as fuel in a Localized Terraforming Device . Unlike Condensed Enzymes , the synthetic version is less potent as a fuel but does not require constructing, placing or defending a Vapor Condenser on an Enzyme Geyser .

items.name: Tackle Box
items.description: The Tackle Box is a storage deployable that can be used to store a handful of lures and caught fish. Unlike other storage deployables, the Tackle Box can be picked up with items inside and does not require shelter to be used. With 3 slots for Lures and 2 slots that will halt the spoil timer of any caught fish, the Tackle Box is a handy tool for fishing adventures.

items.name: Tactical Bow
items.description: The Tactical Bow is an advanced bow that is part of the Great Hunts Campaigns DLC on Prometheus . It fires any type of Arrow and can be upgraded in the Bio-lab .

items.name: Talents
items.description: With 465 combined talents to choose from, Icarus' talent trees give prospectors the ability to construct their own unique play-styles inside of five primary Categories: Survival, Adventure, Habitation, Combat and Solo Talents Trees.

items.name: Talents

items.name: Target Dummy
items.description: Target Dummys are deployable items used to test out weapons and to see their damage output when hitting hard points and weak points.

items.name: Taxidermy Knife
items.description: The Taxidermy Knife is used for skinning Fauna carcasses, when a prospector wishes to obtain a Vestige for mounting. Skinning any carcass with a taxidermy knife grants four Bestiary points for the animal skinned.

items.name: Tea
items.description: Tea are a common form of Plantlife found in the Forest and Riverlands locations on Icarus.

items.name: Textiles Bench
items.description: Allows for the crafting of various Armor sets, such as the Leather Armor Set , Fur Armor Set , Ghillie Armor Set , Sandworm Armor Set , and the Scorpion Armor Set . Items like the Basic Riding Saddle , Simple Creature Deterrent and Rope can also be made at the Textiles Bench.

items.name: Thatch Beam
items.description: Thatch building pieces are very light-weight and are best used for emergency shelters, or as scaffolding inside caves. While subject to damage from milder storms than any other material, they are light enough to carry and will still offer protection to Deployables and Storage containers. For different orientations, hold R while holding a Thatch Beam (more item actions can be seen bottom right).

items.name: Thatch Door
items.description: Thatch building pieces are very light-weight and are best used for emergency shelters. While subject to damage from milder storms than any other material, they are light enough to carry and will still offer protection to Deployables and Storage containers. Can be attached to door frames (hold R while holding a Wall Building Piece and select the door frame variant from the radial menu).

items.name: Threshing Attachment
items.description: Threshing Attachment is a mid game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Tool Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Titanium Arrow
items.description: The Titanium Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Titanium Attachment
items.description: Titanium Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Tool Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Titanium Axe
items.description: The Titanium Axe is the highest tiered Axe that can be crafted while on the surface of Icarus.

items.name: Titanium Bolt
items.description: The Titanium Bolt is ammunition used with a Crossbow . Like arrows and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass. Crafted in batches of 5.

items.name: Titanium Crossbow
items.description: The Titanium Crossbow is an upgrade to the Platinum Crossbow that offers a boost to projectile damage and a slightly larger ammo count; has a chance to slow targets and can fully penetrate hardened points, but has a slower fire rate than Bows .

items.name: Titanium Hammer
items.description: Example: If a Prospector were to upgrade a Wood Wall to a Stone Wall , a Stone Wall must be in the inventory of the Prospector when upgrading.

items.name: Titanium Ingot
items.description: Titanium Ingot is the refined resource crafted from Titanium Ore , is used widely in Tier 4  crafting recipes.

items.name: Titanium Javelin
items.description: The Titanium Javelin is a variant of the Titanium Spear that can only be thrown and is a costly upgrade to Tier 3  Javelins.

items.name: Titanium Knife
items.description: The Titanium Knife is an upgrade in damage and durability from the Platinum Knife , the Titanium Knife can be used as either a melee weapon or tool. Unlike the Titanium Throwing Knife , the Titanium Knife cannot be thrown.

items.name: Titanium Ore
items.description: Titanium Ore is a late-game Mineral, and can be utilized by prospectors after they reach level 30 and unlock the Fabricator in the Tier 4  Tech Tree . Titanium represents the current pinnacle of material strength for Tools and for several Weapons .

items.name: Titanium Pickaxe
items.description: The Titanium Pickaxe is the highest-tiered Pickaxe that can be crafted while on the surface of Icarus. When combined with a Tool Attachment Pack / Advanced Tool Attachment Pack , the Titanium Pickaxe surpasses the Inaris "Neves" Pickaxe in terms of mining.

items.name: Titanium Plate
items.description: Titanium Plate is used in a variety of high-end resources and components.

items.name: Titanium Shovel
items.description: The Titanium Shovel is an upgrade to the Platinum Shovel , offering increased yield when digging and higher tool durability. Like its predecessor, it can be used to create Dirt Mounds (right-click), harvest Ice / Dirt / Sand (left-click), or remove ash/snow buildup on structures in the Arctic / Volcanic biomes on Icarus.

items.name: Titanium Sickle
items.description: Used by 'attacking' plants such as shrubs, Reed Flower , Wheat , Carrots , etc. Sickles significantly increase the yield of plants when harvesting.

items.name: Titanium Spear
items.description: The Titanium Spear is the first Spear available to prospectors once they reach Tier 4  and serves as an, albeit expensive, upgrade to its Tier 3  counterparts. Unlike the Titanium Javelin , the Titanium Spear cannot be thrown.

items.name: Titanium Throwing Knife
items.description: The Titanium Throwing Knife is a variant of the Titanium Knife that can be thrown. Unlike the Titanium Knife , the Titanium Throwing Knife cannot be used to skin fauna. Crafted in batches of five and stacks up to fifty.

items.name: Titanium Tower Shield
items.description: The Titanium Tower Shield is crafted at the Foundry with the following resources:

items.name: Tomato
items.description: Tomato are a fruit found growing on bushes in the Grassland Biome on Icarus. They can be harvested by hand or more efficiently with the use of a Sickle .

items.name: Tomato Farming Packet
items.description: The Tomato Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Tomato seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Tomato Soup
items.description: Tomato Soup is a consumable Food crafted from Tomatoes and Water . As Tomatoes are only found on Prometheus , this recipe requires the New Frontiers DLC to obtain the ingredients.

items.name: Tool Attachment Pack
items.description: Tool Attachment Pack is a Tier 3  Tech needed for the Alteration Bench that allows Prospectors to alter their Tools with Attachment Packs .

items.name: Tracking Attachment
items.description: The Tracking Attachment is an armor alteration that boosts Critical Damage and allows active world bosses to be seen on the map.

items.name: Trajectory Module Attachment
items.description: Trajectory Module Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Tree Sap
items.description: Tree Sap is used in crafting of items such as Epoxy , and Concrete Mix , making this early-game resource very important throughout all aspects of crafting. Tree Sap can also by found while harvesting some plants, like the palms of the Desert .

items.name: Trench Shotgun
items.description: An attachment slot is available, allowing for the application of Ranged Attachment Packs at an Alteration Bench / Advanced Alteration Bench . Devastating up close when paired with the Barrel Widening Attachment / Narrow Barrel Attachment s and the Larkwell Martinez Mercenary Backpack .

items.name: Trophy Bench
items.description: The Trophy Bench allows prospectors to create Trophies from various Vestiges , for eventual display around a building or outpost.

items.name: Tusker Trophy
items.description: Tusker Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Tusker Vestige
items.description: Tusker Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Tusker Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: UDA Aluminium Ore Resource Supply
items.description: Despite the usefulness of these supply packs, they are quite expensive when used often (ideal for creative builds). Don't feel like running out to gather materials, and you're out of Ren? Exotics can be sold for Ren under the Workshop tab while at the station, and Ren can be obtained by completing SMPL3 missions using the Short Range Radio .

items.name: UDA Clay Resource Supply
items.description: The Stabilized Exotics needed to research this item are exclusive to the Prometheus map.

items.name: Ubis Trophy
items.description: Ubis Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Ubis Vestige
items.description: Ubis Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Ubis Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: UltraMeal
items.description: Ultra Meal is a Food with a unique Status Effect : 'Emergency Rations'. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger . It is a one time use emergency ration to stave off starvation.

items.name: Vapor Condenser
items.description: The Vapor Condenser is a deployable that can be placed on Enzyme Geysers to extract Condensed Enzymes and Exotics (depending on the game mode).

items.name: Vegetable Oil
items.description: Vegetable Oil is an intermediary resource used to create Biofuel , Cured Leather , a Submachine Gun and various Food recipes.

items.name: Vegetable Pie
items.description: Vegetable Pie is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Vegetable Roll
items.description: Vegetable Roll is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Viscid Trophy
items.description: Viscid Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Viscid Vestige
items.description: Viscid Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Viscid Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Vitamins
items.description: Vitamins are a late-game Tier 4  preventative Medicine that increases resistance to a number of conditions and is useful in all Biomes . It does not consume a stomach slot so it can be combined with other Food buffs.
items.crafted_at: the Chemistry Bench with the following resources:

items.name: Volatile Exotic Seed
items.description: Volatile Exotic Seeds are a resource obtained from Strange Plants that can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop Plots to produce more Volatile Raw Exotics .

items.name: Volatile Raw Exotics
items.description: While the Exotics prospectors found on Olympus and Styx were originally believed to be the only known variation, the UDA has made a remarkable discovery. This unstable variant is different and appears to have an impact on the local flora not seen before.

items.name: Volatile Substance
items.description: Volatile Substance is a precursor resource used in making explosive Ammunition and weapons like the Frag Grenade . Volatile Substance is highly unstable and has a spoil timer of 600 seconds. Once spoiled, the item will then become Inert Volatile Substance .
items.crafted_at: Crafted atMortar and PestleHerbalism BenchChemistry BenchMedicine Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Crafted atMortar and PestleHerbalism BenchChemistry BenchMedicine Bench

items.name: Volcanic Animal Feed
items.description: Volcanic Animal Feed is a Animal Feed for Pets or Mounts with a unique Status Effect . Can be fed to mounts to satisfy Hunger . Volcanic Animal Feed decays in 10,800 seconds, but that decay can be slowed down by storing Volcanic Animal Feed inside an Ice Box or Refrigerator .

items.name: Wall Torch
items.description: Wall lighting for a prospector's base. Provides limited heat. Will not be damaged by storms if placed outside.

items.name: Water
items.description: Water is a basic resource needed for survival on Icarus. It may be consumed by drinking from natural water sources such as lakes, streams, and pools found in Caves . Water from these natural sources is Tainted Water and has a 15% chance of causing dysentery. Water has various levels of purity depending on source and means of filtering. A status icon is displayed to indicate the type and status of water the prospector has consumed.

items.name: Water Barrel
items.description: Water Barrels are a deployable that can be connected to a water network to store 300,000 water and can output 1,000 water per second to keep the network operational.

items.name: Water Bomb
items.description: The Water Bomb is a Tier 2  item that will aid Prospectors in extinguishing fires. Once thrown, the Water Bomb will douse the area in water, putting out any fires. Stacks up to 5.

items.name: Water Borer
items.description: The Water Borer is a device that can be placed on Enzyme Geysers and when powered, can be used to extract Water which can be fed into a water network.

items.name: Water Consumption Paste
items.description: In-game description: A natural preparation, temporarily reducing the body's need for water. In-game flavor text: The key word here is 'temporarily'.

items.name: Water Pipe Tool
items.description: The Water Pipe Tool connects the Biofuel Water Pump / Electric Water Pump to Deployables / Water Storage to provide Water .

items.name: Water Purifier
items.description: Water Purifiers can be crafted from the Machining Bench with the following resources once the appropriate blueprint point has been spent:

items.name: Water Sprinkler
items.description: The Water Sprinkler will provide fire suppression when connected to a Water Network with a Water Pipe Tool . Can be manually activated by damaging it or by pressing F to water nearby Dirt Mounds / Crop Plots or to apply the Wet modifier to nearby prospectors and deployables, which can help counter heatwaves in Deserts .

items.name: Water Treatment Pill
items.description: Water Treatment Pills remove the risk of dysentery from Tainted and Rainwater. Use with any canteen of water using the Character Crafting interface

items.name: Water Trough
items.description: The Water Trough is a basic trough used to keep Mounts and Pets hydrated. Can be filled using a Liquid Container filled with Water or by leaving it exposed to the elements.

items.name: Water Wheel
items.description: The Water Wheel is a power-generating device that can be placed in any flowing body of water. Use an Electricity Tool to connect it to Benches to provide power.

items.name: Watering Can
items.description: The Watering Can is a mid-game Tool used to water multiple crop plots/dirt mounds simultaneously. Prospectors can unlock it in Tier 2  portion of the Tech Tree after reaching Level 20. The Watering Can hold 5.0 L and can be used five times before needing to be refilled.

items.name: Watermelon
items.description: Watermelons are a common form of Plantlife found in the Forest and Riverlands locations on Icarus. When consumed by Prospectors, they replenish Hunger and Thirst .

items.name: Watermelon Farming Packet
items.description: The Watermelon Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Watermelon seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Watermelon Lollypop
items.description: Watermelon Lollypop is a consumable food that provides a quick burst of energy to reduce movement speed penalties.

items.name: Waterskin
items.description: Filled at any water source, including a Rain Reservoir .

items.name: Wayfarer Arms Armor
items.description: Wayfarer Arms Armor is a mid-game Tier 3  crafted armor which can aid prospectors traveling through the Deserts on Icarus.

items.name: Wheat
items.description: A tall grass which grows in clusters in the Forest Biome on Icarus. They can be harvested most efficiently with the use of Sickles . Can be processed into flour using the Mortar and Pestle .

items.name: Wheat Farming Packet
items.description: The Wheat Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Wheat seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: White Jelly Lure
items.description: The White Jelly Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. Like all Lures , the White Jelly Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: White Jerky
items.description: White Jerky is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Wild Berry
items.description: Wild Berry are a common form of Plantlife found in the Forest and Riverlands locations on Icarus. When consumed by prospectors, they replenish both Hunger and Thirst .

items.name: Wild Boar Bait
items.description: Wild Boar Bait is a single-use Crafted Resource used to attract and capture Wild Boars when used with a Snare Trap . Wild Boar Bait does not decay and can only be used in Forest and Grassland Biomes. Stacks up to ten.

items.name: Wild Boar Trophy
items.description: Wild Boar Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Wild Boar Vestige
items.description: Wild Boar Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Wild Boar Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Wild Salad
items.description: Wild Salad is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Wind Turbine
items.description: The Wind Turbine is a power generating device that must be placed outdoors. It provides 1,750 units of power when active and must also be placed in an area clear of obstructions for it to function. Use an Electricity Tool to connect it to Benches to provide power.

items.name: Windmill
items.description: The Windmill is a faster Tier 3  equivalent of the Mortar and Pestle and an intermediate item before reaching the Material Processor on Tier 4  .

items.name: Wine
items.description: Wine is a mid-game beverage brewed from Wild Berry and Reed Flower that greatly increases stamina and stamina regeneration.
items.crafted_at: Blueprint points in the Glassworking Bench

base_recipe.crafted_at: Blueprint points in the Glassworking Bench

items.name: Wolf Bait
items.description: Wolf Bait is a Crafted Resource used to attract and capture wild wolves. It is a single-use item that is used with a Snare Trap and allows prospectors to tame Wolves / Snow Wolves . Wolf Bait does not decay and can only be used in Forest , Grassland and Arctic Biomes. Stacks up to ten.

items.name: Wolf Lure
items.description: The Wolf Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. The capture zone increase is the size of the capture area during the fishing minigame, increasing the success chance of catching a fish. Like all Lures , the Wolf Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Wolf Rug
items.description: Wolf Rugs are decorative deployables that can be placed on any ground surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from being for decorative purposes, it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Wolf Trophy
items.description: Wolf Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Wolf Vestige
items.description: Wolf Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Wolf Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary . They are also used at any textiles bench to make Wolf Rugs . Decorative purposes aside, both provide a boost to coziness, which increases the duration and effect of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Wolfskin Animal Bed
items.description: The Wolfskin Animal Bed is a bed for Mounts and Pets that has a wolf theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC . Provides no additional attributes and is a cosmetic change to the Animal Bed .

items.name: Wood
items.description: Wood is a basic crafting ingredient obtained from Trees using an axe or harvested by hand in the Desert via Cacti. Wood can also be used as a Fuel source for Campfire , Fireplace , and Stone Furnace .

items.name: Wood Beam
items.description: Stronger than Thatch, wood buildings are a good starting point for prospectors wanting to establish a 'Main Base'. While still flammable they are able to fully withstand most light storms and offer good protection to Deployables and Storage containers. Wood beams require another structure for adjacent 'snapping' and seem to apply 'well stabilized' to a larger area than the Thatch Beam .

items.name: Wood Bow
items.description: The Wood Bow is the first bow a player can get access to. It can be unlocked via the Tech Tree in Tier 1  with no prerequisite tech required.

items.name: Wood Buffalo Statue
items.description: The Wood Buffalo Statue is a decorative wood item.

items.name: Wood Burner
items.description: The Wood Burner is a source of heat and basic cooking similar to a Campfire or Fireplace . It provides the Warming Fire effect (heat and +100% Perceived Threat) allowing a Prospector to sleep nearby. Once fuel is added, it can be activated and will consume fuel regardless of any selected recipe.

items.name: Wood Composter
items.description: Wood Composter increases the rate at which food spoils, and will turn Spoiled Plants or Guano into Basic Fertilizer .

items.name: Wood Crop Plot
items.description: The Wood Crop Plot is a farming plot for growing Seeds that can later be harvested for Plant Resources once fully grown. Unless the Prospector has the Fresh Is Best talent when deploying a seed into the crop plot, the grown Plant Resource will eventually wither if not harvested.

items.name: Wood Cupboard
items.description: Taking up the same floor-space but with a much larger inventory, this is a great upgrade from the Medium Wood Crate .

items.description: The Wood Deer Statue is a decorative wood item.

items.name: Wood Gate Fortification
items.description: The Wood Gate Fortification serves as an entrance when using Wood Wall Fortifications . Similar to Medium Wood Hedgehogs , the Wood Gate Fortification does not take damage during storms. Wood Spikes Fortification cannot be mounted to the Wood Gate Fortification.

items.name: Wood Halfpieces
items.description: Stronger than Thatch, wood buildings are a good starting point for prospectors wanting to establish a 'Main Base'. While still flammable they are able to fully withstand most light storms and offer good protection to Deployables and Storage containers. Wood roofs or walls require a floor or wall structure such as Wood Wall for snapping. Hold 'R' while placing the Wood Halfpieces itself to determine shape as well as placement as roof, or wall.

items.name: Wood Halfpitches
items.description: Stronger than Thatch, wood buildings are a good starting point for prospectors wanting to establish a 'Main Base'. While still flammable they are able to fully withstand most light storms and offer good protection to Deployables and Storage containers. Wood roofs or walls require a floor or wall structure such as Wood Wall for snapping. Hold 'R' while placing the Wood Halfpitches itself to determine shape as well as placement as roof, or wall.

items.name: Wood Hammer
items.description: Example: If a Prospector were to upgrade a Wood Wall to a Stone Wall , a Stone Wall must be in the inventory of the Prospector when upgrading.

items.name: Wood Javelin
items.description: The Wood Javelin is a variant of the Wood Spear that can only be thrown. The Wood Javelin has the slowest projectile travel time and highest projectile fall-off, but that can be overlooked by it's cheap producibility.

items.name: Wood Ladder
items.description: Stronger than Thatch, wood buildings are a good starting point for Prospectors wanting to establish a 'Main Base'. While still flammable, they are able to fully withstand most light storms and offer good protection to Deployables and Storage containers. Wood Ladders can be use with Trapdoor holes (hold R while holding a floor building piece and select the Trapdoor variant from the radial wheel). Does not snap to trapdoor holes.

items.name: Wood Pile
items.description: The Wood Pile, alongside the Stone Pile , are makeshift storage options for large quantities of each raw material. Though immune to most Weather damage, beware of lightning strikes. Can be used as a durable barrier to Fauna , especially against Fauna like the Grizzly Bear , although the stone variant is preferred.

items.name: Wood Piranha Statue
items.description: The Wood Piranha Statue is a decorative wood item.

items.name: Wood Rabbit Statue
items.description: The Wood Rabbit Statue is a decorative wood item.

items.name: Wood Rag Torch
items.description: The first available source of Light Source . Can be equipped in the "L" light slot on the hotbar. When lit, the Wood Rag Torch also provides heat in addition to light. The Wood Rag Torch will last about 33 minutes and 20 seconds when lit before extinguishing. The Wood Rag Torch allows prospectors to see approximately 6 meters, or 3 standard floor pieces, from their position.

items.name: Wood Railing
items.description: The Wood Railing is part of the Wood Building Trim Set , which is learned in the Tier 1  Tech Tree after unlocking the Wood Building Base Set .

items.name: Wood Railing Gate
items.description: Stronger than Thatch, wood buildings are a good starting point for Prospectors wanting to establish a 'Main Base'. While still flammable, they are able to fully withstand most light storms and offers good protection to Deployables and Storage containers. Wood Railing Gates can be deployed on their own or can be snapped to railings/floors.

items.name: Wood Roof
items.description: Wood Roof is crafted in the Character Crafting with the following resources:

items.name: Wood Roof Corner
items.description: Wood Roof Corner is crafted in the Character Crafting with the following resources:

items.name: Wood Shield
items.description: The Wood Shield is crafted at the Anvil, Forge, or Foundry with the following resources:

items.name: Wood Spear
items.description: The Wood Spear is the first Spear available to prospectors and serves as an alternative to the Stone Knife , dealing increased critical damage but with a slower attack speed. Like other spears, the Wood Spear increase the range to which prospectors can attack fauna, providing a unique advantage when up high.

items.name: Wood Spikes Fortification
items.description: The Wood Spikes Fortification serves as large hedgehog that can attach Wood Wall Fortifications to fend off the predators of Icarus. Similar to Medium Wood Hedgehogs , the Wood Spikes Fortification does not take damage during storms.

items.name: Wood Table
items.description: The Wood Table is a decorative item that can be used for deployables like the Mortar and Pestle and provides a bonus to Coziness .

items.name: Wood Torch
items.description: The Wood Torch is an upgraded handheld Light Source that will last longer than the Wood Rag Torch . Can be equipped in the "L" light slot on the hotbar and provides heat when lit. The Wood Torch will last about 50 minutes when lit before extinguishing. The Wood Torch allows prospectors to see approximately 6 meters, or 3 standard floor pieces, from their position.

items.name: Wood Trapdoor
items.description: Stronger than Thatch, wood buildings are a good starting point for Prospectors wanting to establish a 'Main Base'. While still flammable, they are able to fully withstand most light storms and offer good protection to Deployables and Storage containers. Attaches to floors with trapdoor holes (hold R while holding a floor piece and select the Trapdoor variant from the radial wheel).

items.name: Wood Walkway Fortification
items.description: The Wood Walkway Fortification is attached to Wood Wall Fortifications and serves as a platform that Prospectors can stand on, providing them a vantage point to see over their walls. Similar to Medium Wood Hedgehogs , the Wood Walkway Fortification does not take damage during storms.

items.name: Wood Wall
items.description: Wood Wall is crafted in the Character Crafting with the following resources:

items.name: Wood Wall Angled
items.description: Stronger than Thatch, wood buildings are a good starting point for prospectors wanting to establish a 'Main Base'. While still flammable they are able to fully withstand most light storms and offer good protection to Deployables and Storage containers. Wood wall angles may be snapped into existing floors or walls such as Wood Wall . Holding 'R' while placing the angled wood wall for additional placement styles or directionality.

items.name: Wood Wall Fortification
items.description: The Wood Wall Fortification serves as large wall that can attach Wood Spikes Fortifications to fend off the predators of Icarus. Similar to Medium Wood Hedgehogs , the Wood Wall Fortification does not take damage during storms.

items.name: Wood Window
items.description: Stronger than Thatch, wood buildings are a good starting point for Prospectors wanting to establish a 'Main Base'. While still flammable, they are able to fully withstand most light storms and offer good protection to Deployables and Storage containers. Wood Windows may be snapped into walls such as Wood Wall that have been placed in 'window' configuration. Holding 'R' while placing a Wood Wall , for example, allows for additional placement styles, such as the window frame.

items.name: Wooden Armor Stand
items.description: The Wooden Armor Stand is a deployable item to store a set of Armor for display purposes and to easily swap out the armor set.

items.name: Wooden Bed
items.description: The Wooden Bed allows prospectors to sleep provided it is sufficiently sheltered and it is night time in-game. In a multiplayer game, all prospectors must sleep at the same time to pass the night. Prospectors can set their respawn location to a bed, however if this bed is deconstructed or destroyed, the prospector's spawn location will reset back to the drop-pod.

items.name: Wooden Chair
items.description: A Wooden Chair made of refined wood and copper nails.

items.name: Wooden Fishing Rod
items.description: One approach to catching fish is by using a Fishing Rod. Though a lure is not required, attaching one can increase the quality, length, and weight of the caught fish. Additionally, certain lures can increase the odds of catching fish of a certain rarity or increase the size of the capture area. For a list of available lures, view this page .

items.name: Wooden Lure
items.description: The Wooden Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. Like all Lures , the Wooden Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Wooden Shovel
items.description: The Wooden Shovel is an early-game Tool used to create Dirt Mounds (right-click), harvest Ice / Dirt / Sand (left-click), or remove ash/snow buildup on structures in the Arctic / Volcanic biomes on Icarus.

items.name: Wool
items.description: Wool from sheep can be used to craft arctic pelt, platinum weave or rope.

items.name: Woolly Mammoth Trophy
items.description: Woolly Mammoth Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Woolly Mammoth Vestige
items.description: Woolly Mammoth Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Mammoth Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Workshop
items.description: Aboard the Space Station , Prospectors can spend Ren and Exotics to research and craft new Orbital Tech .

items.name: Workshop Repair Kit
items.description: The Workshop Repair Kit is obtained by purchasing a Workshop Repair Kit Bundle from the Workshop on the Space Station and consuming the bundle. Workshop Repair Kits can be used to repair Workshop Items at a powered Repair Bench .

items.name: Workshop Repair Kit Bundle
items.description: The Workshop Repair Kit Bundle is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station . Once opened, this bundle gives the Prospector five Workshop Repair Kit s that can be used to repair Orbital Workshop Tools/Weapons/Armor at a powered Repair Bench .

items.name: World Boss Module
items.description: The World Boss Module is researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Must be equipped in a envirosuit module slot after dropping into a Prospect.

items.name: Worm Scale
items.description: Worm Scales are a resource that drops from Caveworms . Only after completing Unearthed: Research can these scales and Poison Sacks be used to craft new weaponry at a Crafting Bench .

items.name: Xenon Backpack
items.description: The Xenon Backpack is designed to aid prospectors in hunting and vestige gathering, granting prospectors the ability to harvest vestiges from animals without needing to use a Taxidermy Knife ; an excellent choice for those seeking to complete the Bestiary .

items.name: Xigo "Duo" S5 Envirosuit
items.description: The Xigo "Duo" S5 Envirosuit is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station .

items.name: Xigo "Fermi" S5 Envirosuit
items.description: The Xigo "Fermi" S5 Envirosuit is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station .

items.name: Xigo "Gustav" S5 Envirosuit
items.description: The Xigo "Gustav" S5 Envirosuit is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station .

items.name: Xigo "Hark" S5 Envirosuit
items.description: The Xigo "Hark" S5 Envirosuit is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station .

items.name: Xigo Puri-tab
items.description: Xigo Puri-tab is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . The purification tablet will convert any Water to Treated Water in a canteen or Liquid Container . The recipe for purifying water should be available in your character Crafting menu when you have a filled canteen and a Xigo Puri-tab in your inventory.

items.name: Xigo Quick-Fix Bundle
items.description: The Xigo Quick-Fix Bundle provides 5 Xigo Quick-Fix Kits that act as Medicine to heal various types of wounds and remove afflictions.

items.name: Xigo Quick-Fix Kit
items.description: The Xigo Quick-Fix Kit is a consumable Medicine that heals wounds and removes certain Status Effects .

items.name: Xigo S5 Envirosuit
items.description: The Xigo S5 Envirosuit is the default Envirosuit automatically equipped in the Prospector's loadout if an envirosuit is not equipped prior to starting a new prospect.

items.name: Xigo S5-II Envirosuit
items.description: The Xigo S5-II Envirosuit is the first unlockable envirosuit Prospectors can unlock in the Workshop on the Space Station .

items.name: Xigo S5-X Envirosuit
items.description: The Xigo S5-X Envirosuit is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station .

items.name: Xigo SplintX
items.description: Xigo Splint X is a consumable medicine to heal a Broken Leg or Sprain Status Effect and provide a +10% Falling Resistance for a duration of 5 minutes.

items.name: Xigo SplintX Bundle
items.description: The Xigo Splint X Bundle provides 5 Xigo Splint Xs that act as Medicine to heal a Sprain or Broken Leg Status Effect and provide +10% Falling Resistance.

items.name: Yeast
items.description: A small flower which grows in groups in the Forest Biome on Icarus. They can be harvested most efficiently with the use of Sickles .

items.name: Yeast Farming Packet
items.description: The Yeast Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Yeast seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or Crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Yeast Lure
items.description: The Yeast Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. Like all Lures , the Yeast Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Young Coconut
items.description: Harvested from palm trees in the Desert , when chopping their tops with an axe. If a prospector lets it decay, it will ripen into a Ripe Coconut .
harvested_from: when chopping their tops with an axe

items.name: Zebra Animal Bed
items.description: The Zebra Animal Bed is a bed for Mounts and Pets that has a zebra theme. It is available as part of the Creature Comforts DLC . Provides no additional attributes and is a cosmetic change to the Animal Bed .

items.name: Zebra Trophy
items.description: Zebra Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Zebra Vestige
items.description: Zebra Vestiges are used at the Trophy Bench to create a Zebra Trophy , which can help prospectors complete the Bestiary .
